{"title_page": "Cyrus Vance Jr.", "text_new": "{{about|the New York County District Attorney|his father, the former U.S. Secretary of the Army and Secretary of State|Cyrus Vance}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Cyrus Vance Jr.\n|image       = Cyrus Vance Junior.jpg\n|office      = [[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]]\n|term_start  = January 1, 2010\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Robert Morgenthau]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_name  = Cyrus Roberts Vance Jr.\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1954|6|14}}\n|birth_place = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|education   = [[Yale University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br>[[Georgetown University]] ([[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n|spouse      = Peggy McDonnell (1984\u2013present)\n|children    = 2\n|relatives   = [[Cyrus Vance]]\n|website     = {{url|manhattanda.com|Official website}}\n}}\n'''Cyrus Roberts Vance Jr.''' (born June 14, 1954) is the incumbent [[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]], [[New York (state)|New York]], encompassing the island of [[Manhattan]] and [[Marble Hill, Manhattan|Marble Hill]], as a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]. He was a principal partner at the law firm of Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello, & Bohrer, P.C. He is the son of the late [[Cyrus Vance]], former [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] under President [[Jimmy Carter]]. \n\n==Youth, family, and education==\nVance grew up in New York City. He is the son of Grace Elsie (Sloane) and [[Cyrus Vance|Cyrus Vance Sr.]], who served as [[Secretary of the Army]] under presidents [[John F. Kennedy]] and [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] and [[Deputy Secretary of Defense]] under President Johnson, then [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] to President [[Jimmy Carter]].\n\nVance attended the [[Buckley School (New York City)|Buckley]] and [[Groton School|Groton Schools]], and then went on to graduate from [[Yale University]]. He then earned his [[Juris Doctor]] from [[Georgetown University Law Center]] in 1982. While in law school, he planned campaign trips for [[Colorado]] Senator [[Gary Hart]].\n\nHe moved to [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]] in 1989, and back to New York City in 2005. He and his wife, printer and photographer Peggy McDonnell,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1984/05/06/style/peggy-mcdonnell-becomes-the-bride-of-cyrus-r-vance-jr-in-peapack-nj.html |title=Peggy McDonnell Becomes the Bride of Cyrus R. Vance Jr. in Peapack, N.J. |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=May 6, 1984 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=November 19, 2015 }}</ref> were married in 1984 and have two children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/18/nyregion/18vance.html|title=Getting Ready for a Race, Just in Case There's a Spot|last=Eligon|first=John|date=August 17, 2008|work=The New York Times|access-date=January 24, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\nUpon graduating from Georgetown, Vance joined the [[Manhattan District Attorney]]\u2019s office as an [[Assistant District Attorney]], where he supervised [[grand jury]] investigations and prosecuted cases involving murder, [[organized crime]], career criminals, [[political corruption]], international art fraud, and [[white-collar crime]].\n\nIn 1988, Vance moved to [[Seattle]] because, according to Vance, he wanted to build a name for himself independent of his father's influence.<ref>{{cite news | title=Getting Ready for a Race, Just in Case There\u2019s a Spot | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/18/nyregion/18vance.html?fta=y&pagewanted=all |work=The New York Times | date=August 18, 2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=John | last=Eligon}}</ref>  In 1995, Vance co-founded McNaul Ebel Nawrot Helgren & Vance.<ref>{{cite web | title=About McNaul Ebel | url=http://www.mcnaul.com/about | publisher=McNaul Ebel Narwot & Helgren LLC | year=2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091025103534/http://www.mcnaul.com/about | archive-date=October 25, 2009 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Cyrus R. Vance, Jr. |url=http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus |publisher=Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. |year=2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090101114103/http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus |archivedate=January 1, 2009 }}</ref>  During this time, Vance taught trial advocacy as an adjunct professor at [[Seattle University School of Law]].\n\nIn 2004, Vance returned to New York, where he joined Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. as a principal.\n\nVance is admitted to the bar in [[New York State]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington State]], and Washington, D.C., and to practice before the [[United States Supreme Court]], the U.S. District Courts for the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York|Southern District of New York]] and [[United States District Court for the Western District of Washington|Western]] and [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of Washington|Eastern Districts]] of Washington, and the U.S. [[United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit|Second]] and [[United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit|Ninth Circuit]] Courts of Appeals.\n\nVance is a Fellow in the [[American College of Trial Lawyers]], and is listed in ''The Best Lawyers in America \u2013 The New York Area\u2019s Best Lawyers''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestlawyers.com/magazines/ads/27737.pdf|title=Advertisement|accessdate=May 12, 2009}}{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and ''New York\u2019s Superlawyers \u2013 Manhattan Edition''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superlawyers.com/new-york-metro/lawyer/Cyrus-R-Vance-Jr/bc945302-450f-4297-b3e1-a46e0bf5c3d8.html|title=Cyrus Vance, Jr.|publisher=Key Professional Media, Inc.|accessdate=May 12, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829125811/http://www.superlawyers.com/new-york-metro/lawyer/Cyrus-R-Vance-Jr/bc945302-450f-4297-b3e1-a46e0bf5c3d8.html|archivedate=August 29, 2009}}</ref>\n\n[[File:DA Vance Photo 2.jpg|upright|thumb|left|District Attorney Vance at a town hall meeting]]\n\n==Public service==\nVance was a consulting expert to the Office of Family and Children Ombudsman in its investigation of the [[Wenatchee child abuse prosecutions]], and served as Special Assistant [[New York State Attorney General]] representing the state in investigations and litigation. He has served on sentencing commissions in two states, including New York, where he served on the Governor's Sentencing Commission, which helped overhaul New York\u2019s [[Rockefeller drug laws]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html|title=Sentencing Commission Calls for Drug Law Reform|author=New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services|accessdate=May 12, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101004065212/http://www.criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html|archivedate=October 4, 2010}}</ref>\n\nVance also served, by appointment of the Governor of New York, as a member of the New York State Appellate Division, First Department, Judicial Screening Panel which makes recommendations on judicial appointments.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}  Vance is a member of the Criminal Justice Council of the [[New York City Bar Association]], the [[Federal Bar Council]], and the New York Council of Defense Lawyers.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}\n\nHe is a member of the Board of Directors of the Fund for Modern Courts, the [[Sargent Shriver]] National Center on Poverty Law, and the [[Alzheimer's Drug Discovery Foundation]]. Cyrus Vance Sr., Vance's father died of Alzheimer's Disease in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/crvance.htm|title=Cyrus Roberts Vance, Lieutenant, United States Navy and Public Official | author=ArlingtonCemetery.net |publisher=Michael Robert Patterson |year=2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==2009 Manhattan District Attorney election==\n[[File:Vance Campaign Announcement.jpg|thumb|Vance campaign in May 2009]]\nIn 2008, Vance announced his intention to seek the District Attorney\u2019s office only if current District Attorney Robert Morgenthau decided to retire.<ref>{{cite news | title=Vance's Chance to Succeed Morgy? | url=http://nymag.com/news/intelligencer/44219/ | work=[[New York Magazine]] | date=February 18, 2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009}}</ref>  On March 9, 2009, ten days after Morgenthau made his decision to retire public, Vance officially announced his candidacy for the office.<ref>{{cite news | title=Manhattan DA Morgenthau to Retire after 35 Years | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/domesticNews/idUSTRE51Q3JT20090228 |agency=Reuters   | date=February 27, 2009 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=Daniel | last=Trotta}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyvanceforda.com/node/46 |title=Cy Vance Announces Candidacy For Manhattan DA |author=Press Release |publisher=Cyrus Vance for Manhattan DA |date=March 9, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903173442/http://www.cyvanceforda.com/node/46 |archivedate=September 3, 2009  }}</ref>  In an April 8, 2009 appearance on [[Charlie Rose]], Morgenthau said of Vance, \u201cI think Vance is by far the best qualified. Good lawyer, fair.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.charlierose.com/view/interview/10209 |title=A conversation with Robert Morgenthau |author=Charlie Rose Show |publisher=Charlie Rose |date=April 8, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090412064334/http://www.charlierose.com/view/interview/10209 |archivedate=April 12, 2009  }}</ref> [[Robert Morgenthau|Morgenthau]] officially endorsed Vance on June 25.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/26/nyregion/26vance.html | title = Manhattan District Attorney Endorses a Candidate to Succeed Him | first = John | last = Elingon | date = June 25, 2009 | work=The New York Times | accessdate =June 25, 2009 }}</ref>\n\nOther Democrats who endorsed Vance included former Mayor [[David Dinkins]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/blogs/dailypolitics/2009/04/dinkins-likes-mike-but-will-ba.html |title=Dinkins Likes Mike, But Will Back Thompson For Mayor |author=Elizabeth Benjamin |work=New York Daily News |date=April 30, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090503061344/http://www.nydailynews.com/blogs/dailypolitics/2009/04/dinkins-likes-mike-but-will-ba.html |archivedate=May 3, 2009  }}</ref> Public Advocate [[Betsy Gotbaum]],<ref>{{cite news | author=Michael Saul|title=Public Advocate Betsy Gotbaum backs Cy Vance Jr. in Manhattan District Attorney contest| url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/2009/04/24/2009-04-24_public_advocate_betsy_gotbaum_backs_cy_vance_jr_in_manhattan_district_attorney_c.html|work=New York Daily News | date=April 24, 2009 | accessdate=May 13, 2009}}</ref> [[Gloria Steinem]],\n[[Caroline Kennedy]], [[Robert F. Kennedy Jr.]], Congresswoman [[Nydia Vel\u00e1zquez]], Manhattan Borough President [[Scott Stringer]], and [[Barry Scheck]] and [[Peter Neufeld]] of The Innocence Project. ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/15/opinion/15sat4.html |title=Manhattan\u2019s District Attorney |work=The New York Times  |date=August 14, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> ''[[New York Daily News]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nypolitics.com/2009/08/09/daily-news-endorses-cy-vance-for-da/ |title=Daily News Endorses Cy Vance for DA |publisher=Nypolitics.com |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> ''[[New York Post]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/opinion/editorials/vance_for_manhattan_da_Dep6lpUNm4AhE0Mr2HAo1N |title=New York Post September 2, 2009 |work=New York Post  |date=August 31, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> and ''[[New York Amsterdam News]]''<ref>{{cite web |author=Free Online Access |url=http://www.amsterdamnews.com/articles/2009/09/06/news/doc4a9ff23f86fdb765443126.txt |title=New York Amsterdam News September 7, 2009 |publisher=Amsterdamnews.com |date=September 14, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130117132616/http://www.amsterdamnews.com/articles/2009/09/06/news/doc4a9ff23f86fdb765443126.txt |archivedate=January 17, 2013  }}</ref> also endorsed Vance.\n\nVance stated that as Manhattan District Attorney, he would develop a program of \u201cCommunity Based Justice\u201d,<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/PubArticleNY.jsp?id=1202433752939&slreturn=1 |title=Vance: 'Community-Based Justice' |first=Noeleen G. |last=Walder |journal=New York Law Journal |date=September 14, 2009}}</ref> in which teams of prosecutors would be aligned to specific precincts and communities so as to develop a working relationship with community members, police officers, and local organizations. According to Vance, the Community Based Justice Program would make crime reduction a central measure of performance. Vance has also proposed a plan designed to reduce the year-long case backlog in the New York Criminal Court where the overwhelming majority of criminal cases are brought.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/PubArticleNY.jsp?id=1202520565462&Efforts_to_Cut_Criminal_Backlog_in_Manhattan_Produce_Results |title=Efforts to Cut Criminal Backlog in Manhattan Produce Results |journal=New York Law Journal |first=John |last=Caher |date=October 28, 2011}}</ref> In addition to processing cases, Vance has expressed his commitment to establishing a conviction integrity panel to carefully review allegations of wrongful conviction and promoting alternatives to incarceration that do not compromise public safety.<ref>{{cite news | title=Letter \u2013 Alternatives to Jail | url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9906EFDF1430F931A15753C1A96E9C8B63 |work=The New York Times | date=October 22, 2008 | accessdate=July 2, 2009}}</ref>\n\nVance states that he has always been opposed to the death penalty.<ref>{{cite news | title=District Attorney hopefuls trash rival Snyder's flip on execution | url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/2009/04/23/2009-04-23_district_attorney_hopefuls_trash_snyder.html |work=New York Daily News | date=April 23, 2009 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=Michael | last=Saul}}</ref>\n\nVance emerged victorious after facing former judge and 2005 D.A. candidate [[Leslie Crocker Snyder]], and [[Richard Aborn]], another former Assistant District Attorney and [[gun control]] advocate, in the September 15, 2009 Democratic [[Primary election|primary]].<ref>{{cite news | title=Vance Captures Nomination for District Attorney | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/09/16/nyregion/16election.html?hp|work=The New York Times | date=September 16, 2009 | accessdate=September 16, 2009 | first1=David W. | last1=Chen | first2=John | last2=Eligon}}</ref> The victory ensured that Vance would become only the fourth person to run the office since 1941, given the traditional absence during Morgenthau's tenure of a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] backed opponent.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Vance is winner in primary vote for prosecutor |work=The New York Times |page=1 |date=September 16, 2009}}</ref>\n\nOn November 3, 2009, Vance won the general election with a 91 percent share of the votes cast.\n\n==Manhattan District Attorney==\n\nVance was sworn into office as the Manhattan District Attorney on January 1, 2010. Within a few months, he established or consolidated numerous new bureaus and units in an effort to modernize the District Attorney's Office. Vance's administration established a Conviction Integrity Program,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/05/nyregion/05wrongful.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |title=Prosecutor in Manhattan Will Monitor Convictions |first=John |last=Eligon |work=The New York Times |date=March 4, 2010}}</ref> Crime Strategies Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/25/nyregion/25vance.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |title=Top Prosecutor Creates a Unit On Crime Trends |first=John |last=Eligon |date=May 25, 2010 |work=The New York Times}}</ref> Cybercrime and Identity Theft Bureau,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204720204577129022552945152 |title=D.A. Cracks Down On Internet Crime |first=Michael |last=Rothfeld |work=Wall Street Journal |date= December 30, 2011}}</ref> Forensic Sciences/ Cold Case Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/15/nyregion/district-attorney-vance-sees-dna-as-tool-to-solve-cold-cases.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |first=Al |last=Baker |work=The New York Times |date=June 14, 2011 |title=In Manhattan, District Attorney Sees DNA as Tool to Solve Cold Cases}}</ref> Hate Crimes Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sohojournal.com/content/da-vance-announces-hate-crime-unit |title=D.A. Vance Announces Hate Crime Unit |work=SoHo Journal |access-date=January 10, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130141449/http://sohojournal.com/content/da-vance-announces-hate-crime-unit |archive-date=November 30, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Public Integrity Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/corruption-currents/2010/10/20/manhattan-da-announces-new-unit-to-investigate-public-corruption/ |title=Manhattan DA Announces New Unit To Investigate Public Corruption |date=October 20, 2010 |first=Samuel |last=Rubenfeld |work=Wall Street Journal}}</ref> Special Victims Bureau,<ref>[https://archive.is/20120728005937/http://www.dnainfo.com/20100924/downtown/manhattan-special-victims-be-serviced-by-new-da-bureau]</ref> and Vehicular Crimes Unit.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/119415/manhattan-d-a--expands-vehicular-crimes-unit/ |title=Manhattan D.A. Expands Vehicular Crimes Unit |publisher=NY1 |date=May 27, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100530130316/http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/119415/manhattan-d-a--expands-vehicular-crimes-unit/ |archivedate=May 30, 2010  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/05/28/prosecutors-get-along-and-a-crime-unit-gets-a-lift/ |date=May 28, 2010 |title=Prosecutors Get Along, and a Crime Unit Gets a Lift |work=The New York Times |first=John |last=Eligon}}</ref>\n\n[[File:February 2011 Press Conference.jpg|upright|thumb|right|Vance speaks at a February 2011 press conference]]\n\n===Notable cases===\nIn 2011, a New York prosecutor from Vance's office argued on behalf of billionaire and sex offender [[Jeffrey Epstein]], to New York Supreme Court Judge Ruth Pickholtz, asking for Epstein's sex offender status to be reduced. The reasoning was that Epstein had not been indicted and his underage victims had failed to cooperate in the case. The judge, however, denied the petition, and expressed bewilderment that a New York prosecutor would make such a request on behalf of a serial sex offender accused of molesting multiple girls: \"I have to tell you, I\u2019m a little overwhelmed because I have never seen a prosecutor\u2019s office do anything like this. I have done so many [sex offender registration hearings] much less troubling than this one where the [prosecutor] would never make a downward argument like this,\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article220097825.html |title=How a future Trump Cabinet member gave a serial sex abuser the deal of a lifetime|work=Miami Herald|first=Julie|last=Brown|date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> Jennifer Gaffney, then deputy chief of Cyrus Vance Jr.\u2019s sex-crimes unit, stated at the hearing that, \u201cThere is only an indictment for one victim. If an offender is not indicted for an offense, it is strong evidence that the offense did not occur.\u201d.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nypost.com/2018/12/01/manhattan-da-sided-with-pedophile-billionaire-after-botching-investigation| title=Manhattan DA sided with pedophile billionaire after botching investigation|work=New York Post|first=Rebecca|last=Rosenberg|date= December 1, 2018}}</ref> Pickholz rejected Gaffney\u2019s arguments and gave Epstein the highest sex-offender status \u2013 Level 3. While Vance denies having been aware of the hearing until years later, some law enforcement sources find it unlikely that he was clueless that his office was handling a sex-offender case involving a Manhattan mogul with close ties to Democrats.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nypost.com/2018/12/01/manhattan-da-sided-with-pedophile-billionaire-after-botching-investigation| title=Manhattan DA sided with pedophile billionaire after botching investigation|work=New York Post|first=Rebecca|last=Rosenberg|date= December 1, 2018}}</ref> In 2019, Epstein was arrested and charged with sex trafficking <ref>{{cite news | title=Jeffrey Epstein, Billionaire Long Accused of Molesting Minors, Is Charged |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/06/nyregion/jeffrey-epstein-arrested-sex-trafficking.html?campaign_id=60&instance_id=0&segment_id=14985&user_id=24491ccb6443e3eb868c38fc8dc7a8ab&regi_id=65747128ing-news |first=Patricia |last=Mazzei |work=New York Daily News |date=July 6, 2011}}</ref>.\n\nVance's recent successes include the sentencing of a serial rapist to 428 years to life in prison;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-12-12/news/30509662_1_serial-rapist-black-men-court-officers |title=Manhattan serial rapist Vincent Heyward socked with 428-year sentence Victims describe the lasting horror of his brutal knife-point attacks |work=New York Daily News |first=Barbara |last=Ross |date=December 12, 2011}}</ref> sentencing of a man to 23 years to life in prison for a domestic violence murder;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/11/28/jesus-alejandro-sentenced-for-brutal-murder-of-girlfriend/ |title=Jesus Alejandro Sentenced For Brutal Murder Of Girlfriend |publisher=CBS New York |date=November 28, 2011}}</ref> indictments against 26 individuals living in Manhattan who possessed graphic images of child sexual assault;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/06/14/manhattan-da-massive-child-cyber-porn-sting-ends-with-26-arrests/ |title=Manhattan DA: Massive Child Cyber Porn Sting Ends With 26 Arrests |publisher=CBS New York |date=June 14, 2011}}</ref> the sentencing of a man to at least 15 years in prison for a 2000 rape; a sentencing of a man to 25 to life in prison for a 1997 home invasion and murder;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-sentencing-1997-cold-case-murder |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=District Attorney Vance announces sentencing in 1997 cold case murder |date=June 29, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111227125457/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-sentencing-1997-cold-case-murder |archive-date=December 27, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> an indictment against another man for a 1986 rape and murder;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/man-indicted-24-year-old-%E2%80%9Ccold-case%E2%80%9D-rape-and-murder |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=Man indicted in 24-year-old \"cold case\" rape murder |date=July 6, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020012703/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/man-indicted-24-year-old-%E2%80%9Ccold-case%E2%80%9D-rape-and-murder |archive-date=October 20, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the guilty plea of a man for attacking a woman in the restroom of a bar in Hell's Kitchen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-guilty-plea-brutal-attack-woman-hell%E2%80%99s-kitchen-bar |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=District Attorney Vance announces guilty plea in brutal attack on woman in Hell's Kitchen bar |date=July 18, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026041809/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-guilty-plea-brutal-attack-woman-hell%E2%80%99s-kitchen-bar |archive-date=October 26, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nVance has also won convictions in an October 2009 drunk-driving incident that killed 11-year-old Leandra Rosado, resulting in the creation of [[Leandra's Law]]; and a case of two men in a 2005 murder-for-hire plot. In January 2011, the District Attorney's Forensic Sciences/ Cold Case Unit announced an indictment against noted serial killer [[Rodney Alcala]] for two Manhattan homicides in the 1970s.\n[[File:PC 6.14.11 1 (740x470) small.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Vance at June 2011 press conference on child assault]]\n\nVance's newly created Major Economic Crimes Bureau has won convictions in the $120 million-dollar art fraud prosecution of the Salander-O'Reilly Gallery, the gallery's president [[Lawrence Salander]] and director Leigh Morse, in which [[Robert De Niro]] was one of the principal witnesses for the prosecution;<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/robert-de-niro-to-testify-as-ex-salander-employee-starts-trial-for-fraud.html | work=Bloomberg | first=Philip | last=Boroff | title=De Niro Testifies Against Dealer Accused of Stealing Dad's Art | date=March 19, 2011}}</ref> a $100 million-dollar securities fraud scheme in which [[Yale University]] was one of the victims;<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/20/nyregion/lawyer-convicted-in-100-million-stock-swindle.html?scp=1&sq=mazzuto&st=cse | work=The New York Times | first=John | last=Eligon | title=Lawyer Convicted in $100 Million Stock Swindle | date=July 19, 2011}}</ref> a $100 million-dollar mortgage fraud case;<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/local/mortgage_scam_con_gets_jail_time_XeVcWp0DuPc4JA7KazTayN | work=New York Post | first=David K. | last=Li | title=$100M mortgage scam con gets jail time | date=September 21, 2010 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122201207/http://www.nypost.com/p/news/local/mortgage_scam_con_gets_jail_time_XeVcWp0DuPc4JA7KazTayN | archivedate=January 22, 2012 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and a $7 million-dollar Ponzi scheme.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/money-manager-de-chimay-sentenced-to-3-to-9-years-for-fraud-1-.html | work=Bloomberg | title=Money Manager De Chimay Sentenced to Three to Nine Years by New York Judge | date=March 23, 2011}}</ref> The District Attorney's Office in June 2011 announced indictments in a conspiracy involving 11 corporations who evaded U.S. economic sanctions on Iran by funneling tens of millions of dollars through Manhattan banks.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/20/nyregion/iranian-shipper-accused-of-sneaking-money-through-ny-banks.html | work=The New York Times | first=Jo | last=Becker | title=Iranian Shipper Accused of Sneaking Money Through N.Y. Banks | date=June 20, 2011}}</ref> To date, Vance's administration has brought hundreds of millions of dollars in settlements to New York City.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2010-09-25/local/27076255_1_budget-cuts-budget-war-budget-battle | location=New York | work=Daily News | title=Virginia girl found eating herself in cage in mobile home; parents Brian and Shannon Gore charged | first=Melissa | last=Grace | date=September 25, 2010}}</ref>\n\nCyrus Vance prosecuted programmer [[Sergey Aleynikov]] for duplicating computer code from Goldman Sachs, following the reversal of his federal conviction by the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit. The state case found Aleynikov guilty. However, on July 6, 2015, a New York State Supreme Court justice overturned that decision, but an appellate court reinstated the jury's guilty verdict on January 24, 2017. 148 AD3d 77 [1st Dept 2017], affirmed, 31 NY3d 383 [2018].\n\n===Abacus Federal Savings Bank case===\n\nIn 2009, [[Abacus Federal Savings Bank]], a small Chinese-American family-run bank in New York City's Chinatown, self-reported a mortgage fraud committed by an ex-employee to its regulators. It led Cyrus Vance's office to later accuse the bank itself of mortgage fraud. In an unusual move characterized by critics as an effort at at grandstanding, Vance's office orchestrated a parade of ex-employees of the bank in a chain, handcuffed to each other, in front of reporters.<ref name=\"pbs.org\">[http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/article/after-the-crash-big-banks-got-bailouts-abacus-faced-charges/ \"After the Crash, Big Banks Got Bailouts. Abacus Faced Charges.\"], September 12, 2016.</ref>  After Vance spent five years and $10 million prosecuting the bank for larceny, the bank and its employees were found not guilty on all 80 charges.\n\nThe bank was the only New York bank so charged during the Great Recession, although Vance said that [[Citibank]], among others, had behaved badly. The episode was covered in a feature-length documentary by [[Steve James (producer)|Steve James]], ''[[Abacus: Small Enough to Jail]]'', which characterized Vance as throwing the bank's owners under the bus in an effort to appear tough on white-collar crime.<ref name=\"Ebert Review\">{{cite news |last1=Seitz |first1=Matt Zoller |title=Abacus: Small Enough to Jail |url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/abacus-small-enough-to-jail-2017 |accessdate=20 March 2019 |agency=Roger Ebert.com |date=May 26, 2017}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[Toronto International Film Festival]] in 2016,<ref>[http://www.tiff.net/films/abacus-small-enough-to-jail/]</ref> was broadcast on [[PBS Frontline]] in 2017, and was nominated for an Oscar.<ref name=\"pbs.org\"/><ref>\n[http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/film/abacus/ \"Abacus: Small Enough to Jail\"], Retrieved September 13, 2017.</ref>\n\n===Motor vehicle prosecution===\n\nTransportation advocates have criticized Vance's office for what they see as a history of failing to fully prosecute motor vehicle offenses that result in death or serious injury to pedestrians and cyclists.\n\nIn July 2010, no charges were filed when an MTA tow truck struck and killed a seven-year-old boy standing on the sidewalk.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://nypost.com/2010/07/31/bridge-tragedy/ | work=The New York Post | first1=Kenneth M. | last1=Walsh | title=Bridge tragedy | date=July 31, 2010}}</ref> In October 2010, Vance declined to press charges in the [[dooring]] death of Marcus Ewing, on the rationale that, because the engine was not running and because the person who opened the door into Ewing's path did not have the keys in his possession, that person could not be prosecuted as a driver.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.vaccaroandwhite.com/bicycles/gothamist-how-to-kill-a-cyclist-and-walk-away/ | work=Vaccaro & White | first1=Sam | last1=Vaccaro | first2=Adam | last2=White | title=Gothamist: How to Kill a Cyclist and Walk Away | date=February 4, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, a cab driver hopped a curb, injuring several pedestrians and severing the leg of a British tourist. Despite a history of driving offenses, and admitting that he intentionally hit the gas before entering the sidewalk, the driver was able to regain his cab license, and after a two-month investigation, no charges were filed.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.streetsblog.org/2013/11/14/no-charges-from-cy-vance-for-cab-driver-who-maimed-tourist-sian-green/ | work=Streetsblog NYC | first1=Brad | last1=Aaron | title=No Charges From Cy Vance for Cab Driver Who Maimed Tourist Sian Green | date=November 14, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2014, Vance's office offered a plea to a driver accused of intentionally striking a cyclist with his car. The deal reduced charges of third-degree assault, punishable by up to a year in jail, to leaving the scene of an accident with property damage. The motorist paid a $250 fine.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.streetsblog.org/2014/10/22/da-cy-vance-250-fine-for-motorist-accused-of-deliberately-striking-cyclist/ | work=Streetsblog NYC | first1=Brad | last1=Aaron | title=DA Cy Vance: $250 Fine for Motorist Accused of Deliberately Striking Cyclist | date=October 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe lack of prosecutorial aggressiveness from Vance's office, in spite of recently passed vulnerable user laws<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2010/10/12/new_law_inspired_by_chinatown_van_c.php | work=Gothamist | first1=John Del | last1=Signore | title=New Law Inspired By Chinatown Van Crash Takes Effect | date=October 12, 2010 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030093804/http://gothamist.com/2010/10/12/new_law_inspired_by_chinatown_van_c.php | archivedate=October 30, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and Vance's own initiatives<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.transalt.org/news/releases/4530 | work=Transportation Alternatives | first1=Wiley | last1=Norvell | title=Statement on Manhattan DA Cy Vance's New Traffic Safety Initiatives | date=May 27, 2010}}</ref> has led to widespread media commentary on whether New York City cyclists can reasonably expect protection from the justice system.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2011/02/04/how_to_kill_a_cyclist_and_walk_away.php | work=Gothamist | first1=John Del | last1=Signore | title=How to Kill a Cyclist and Walk Away | date=February 4, 2011 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128014124/http://gothamist.com/2011/02/04/how_to_kill_a_cyclist_and_walk_away.php | archivedate=January 28, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/10/opinion/sunday/is-it-ok-to-kill-cyclists.html?pagewanted=all | work=The New York Times | first1=Daniel | last1=Duane | title=Is It O.K. to Kill Cyclists? | date=November 9, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, during an investigation into faded white flags flown over the Brooklyn Bridge in July 2014, Vance's office subpoenaed a farcical Twitter account, purporting to be the bicycle industry lobby, which had jokingly taken responsibility for the flag swap.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2014/08/08/parody_twitter_account_subpoenaed_o.php#photo-1 | work=Gothamist | first1=Ben | last1=Yakas | title=Manhattan DA Subpoenas Parody Twitter Account Over Obvious Brooklyn Bridge White Flag Joke | date=August 8, 2014 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010010554/http://gothamist.com/2014/08/08/parody_twitter_account_subpoenaed_o.php#photo-1 | archivedate=October 10, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The flags were later revealed to be the work of German artists.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/11030119/Mystery-of-white-flags-on-Brooklyn-Bridge-solved-as-German-artists-claim-responsibility.html | work=The Telegraph | agency=Associated Press | title=Mystery of white flags on Brooklyn Bridge solved as German artists claim responsibility | date=August 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Dominique Strauss-Kahn case===\nVance initially came under criticism by the media for ultimately dismissing charges in the [[Dominique Strauss-Kahn sexual assault case]], after the French head of the [[International Monetary Fund]] was arrested, based on accusations by a hotel maid at the [[Sofitel]] hotel who said he had forced her to perform oral sex when she came to clean his room. Kahn admitted the encounter had taken place, but maintained the sex was consensual. <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rsr.ch/#/info/les-titres/monde/3252521-le-procureur-dans-la-tourmente-de-l-affaire-dsk.html |title=Affaire DSK: l'enqu\u00eate se poursuit |language=French |publisher=Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Suisse |date=July 6, 2011}}</ref> However, Vance was praised by New York City Mayor [[Michael Bloomberg]],<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/06/nyregion/strauss-kahn-lawyers-and-prosecution-to-meet.html | work=The New York Times | first1=John | last1=Eligon | first2=William K. | last2=Rashbaum | title=Strauss-Kahn Lawyers and Prosecution Meet | date=July 5, 2011}}</ref> former Mayor [[Ed Koch]], former Manhattan District Attorney [[Robert Morgenthau]],<ref>{{cite news| url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/07/07/morgenthau-comes-to-vances-defense/?scp=1&sq=morgenthau&st=cse | work=The New York Times | first=John | last=Eligon | title=Morgenthau Comes to Vance's Defense | date=July 7, 2011}}</ref> and other prominent litigators and government officials for adhering to prosecutorial protocol and acting \"with integrity\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/politics/142305/ny1-online--ny1-wise-guys-7-5-11 |publisher=NY1 |title=NY1 Online: NY1 Wise Guys 7/5/11 |date=July 5, 2011 }}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>{{explain|date=October 2017}} Vance has also been applauded in editorials by the ''New York Times,'' ''Wall Street Journal,'' and the ''New York Daily News'' for making a \"tough but fair and just call\"{{clarify|date=October 2017}} in \"an exceptional case\" in which a woman made a \"credible\" accusation against a very powerful man.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/05/opinion/05nocera.html?_r=1&ref=joenocera | work=The New York Times | first=Joe | last=Nocera | title=The D.A. Did the Right Thing | date=July 4, 2011}}</ref><ref name=WSJDSK>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424053111903461304576526503562746350?KEYWORDS=dominique+strauss-kahn |title=The Judgment on DSK |date=August 24, 2011 |work=Wall Street Journal}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/opinion/da-cy-vance-made-tough-fair-call-dismiss-charges-dominique-strauss-kahn-article-1.950312 |title=DA Cy Vance made tough but fair and just call to dismiss charges against Dominique Strauss-Kahn |work=New York Daily News |date=August 23, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/24/opinion/the-strauss-kahn-case.html?scp=4&sq=vance%20august%2024&st=cse |title=The Strauss-Kahn Case |date=August 23, 2011 |work=The New York Times}}</ref> The ''Wall Street Journal'' wrote: \"DSK got neither more nor less than he deserved\u2014something for which he can blame, and thank, Cy Vance and America's justice system.\"<ref name=WSJDSK/> He dropped all charges against the defendant on August 11, stating that he could not prove Kahn's guilt beyond reasonable doubt due to questions about the credibility of the accuser Nafissatou Diallo.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/23/dominique-strauss-kahn-charges-dropped|date=August 23, 2011|title=\nDominique Strauss-Kahn walks free from New York court}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/jan/19/dominique-strauss-kahn-prosecutor-reasons|date=January 19, 2012|title=Dominique Strauss-Kahn prosecutor tells why he dropped case}}</ref>\n\n===Paul Manafort===\n{{further|Trials of Paul Manafort}}\nOn March 13, 2019 Vance filed 16 indictments charging mortgage fraud against [[Paul Manafort]], former chairman of  [[Donald Trump presidential campaign, 2016|Donald Trump's 2016 presidential campaign]]. Vance said the charges stemmed from an investigation launched in March 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/regulation/433875-manafort-indicted-by-manhattan-district-attorney|title=Manafort indicted by Manhattan DA on mortgage fraud charges|last=Samuels|first=Brett|date=March 13, 2019|work=The Hill|accessdate=14 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Political contributions and non-prosecutions===\n{{expand section|date=October 2017}}\nFrom August 2017, allegations appeared across various news media outlets concerning Vance's associations, and certain contributions made to his office in relation to past cases. Under scrutiny are the Manhattan DA's handling of [[Harvey Weinstein sexual misconduct allegations|allegations of sexual assault]] against film producer [[Harvey Weinstein]],<ref>[http://www.businessinsider.com/cyrus-vance-harvey-weinstein-audio-trump-2017-10?IR=T Manhattan district attorney defends handling of 2015 Harvey Weinstein investigation as shocking audio emerges]</ref> and allegations of his handling of [[Trump SoHo#Fraud lawsuit|improper conduct by members of the Trump family around the Trump SoHo development]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Manhattan DA ignores questions regarding concern over donations |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=October 7, 2017 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/oct/07/cyrus-vance-donations-donald-ivanka-trump-harvey-weinstein }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=How Ivanka Trump and Donald Trump, Jr., Avoided a Criminal Indictment |work=[[The New Yorker]] |date=October 4, 2017 |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/how-ivanka-trump-and-donald-trump-jr-avoided-a-criminal-indictment }}</ref> Critics have suggested that contributions to the DA around these times were directly linked to Vance not prosecuting these cases. Vance has defended the actions of his office, citing insufficient evidence to prosecute in each case.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vance Returned Trump Lawyer\u2019s Donation After Reporters\u2019 Questions |work=New York Times |date=October 4, 2017 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/04/nyregion/cyrus-vance-manhattan-da-trump-lawyer.html }}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018,  New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo announced that the New York State attorney general will investigate the Manhattan district attorney's handling of a 2015 sexual abuse case involving disgraced media mogul Harvey Weinstein.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/19/entertainment/times-up-cyrus-vance/index.html|title=District attorney who didn't prosecute Weinstein will be investigated|last=Joseph|first=Sandra Gonzalez and Elizabeth|work=CNN|access-date=March 20, 2018}}</ref> NYPD investigators who investigated the 2015 case believed that the sexual abuse case was strong enough to be prosecuted, but Vance opted not to prosecute the case.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/mar/17/weinstein-ambra-battilana-case-hidden-nypd-district-attorney|title=NYPD reportedly hid Weinstein accuser, fearing district attorney would sink case|last=Helmore|first=Edward|date=March 17, 2018|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref> \n\nThe case concerned a 22-year old Filipina-Italian model - [[Ambra Gutierrez|Ambra Battilana Gutierrez]], who went straight to the police after Weinstein lunged at her, groping her breasts and attempting to put a hand up her skirt while she protested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/oct/11/the-allegations-against-harvey-weinstein-what-we-know-so-far|title=Harvey Weinstein: the women who have accused him|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The next day she met with Weinstein, equipped with a NYPD wire tap. In the recording, published by The New Yorker and ABC News , Weinstein insists - \"I'm telling you right now, get in here.\" Gutierrez explicitly refuses, adding '''\"'''yesterday was kind of aggressive for me\" and asks why he had groped her breast the day before. \u201cOh, please, I\u2019m sorry, just come on in. I\u2019m used to that. Come on. Please\u201d he says. \u201cYou are used to that?\u201d Gutierrez asks. \u201cYes,\u201d Weinstein replies, later adding: \u201cDon\u2019t ruin your friendship with me for five minutes.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-10-11/harvey-weinstein-full-transcript-of-audio-with-ambra-gutierrez/9037268|title=Harvey Weinstein: Full transcript of the 'horrifying' exchange with Ambra Gutierrez|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Joseph|first=Sandra Gonzalez and Elizabeth|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/19/entertainment/times-up-cyrus-vance/index.html|title=District attorney who didn't prosecute Weinstein will be investigated|work=CNN|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Stelter|first=Lisa France and Brian|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/10/media/harvey-weinstein-new-yorker-magazine/index.html|title=Harvey Weinstein accused of rape in New Yorker story|work=CNNMoney|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''The Guardian'', the investigators were at the time under the belief that Vance would undermine the case, given that he had previously dropped a similar case against Dominique Strauss-Kahn.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nVance has heavily prosecuted possession of [[gravity knife|gravity knives]], disproportionately arresting and indicting defendants of color.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Grant |first1=Melissa Gira |title=Manhattan D.A.\u2019s Office Still Prosecuting People for the Knives They Carry for Work |url=https://theappeal.org/manhattan-d-a-s-office-still-prosecuting-people-for-the-knives-they-carry-for-work/ |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The Appeal |publisher=The Appeal |date=26 November 2018 |language=en}}</ref> The law banning them, which was interpreted broadly by Vance and is enforced mainly in Manhattan, has been the subject of several repeal efforts in the New York state legislature. Governor Andrew Cuomo has vetoed two such repeal bills passed in two years by majority votes in both chambers of the state congress.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Victor |first1=Daniel |title=Cuomo Vetoes Bill to Overhaul \u2018Gravity Knife\u2019 Law for Second Straight Year |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/24/nyregion/gravity-knife-cuomo-veto.html |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The New York Times |publisher=The New York Times |date=24 October 2017}}</ref> Despite the 70,000 people arrested under this law in ten years, Vance declined to take action against the more than 100 hardware stores selling potential gravity knives in the city.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/new-york-just-saved-a-law-used-to-jail-thousands-of-minorities|title=New York Just Saved a Law Used to Jail Thousands of Minorities|last=Campbell|first=Jon|date=October 24, 2017|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=October 24, 2017}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 27, 2019, in Cracco v. Vance, No. 14 Civ. 8235 (SDNY), a federal judge  ruled that Vance's office had applied the  law unconstitutionally, resulting a in a lack of notice of prohibited behavior as well as allowing for arbitrary and discriminatory enforcement.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gothamist.com/2019/03/29/gravity_knife_unconstitutional.php|title=Federal Judge Rules Controversial Gravity Knife Law Is Too Vague To Enforce|last=Offenhartz|first=Jake|work=Gothamist|access-date=March 29, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330175545/http://gothamist.com/2019/03/29/gravity_knife_unconstitutional.php|archive-date=March 30, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Soon after, state lawmakers Dan Quart and Diane Savino introduced a third iteration of the bill repealing the gravity knife ban. On May 31, 2019, Governor Andrew Cuomo signed the bill into law, making gravity knives legal to possess in the state of New York.<ref>{{cite news |last1=OFFENHARTZ |first1=JAKE |title=Cuomo Signs Bill To End 'Absurd' Gravity Knife Ban That He Supported For Years |url=https://gothamist.com/2019/05/31/gravity_knife_ban_ends.php |accessdate=14 June 2019 |publisher=The Gothamist |date=31 May 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531213959/http://gothamist.com/2019/05/31/gravity_knife_ban_ends.php |archive-date=May 31, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=McKinley |first1=Jesse |title=The \u2018Gravity Knife\u2019 Led to Thousands of Questionable Arrests. Now It\u2019s Legal. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/31/nyregion/ny-gravity-knife-law.html |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=31 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Affiliations==\nVance serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the [[Police Athletic League of New York City]], a non-profit youth development agency that helps inner-city children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palnyc.org/800-PAL-4KIDS/BoardOfDirectors.aspx |title=Board of Directors |publisher=Police Athletic League NYC |accessdate=July 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727162754/http://www.palnyc.org/800-PAL-4KIDS/BoardOfDirectors.aspx |archivedate=July 27, 2011  }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Tax returns of Donald Trump]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.manhattanda.com/ Manhattan District Attorney's Office (official website)]\n*[http://www.cyvanceforda.com/ Cyrus Vance For District Attorney (official campaign website)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090101114103/http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Isaon, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. Website on Cyrus Vance]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101004065212/http://www.criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html Commission on Sentencing Reform Recommendation Announcement]\n*[https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/15/nyregion/district-attorney-vance-sees-dna-as-tool-to-solve-cold-cases.html?src=recg 'In Manhattan, District Attorney Sees DNA as Tool to Solve Cold Cases'], Al Baker, ''[[The New York Times]]'', June 14, 2011\n*{{C-SPAN|Cyrus Vance 02}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Morgenthau]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]]|years=2010\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Manhattan DA}}\n{{New York City District Attorneys}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vance, Cyrus Jr}}\n[[Category:American prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Politicians from New York City]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Democrats]]\n[[Category:New York (state) lawyers]]\n<!--[[Category:Liberal politicians]] Temporary, category is being considered for deletion.-->\n[[Category:New York County District Attorneys]]\n[[Category:Real property lawyers]]\n[[Category:Georgetown University Law Center alumni]]\n[[Category:Yale University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Manhattan]]\n[[Category:Seattle University faculty]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Buckley School (New York City) alumni]]\n[[Category:Groton School alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the New York County District Attorney|his father, the former U.S. Secretary of the Army and Secretary of State|Cyrus Vance}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Cyrus Vance Jr.\n|image       = Cyrus Vance Junior.jpg\n|office      = [[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]]\n|term_start  = January 1, 2010\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Robert Morgenthau]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_name  = Cyrus Roberts Vance Jr.\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1954|6|14}}\n|birth_place = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n|education   = [[Yale University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br>[[Georgetown University]] ([[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n|spouse      = Peggy McDonnell (1984\u2013present)\n|children    = 2\n|relatives   = [[Cyrus Vance]]\n|website     = {{url|manhattanda.com|Official website}}\n}}\n'''Cyrus Roberts Vance Jr.''' (born June 14, 1954) is the incumbent [[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]], [[New York (state)|New York]], encompassing the island of [[Manhattan]] and [[Marble Hill, Manhattan|Marble Hill]], as a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]. He was a principal partner at the law firm of Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello, & Bohrer, P.C. He is the son of the late [[Cyrus Vance]], former [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] under President [[Jimmy Carter]]. \n\n==Youth, family, and education==\nVance grew up in New York City. He is the son of Grace Elsie (Sloane) and [[Cyrus Vance|Cyrus Vance Sr.]], who served as [[Secretary of the Army]] under presidents [[John F. Kennedy]] and [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] and [[Deputy Secretary of Defense]] under President Johnson, then [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] to President [[Jimmy Carter]].\n\nVance attended the [[Buckley School (New York City)|Buckley]] and [[Groton School|Groton Schools]], and then went on to graduate from [[Yale University]]. He then earned his [[Juris Doctor]] from [[Georgetown University Law Center]] in 1982. While in law school, he planned campaign trips for [[Colorado]] Senator [[Gary Hart]].\n\nHe moved to [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]] in 1989, and back to New York City in 2005. He and his wife, printer and photographer Peggy McDonnell,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1984/05/06/style/peggy-mcdonnell-becomes-the-bride-of-cyrus-r-vance-jr-in-peapack-nj.html |title=Peggy McDonnell Becomes the Bride of Cyrus R. Vance Jr. in Peapack, N.J. |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=May 6, 1984 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=November 19, 2015 }}</ref> were married in 1984 and have two children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/18/nyregion/18vance.html|title=Getting Ready for a Race, Just in Case There's a Spot|last=Eligon|first=John|date=August 17, 2008|work=The New York Times|access-date=January 24, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==Legal career==\nUpon graduating from Georgetown, Vance joined the [[Manhattan District Attorney]]\u2019s office as an [[Assistant District Attorney]], where he supervised [[grand jury]] investigations and prosecuted cases involving murder, [[organized crime]], career criminals, [[political corruption]], international art fraud, and [[white-collar crime]].\n\nIn 1988, Vance moved to [[Seattle]] because, according to Vance, he wanted to build a name for himself independent of his father's influence.<ref>{{cite news | title=Getting Ready for a Race, Just in Case There\u2019s a Spot | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/18/nyregion/18vance.html?fta=y&pagewanted=all |work=The New York Times | date=August 18, 2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=John | last=Eligon}}</ref>  In 1995, Vance co-founded McNaul Ebel Nawrot Helgren & Vance.<ref>{{cite web | title=About McNaul Ebel | url=http://www.mcnaul.com/about | publisher=McNaul Ebel Narwot & Helgren LLC | year=2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091025103534/http://www.mcnaul.com/about | archive-date=October 25, 2009 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Cyrus R. Vance, Jr. |url=http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus |publisher=Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. |year=2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090101114103/http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus |archivedate=January 1, 2009 }}</ref>  During this time, Vance taught trial advocacy as an adjunct professor at [[Seattle University School of Law]].\n\nIn 2004, Vance returned to New York, where he joined Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Iason, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. as a principal.\n\nVance is admitted to the bar in [[New York State]], [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington State]], and Washington, D.C., and to practice before the [[United States Supreme Court]], the U.S. District Courts for the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York|Southern District of New York]] and [[United States District Court for the Western District of Washington|Western]] and [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of Washington|Eastern Districts]] of Washington, and the U.S. [[United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit|Second]] and [[United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit|Ninth Circuit]] Courts of Appeals.\n\nVance is a Fellow in the [[American College of Trial Lawyers]], and is listed in ''The Best Lawyers in America \u2013 The New York Area\u2019s Best Lawyers''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bestlawyers.com/magazines/ads/27737.pdf|title=Advertisement|accessdate=May 12, 2009}}{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and ''New York\u2019s Superlawyers \u2013 Manhattan Edition''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superlawyers.com/new-york-metro/lawyer/Cyrus-R-Vance-Jr/bc945302-450f-4297-b3e1-a46e0bf5c3d8.html|title=Cyrus Vance, Jr.|publisher=Key Professional Media, Inc.|accessdate=May 12, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090829125811/http://www.superlawyers.com/new-york-metro/lawyer/Cyrus-R-Vance-Jr/bc945302-450f-4297-b3e1-a46e0bf5c3d8.html|archivedate=August 29, 2009}}</ref>\n\n[[File:DA Vance Photo 2.jpg|upright|thumb|left|District Attorney Vance at a town hall meeting]]\n\n==Public service==\nVance was a consulting expert to the Office of Family and Children Ombudsman in its investigation of the [[Wenatchee child abuse prosecutions]], and served as Special Assistant [[New York State Attorney General]] representing the state in investigations and litigation. He has served on sentencing commissions in two states, including New York, where he served on the Governor's Sentencing Commission, which helped overhaul New York\u2019s [[Rockefeller drug laws]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html|title=Sentencing Commission Calls for Drug Law Reform|author=New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services|accessdate=May 12, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101004065212/http://www.criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html|archivedate=October 4, 2010}}</ref>\n\nVance also served, by appointment of the Governor of New York, as a member of the New York State Appellate Division, First Department, Judicial Screening Panel which makes recommendations on judicial appointments.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}  Vance is a member of the Criminal Justice Council of the [[New York City Bar Association]], the [[Federal Bar Council]], and the New York Council of Defense Lawyers.{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}\n\nHe is a member of the Board of Directors of the Fund for Modern Courts, the [[Sargent Shriver]] National Center on Poverty Law, and the [[Alzheimer's Drug Discovery Foundation]]. Cyrus Vance Sr., Vance's father died of Alzheimer's Disease in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/crvance.htm|title=Cyrus Roberts Vance, Lieutenant, United States Navy and Public Official | author=ArlingtonCemetery.net |publisher=Michael Robert Patterson |year=2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009}}</ref>\n\n==2009 Manhattan District Attorney election==\n[[File:Vance Campaign Announcement.jpg|thumb|Vance campaign in May 2009]]\nIn 2008, Vance announced his intention to seek the District Attorney\u2019s office only if current District Attorney Robert Morgenthau decided to retire.<ref>{{cite news | title=Vance's Chance to Succeed Morgy? | url=http://nymag.com/news/intelligencer/44219/ | work=[[New York Magazine]] | date=February 18, 2008 | accessdate=May 12, 2009}}</ref>  On March 9, 2009, ten days after Morgenthau made his decision to retire public, Vance officially announced his candidacy for the office.<ref>{{cite news | title=Manhattan DA Morgenthau to Retire after 35 Years | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/domesticNews/idUSTRE51Q3JT20090228 |agency=Reuters   | date=February 27, 2009 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=Daniel | last=Trotta}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyvanceforda.com/node/46 |title=Cy Vance Announces Candidacy For Manhattan DA |author=Press Release |publisher=Cyrus Vance for Manhattan DA |date=March 9, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903173442/http://www.cyvanceforda.com/node/46 |archivedate=September 3, 2009  }}</ref>  In an April 8, 2009 appearance on [[Charlie Rose]], Morgenthau said of Vance, \u201cI think Vance is by far the best qualified. Good lawyer, fair.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.charlierose.com/view/interview/10209 |title=A conversation with Robert Morgenthau |author=Charlie Rose Show |publisher=Charlie Rose |date=April 8, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090412064334/http://www.charlierose.com/view/interview/10209 |archivedate=April 12, 2009  }}</ref> [[Robert Morgenthau|Morgenthau]] officially endorsed Vance on June 25.<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/06/26/nyregion/26vance.html | title = Manhattan District Attorney Endorses a Candidate to Succeed Him | first = John | last = Elingon | date = June 25, 2009 | work=The New York Times | accessdate =June 25, 2009 }}</ref>\n\nOther Democrats who endorsed Vance included former Mayor [[David Dinkins]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/blogs/dailypolitics/2009/04/dinkins-likes-mike-but-will-ba.html |title=Dinkins Likes Mike, But Will Back Thompson For Mayor |author=Elizabeth Benjamin |work=New York Daily News |date=April 30, 2009 |accessdate=May 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090503061344/http://www.nydailynews.com/blogs/dailypolitics/2009/04/dinkins-likes-mike-but-will-ba.html |archivedate=May 3, 2009  }}</ref> Public Advocate [[Betsy Gotbaum]],<ref>{{cite news | author=Michael Saul|title=Public Advocate Betsy Gotbaum backs Cy Vance Jr. in Manhattan District Attorney contest| url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/2009/04/24/2009-04-24_public_advocate_betsy_gotbaum_backs_cy_vance_jr_in_manhattan_district_attorney_c.html|work=New York Daily News | date=April 24, 2009 | accessdate=May 13, 2009}}</ref> [[Gloria Steinem]],\n[[Caroline Kennedy]], [[Robert F. Kennedy Jr.]], Congresswoman [[Nydia Vel\u00e1zquez]], Manhattan Borough President [[Scott Stringer]], and [[Barry Scheck]] and [[Peter Neufeld]] of The Innocence Project. ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/15/opinion/15sat4.html |title=Manhattan\u2019s District Attorney |work=The New York Times  |date=August 14, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> ''[[New York Daily News]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nypolitics.com/2009/08/09/daily-news-endorses-cy-vance-for-da/ |title=Daily News Endorses Cy Vance for DA |publisher=Nypolitics.com |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> ''[[New York Post]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/opinion/editorials/vance_for_manhattan_da_Dep6lpUNm4AhE0Mr2HAo1N |title=New York Post September 2, 2009 |work=New York Post  |date=August 31, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011}}</ref> and ''[[New York Amsterdam News]]''<ref>{{cite web |author=Free Online Access |url=http://www.amsterdamnews.com/articles/2009/09/06/news/doc4a9ff23f86fdb765443126.txt |title=New York Amsterdam News September 7, 2009 |publisher=Amsterdamnews.com |date=September 14, 2009 |accessdate=July 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130117132616/http://www.amsterdamnews.com/articles/2009/09/06/news/doc4a9ff23f86fdb765443126.txt |archivedate=January 17, 2013  }}</ref> also endorsed Vance.\n\nVance stated that as Manhattan District Attorney, he would develop a program of \u201cCommunity Based Justice\u201d,<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/PubArticleNY.jsp?id=1202433752939&slreturn=1 |title=Vance: 'Community-Based Justice' |first=Noeleen G. |last=Walder |journal=New York Law Journal |date=September 14, 2009}}</ref> in which teams of prosecutors would be aligned to specific precincts and communities so as to develop a working relationship with community members, police officers, and local organizations. According to Vance, the Community Based Justice Program would make crime reduction a central measure of performance. Vance has also proposed a plan designed to reduce the year-long case backlog in the New York Criminal Court where the overwhelming majority of criminal cases are brought.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.newyorklawjournal.com/PubArticleNY.jsp?id=1202520565462&Efforts_to_Cut_Criminal_Backlog_in_Manhattan_Produce_Results |title=Efforts to Cut Criminal Backlog in Manhattan Produce Results |journal=New York Law Journal |first=John |last=Caher |date=October 28, 2011}}</ref> In addition to processing cases, Vance has expressed his commitment to establishing a conviction integrity panel to carefully review allegations of wrongful conviction and promoting alternatives to incarceration that do not compromise public safety.<ref>{{cite news | title=Letter \u2013 Alternatives to Jail | url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9906EFDF1430F931A15753C1A96E9C8B63 |work=The New York Times | date=October 22, 2008 | accessdate=July 2, 2009}}</ref>\n\nVance states that he has always been opposed to the death penalty.<ref>{{cite news | title=District Attorney hopefuls trash rival Snyder's flip on execution | url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/2009/04/23/2009-04-23_district_attorney_hopefuls_trash_snyder.html |work=New York Daily News | date=April 23, 2009 | accessdate=May 12, 2009 | first=Michael | last=Saul}}</ref>\n\nVance emerged victorious after facing former judge and 2005 D.A. candidate [[Leslie Crocker Snyder]], and [[Richard Aborn]], another former Assistant District Attorney and [[gun control]] advocate, in the September 15, 2009 Democratic [[Primary election|primary]].<ref>{{cite news | title=Vance Captures Nomination for District Attorney | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/09/16/nyregion/16election.html?hp|work=The New York Times | date=September 16, 2009 | accessdate=September 16, 2009 | first1=David W. | last1=Chen | first2=John | last2=Eligon}}</ref> The victory ensured that Vance would become only the fourth person to run the office since 1941, given the traditional absence during Morgenthau's tenure of a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] backed opponent.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Vance is winner in primary vote for prosecutor |work=The New York Times |page=1 |date=September 16, 2009}}</ref>\n\nOn November 3, 2009, Vance won the general election with a 91 percent share of the votes cast.\n\n==Manhattan District Attorney==\n\nVance was sworn into office as the Manhattan District Attorney on January 1, 2010. Within a few months, he established or consolidated numerous new bureaus and units in an effort to modernize the District Attorney's Office. Vance's administration established a Conviction Integrity Program,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/05/nyregion/05wrongful.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |title=Prosecutor in Manhattan Will Monitor Convictions |first=John |last=Eligon |work=The New York Times |date=March 4, 2010}}</ref> Crime Strategies Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/25/nyregion/25vance.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |title=Top Prosecutor Creates a Unit On Crime Trends |first=John |last=Eligon |date=May 25, 2010 |work=The New York Times}}</ref> Cybercrime and Identity Theft Bureau,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204720204577129022552945152 |title=D.A. Cracks Down On Internet Crime |first=Michael |last=Rothfeld |work=Wall Street Journal |date= December 30, 2011}}</ref> Forensic Sciences/ Cold Case Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/15/nyregion/district-attorney-vance-sees-dna-as-tool-to-solve-cold-cases.html?ref=cyrusrvancejr |first=Al |last=Baker |work=The New York Times |date=June 14, 2011 |title=In Manhattan, District Attorney Sees DNA as Tool to Solve Cold Cases}}</ref> Hate Crimes Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sohojournal.com/content/da-vance-announces-hate-crime-unit |title=D.A. Vance Announces Hate Crime Unit |work=SoHo Journal |access-date=January 10, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130141449/http://sohojournal.com/content/da-vance-announces-hate-crime-unit |archive-date=November 30, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Public Integrity Unit,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/corruption-currents/2010/10/20/manhattan-da-announces-new-unit-to-investigate-public-corruption/ |title=Manhattan DA Announces New Unit To Investigate Public Corruption |date=October 20, 2010 |first=Samuel |last=Rubenfeld |work=Wall Street Journal}}</ref> Special Victims Bureau,<ref>[https://archive.is/20120728005937/http://www.dnainfo.com/20100924/downtown/manhattan-special-victims-be-serviced-by-new-da-bureau]</ref> and Vehicular Crimes Unit.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/119415/manhattan-d-a--expands-vehicular-crimes-unit/ |title=Manhattan D.A. Expands Vehicular Crimes Unit |publisher=NY1 |date=May 27, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100530130316/http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/119415/manhattan-d-a--expands-vehicular-crimes-unit/ |archivedate=May 30, 2010  }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/05/28/prosecutors-get-along-and-a-crime-unit-gets-a-lift/ |date=May 28, 2010 |title=Prosecutors Get Along, and a Crime Unit Gets a Lift |work=The New York Times |first=John |last=Eligon}}</ref>\n\n[[File:February 2011 Press Conference.jpg|upright|thumb|right|Vance speaks at a February 2011 press conference]]\n\n===Notable cases===\nIn 2011, a New York prosecutor from Vance's office argued on behalf of billionaire and sex offender [[Jeffrey Epstein]], to New York Supreme Court Judge Ruth Pickholtz, asking for Epstein's sex offender status to be reduced. The reasoning was that Epstein had not been indicted and his underage victims had failed to cooperate in the case. The judge, however, denied the petition, and expressed bewilderment that a New York prosecutor would make such a request on behalf of a serial sex offender accused of molesting multiple girls: \"I have to tell you, I\u2019m a little overwhelmed because I have never seen a prosecutor\u2019s office do anything like this. I have done so many [sex offender registration hearings] much less troubling than this one where the [prosecutor] would never make a downward argument like this,\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article220097825.html |title=How a future Trump Cabinet member gave a serial sex abuser the deal of a lifetime|work=Miami Herald|first=Julie|last=Brown|date=November 28, 2018}}</ref>. Jennifer Gaffney, then deputy chief of Cyrus Vance Jr.\u2019s sex-crimes unit, stated at the hearing that, \u201cThere is only an indictment for one victim. If an offender is not indicted for an offense, it is strong evidence that the offense did not occur.\u201d<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nypost.com/2018/12/01/manhattan-da-sided-with-pedophile-billionaire-after-botching-investigation| title=Manhattan DA sided with pedophile billionaire after botching investigation|work=New York Post|first=Rebecca|last=Rosenberg|date= December 1, 2018}}</ref>. Pickholz rejected Gaffney\u2019s arguments and gave Epstein the highest sex-offender status \u2013 Level 3. While Vance denies having been aware of the hearing until years later, some law enforcement sources find it unlikely that he was clueless that his office was handling a sex-offender case involving a Manhattan mogul with close ties to Democrats<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nypost.com/2018/12/01/manhattan-da-sided-with-pedophile-billionaire-after-botching-investigation| title=Manhattan DA sided with pedophile billionaire after botching investigation|work=New York Post|first=Rebecca|last=Rosenberg|date= December 1, 2018}}</ref>. In 2019, Epstein was arrested and charged with sex trafficking <ref>{{cite news | title=Jeffrey Epstein, Billionaire Long Accused of Molesting Minors, Is Charged |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/06/nyregion/jeffrey-epstein-arrested-sex-trafficking.html?campaign_id=60&instance_id=0&segment_id=14985&user_id=24491ccb6443e3eb868c38fc8dc7a8ab&regi_id=65747128ing-news |first=Patricia |last=Mazzei |work=New York Daily News |date=July 6, 2011}}</ref>.\n\nVance's recent successes include the sentencing of a serial rapist to 428 years to life in prison;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2011-12-12/news/30509662_1_serial-rapist-black-men-court-officers |title=Manhattan serial rapist Vincent Heyward socked with 428-year sentence Victims describe the lasting horror of his brutal knife-point attacks |work=New York Daily News |first=Barbara |last=Ross |date=December 12, 2011}}</ref> sentencing of a man to 23 years to life in prison for a domestic violence murder;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/11/28/jesus-alejandro-sentenced-for-brutal-murder-of-girlfriend/ |title=Jesus Alejandro Sentenced For Brutal Murder Of Girlfriend |publisher=CBS New York |date=November 28, 2011}}</ref> indictments against 26 individuals living in Manhattan who possessed graphic images of child sexual assault;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/06/14/manhattan-da-massive-child-cyber-porn-sting-ends-with-26-arrests/ |title=Manhattan DA: Massive Child Cyber Porn Sting Ends With 26 Arrests |publisher=CBS New York |date=June 14, 2011}}</ref> the sentencing of a man to at least 15 years in prison for a 2000 rape; a sentencing of a man to 25 to life in prison for a 1997 home invasion and murder;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-sentencing-1997-cold-case-murder |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=District Attorney Vance announces sentencing in 1997 cold case murder |date=June 29, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111227125457/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-sentencing-1997-cold-case-murder |archive-date=December 27, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> an indictment against another man for a 1986 rape and murder;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/man-indicted-24-year-old-%E2%80%9Ccold-case%E2%80%9D-rape-and-murder |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=Man indicted in 24-year-old \"cold case\" rape murder |date=July 6, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020012703/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/man-indicted-24-year-old-%E2%80%9Ccold-case%E2%80%9D-rape-and-murder |archive-date=October 20, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the guilty plea of a man for attacking a woman in the restroom of a bar in Hell's Kitchen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-guilty-plea-brutal-attack-woman-hell%E2%80%99s-kitchen-bar |publisher=The New York County District Attorney's Office |title=District Attorney Vance announces guilty plea in brutal attack on woman in Hell's Kitchen bar |date=July 18, 2011 |first=Cyrus R. Jr. |last=Vance |access-date=July 25, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026041809/http://www.manhattanda.com/press-release/district-attorney-vance-announces-guilty-plea-brutal-attack-woman-hell%E2%80%99s-kitchen-bar |archive-date=October 26, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nVance has also won convictions in an October 2009 drunk-driving incident that killed 11-year-old Leandra Rosado, resulting in the creation of [[Leandra's Law]]; and a case of two men in a 2005 murder-for-hire plot. In January 2011, the District Attorney's Forensic Sciences/ Cold Case Unit announced an indictment against noted serial killer [[Rodney Alcala]] for two Manhattan homicides in the 1970s.\n[[File:PC 6.14.11 1 (740x470) small.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Vance at June 2011 press conference on child assault]]\n\nVance's newly created Major Economic Crimes Bureau has won convictions in the $120 million-dollar art fraud prosecution of the Salander-O'Reilly Gallery, the gallery's president [[Lawrence Salander]] and director Leigh Morse, in which [[Robert De Niro]] was one of the principal witnesses for the prosecution;<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/robert-de-niro-to-testify-as-ex-salander-employee-starts-trial-for-fraud.html | work=Bloomberg | first=Philip | last=Boroff | title=De Niro Testifies Against Dealer Accused of Stealing Dad's Art | date=March 19, 2011}}</ref> a $100 million-dollar securities fraud scheme in which [[Yale University]] was one of the victims;<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/20/nyregion/lawyer-convicted-in-100-million-stock-swindle.html?scp=1&sq=mazzuto&st=cse | work=The New York Times | first=John | last=Eligon | title=Lawyer Convicted in $100 Million Stock Swindle | date=July 19, 2011}}</ref> a $100 million-dollar mortgage fraud case;<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/local/mortgage_scam_con_gets_jail_time_XeVcWp0DuPc4JA7KazTayN | work=New York Post | first=David K. | last=Li | title=$100M mortgage scam con gets jail time | date=September 21, 2010 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122201207/http://www.nypost.com/p/news/local/mortgage_scam_con_gets_jail_time_XeVcWp0DuPc4JA7KazTayN | archivedate=January 22, 2012 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and a $7 million-dollar Ponzi scheme.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/money-manager-de-chimay-sentenced-to-3-to-9-years-for-fraud-1-.html | work=Bloomberg | title=Money Manager De Chimay Sentenced to Three to Nine Years by New York Judge | date=March 23, 2011}}</ref> The District Attorney's Office in June 2011 announced indictments in a conspiracy involving 11 corporations who evaded U.S. economic sanctions on Iran by funneling tens of millions of dollars through Manhattan banks.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/20/nyregion/iranian-shipper-accused-of-sneaking-money-through-ny-banks.html | work=The New York Times | first=Jo | last=Becker | title=Iranian Shipper Accused of Sneaking Money Through N.Y. Banks | date=June 20, 2011}}</ref> To date, Vance's administration has brought hundreds of millions of dollars in settlements to New York City.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2010-09-25/local/27076255_1_budget-cuts-budget-war-budget-battle | location=New York | work=Daily News | title=Virginia girl found eating herself in cage in mobile home; parents Brian and Shannon Gore charged | first=Melissa | last=Grace | date=September 25, 2010}}</ref>\n\nCyrus Vance prosecuted programmer [[Sergey Aleynikov]] for duplicating computer code from Goldman Sachs, following the reversal of his federal conviction by the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit. The state case found Aleynikov guilty. However, on July 6, 2015, a New York State Supreme Court justice overturned that decision, but an appellate court reinstated the jury's guilty verdict on January 24, 2017. 148 AD3d 77 [1st Dept 2017], affirmed, 31 NY3d 383 [2018].\n\n===Abacus Federal Savings Bank case===\n\nIn 2009, [[Abacus Federal Savings Bank]], a small Chinese-American family-run bank in New York City's Chinatown, self-reported a mortgage fraud committed by an ex-employee to its regulators. It led Cyrus Vance's office to later accuse the bank itself of mortgage fraud. In an unusual move characterized by critics as an effort at at grandstanding, Vance's office orchestrated a parade of ex-employees of the bank in a chain, handcuffed to each other, in front of reporters.<ref name=\"pbs.org\">[http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/article/after-the-crash-big-banks-got-bailouts-abacus-faced-charges/ \"After the Crash, Big Banks Got Bailouts. Abacus Faced Charges.\"], September 12, 2016.</ref>  After Vance spent five years and $10 million prosecuting the bank for larceny, the bank and its employees were found not guilty on all 80 charges.\n\nThe bank was the only New York bank so charged during the Great Recession, although Vance said that [[Citibank]], among others, had behaved badly. The episode was covered in a feature-length documentary by [[Steve James (producer)|Steve James]], ''[[Abacus: Small Enough to Jail]]'', which characterized Vance as throwing the bank's owners under the bus in an effort to appear tough on white-collar crime.<ref name=\"Ebert Review\">{{cite news |last1=Seitz |first1=Matt Zoller |title=Abacus: Small Enough to Jail |url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/abacus-small-enough-to-jail-2017 |accessdate=20 March 2019 |agency=Roger Ebert.com |date=May 26, 2017}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[Toronto International Film Festival]] in 2016,<ref>[http://www.tiff.net/films/abacus-small-enough-to-jail/]</ref> was broadcast on [[PBS Frontline]] in 2017, and was nominated for an Oscar.<ref name=\"pbs.org\"/><ref>\n[http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/film/abacus/ \"Abacus: Small Enough to Jail\"], Retrieved September 13, 2017.</ref>\n\n===Motor vehicle prosecution===\n\nTransportation advocates have criticized Vance's office for what they see as a history of failing to fully prosecute motor vehicle offenses that result in death or serious injury to pedestrians and cyclists.\n\nIn July 2010, no charges were filed when an MTA tow truck struck and killed a seven-year-old boy standing on the sidewalk.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://nypost.com/2010/07/31/bridge-tragedy/ | work=The New York Post | first1=Kenneth M. | last1=Walsh | title=Bridge tragedy | date=July 31, 2010}}</ref> In October 2010, Vance declined to press charges in the [[dooring]] death of Marcus Ewing, on the rationale that, because the engine was not running and because the person who opened the door into Ewing's path did not have the keys in his possession, that person could not be prosecuted as a driver.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.vaccaroandwhite.com/bicycles/gothamist-how-to-kill-a-cyclist-and-walk-away/ | work=Vaccaro & White | first1=Sam | last1=Vaccaro | first2=Adam | last2=White | title=Gothamist: How to Kill a Cyclist and Walk Away | date=February 4, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, a cab driver hopped a curb, injuring several pedestrians and severing the leg of a British tourist. Despite a history of driving offenses, and admitting that he intentionally hit the gas before entering the sidewalk, the driver was able to regain his cab license, and after a two-month investigation, no charges were filed.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.streetsblog.org/2013/11/14/no-charges-from-cy-vance-for-cab-driver-who-maimed-tourist-sian-green/ | work=Streetsblog NYC | first1=Brad | last1=Aaron | title=No Charges From Cy Vance for Cab Driver Who Maimed Tourist Sian Green | date=November 14, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2014, Vance's office offered a plea to a driver accused of intentionally striking a cyclist with his car. The deal reduced charges of third-degree assault, punishable by up to a year in jail, to leaving the scene of an accident with property damage. The motorist paid a $250 fine.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.streetsblog.org/2014/10/22/da-cy-vance-250-fine-for-motorist-accused-of-deliberately-striking-cyclist/ | work=Streetsblog NYC | first1=Brad | last1=Aaron | title=DA Cy Vance: $250 Fine for Motorist Accused of Deliberately Striking Cyclist | date=October 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe lack of prosecutorial aggressiveness from Vance's office, in spite of recently passed vulnerable user laws<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2010/10/12/new_law_inspired_by_chinatown_van_c.php | work=Gothamist | first1=John Del | last1=Signore | title=New Law Inspired By Chinatown Van Crash Takes Effect | date=October 12, 2010 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030093804/http://gothamist.com/2010/10/12/new_law_inspired_by_chinatown_van_c.php | archivedate=October 30, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and Vance's own initiatives<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.transalt.org/news/releases/4530 | work=Transportation Alternatives | first1=Wiley | last1=Norvell | title=Statement on Manhattan DA Cy Vance's New Traffic Safety Initiatives | date=May 27, 2010}}</ref> has led to widespread media commentary on whether New York City cyclists can reasonably expect protection from the justice system.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2011/02/04/how_to_kill_a_cyclist_and_walk_away.php | work=Gothamist | first1=John Del | last1=Signore | title=How to Kill a Cyclist and Walk Away | date=February 4, 2011 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128014124/http://gothamist.com/2011/02/04/how_to_kill_a_cyclist_and_walk_away.php | archivedate=January 28, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/10/opinion/sunday/is-it-ok-to-kill-cyclists.html?pagewanted=all | work=The New York Times | first1=Daniel | last1=Duane | title=Is It O.K. to Kill Cyclists? | date=November 9, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, during an investigation into faded white flags flown over the Brooklyn Bridge in July 2014, Vance's office subpoenaed a farcical Twitter account, purporting to be the bicycle industry lobby, which had jokingly taken responsibility for the flag swap.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://gothamist.com/2014/08/08/parody_twitter_account_subpoenaed_o.php#photo-1 | work=Gothamist | first1=Ben | last1=Yakas | title=Manhattan DA Subpoenas Parody Twitter Account Over Obvious Brooklyn Bridge White Flag Joke | date=August 8, 2014 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010010554/http://gothamist.com/2014/08/08/parody_twitter_account_subpoenaed_o.php#photo-1 | archivedate=October 10, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The flags were later revealed to be the work of German artists.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/11030119/Mystery-of-white-flags-on-Brooklyn-Bridge-solved-as-German-artists-claim-responsibility.html | work=The Telegraph | agency=Associated Press | title=Mystery of white flags on Brooklyn Bridge solved as German artists claim responsibility | date=August 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Dominique Strauss-Kahn case===\nVance initially came under criticism by the media for ultimately dismissing charges in the [[Dominique Strauss-Kahn sexual assault case]], after the French head of the [[International Monetary Fund]] was arrested, based on accusations by a hotel maid at the [[Sofitel]] hotel who said he had forced her to perform oral sex when she came to clean his room. Kahn admitted the encounter had taken place, but maintained the sex was consensual. <ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rsr.ch/#/info/les-titres/monde/3252521-le-procureur-dans-la-tourmente-de-l-affaire-dsk.html |title=Affaire DSK: l'enqu\u00eate se poursuit |language=French |publisher=Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Suisse |date=July 6, 2011}}</ref> However, Vance was praised by New York City Mayor [[Michael Bloomberg]],<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/06/nyregion/strauss-kahn-lawyers-and-prosecution-to-meet.html | work=The New York Times | first1=John | last1=Eligon | first2=William K. | last2=Rashbaum | title=Strauss-Kahn Lawyers and Prosecution Meet | date=July 5, 2011}}</ref> former Mayor [[Ed Koch]], former Manhattan District Attorney [[Robert Morgenthau]],<ref>{{cite news| url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/07/07/morgenthau-comes-to-vances-defense/?scp=1&sq=morgenthau&st=cse | work=The New York Times | first=John | last=Eligon | title=Morgenthau Comes to Vance's Defense | date=July 7, 2011}}</ref> and other prominent litigators and government officials for adhering to prosecutorial protocol and acting \"with integrity\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ny1.com/content/news_beats/politics/142305/ny1-online--ny1-wise-guys-7-5-11 |publisher=NY1 |title=NY1 Online: NY1 Wise Guys 7/5/11 |date=July 5, 2011 }}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>{{explain|date=October 2017}} Vance has also been applauded in editorials by the ''New York Times,'' ''Wall Street Journal,'' and the ''New York Daily News'' for making a \"tough but fair and just call\"{{clarify|date=October 2017}} in \"an exceptional case\" in which a woman made a \"credible\" accusation against a very powerful man.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/05/opinion/05nocera.html?_r=1&ref=joenocera | work=The New York Times | first=Joe | last=Nocera | title=The D.A. Did the Right Thing | date=July 4, 2011}}</ref><ref name=WSJDSK>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424053111903461304576526503562746350?KEYWORDS=dominique+strauss-kahn |title=The Judgment on DSK |date=August 24, 2011 |work=Wall Street Journal}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/opinion/da-cy-vance-made-tough-fair-call-dismiss-charges-dominique-strauss-kahn-article-1.950312 |title=DA Cy Vance made tough but fair and just call to dismiss charges against Dominique Strauss-Kahn |work=New York Daily News |date=August 23, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/24/opinion/the-strauss-kahn-case.html?scp=4&sq=vance%20august%2024&st=cse |title=The Strauss-Kahn Case |date=August 23, 2011 |work=The New York Times}}</ref> The ''Wall Street Journal'' wrote: \"DSK got neither more nor less than he deserved\u2014something for which he can blame, and thank, Cy Vance and America's justice system.\"<ref name=WSJDSK/> He dropped all charges against the defendant on August 11, stating that he could not prove Kahn's guilt beyond reasonable doubt due to questions about the credibility of the accuser Nafissatou Diallo.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/aug/23/dominique-strauss-kahn-charges-dropped|date=August 23, 2011|title=\nDominique Strauss-Kahn walks free from New York court}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/jan/19/dominique-strauss-kahn-prosecutor-reasons|date=January 19, 2012|title=Dominique Strauss-Kahn prosecutor tells why he dropped case}}</ref>\n\n===Paul Manafort===\n{{further|Trials of Paul Manafort}}\nOn March 13, 2019 Vance filed 16 indictments charging mortgage fraud against [[Paul Manafort]], former chairman of  [[Donald Trump presidential campaign, 2016|Donald Trump's 2016 presidential campaign]]. Vance said the charges stemmed from an investigation launched in March 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/regulation/433875-manafort-indicted-by-manhattan-district-attorney|title=Manafort indicted by Manhattan DA on mortgage fraud charges|last=Samuels|first=Brett|date=March 13, 2019|work=The Hill|accessdate=14 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Political contributions and non-prosecutions===\n{{expand section|date=October 2017}}\nFrom August 2017, allegations appeared across various news media outlets concerning Vance's associations, and certain contributions made to his office in relation to past cases. Under scrutiny are the Manhattan DA's handling of [[Harvey Weinstein sexual misconduct allegations|allegations of sexual assault]] against film producer [[Harvey Weinstein]],<ref>[http://www.businessinsider.com/cyrus-vance-harvey-weinstein-audio-trump-2017-10?IR=T Manhattan district attorney defends handling of 2015 Harvey Weinstein investigation as shocking audio emerges]</ref> and allegations of his handling of [[Trump SoHo#Fraud lawsuit|improper conduct by members of the Trump family around the Trump SoHo development]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Manhattan DA ignores questions regarding concern over donations |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=October 7, 2017 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/oct/07/cyrus-vance-donations-donald-ivanka-trump-harvey-weinstein }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=How Ivanka Trump and Donald Trump, Jr., Avoided a Criminal Indictment |work=[[The New Yorker]] |date=October 4, 2017 |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/how-ivanka-trump-and-donald-trump-jr-avoided-a-criminal-indictment }}</ref> Critics have suggested that contributions to the DA around these times were directly linked to Vance not prosecuting these cases. Vance has defended the actions of his office, citing insufficient evidence to prosecute in each case.<ref>{{cite news |title=Vance Returned Trump Lawyer\u2019s Donation After Reporters\u2019 Questions |work=New York Times |date=October 4, 2017 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/04/nyregion/cyrus-vance-manhattan-da-trump-lawyer.html }}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018,  New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo announced that the New York State attorney general will investigate the Manhattan district attorney's handling of a 2015 sexual abuse case involving disgraced media mogul Harvey Weinstein.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/19/entertainment/times-up-cyrus-vance/index.html|title=District attorney who didn't prosecute Weinstein will be investigated|last=Joseph|first=Sandra Gonzalez and Elizabeth|work=CNN|access-date=March 20, 2018}}</ref> NYPD investigators who investigated the 2015 case believed that the sexual abuse case was strong enough to be prosecuted, but Vance opted not to prosecute the case.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/mar/17/weinstein-ambra-battilana-case-hidden-nypd-district-attorney|title=NYPD reportedly hid Weinstein accuser, fearing district attorney would sink case|last=Helmore|first=Edward|date=March 17, 2018|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref> \n\nThe case concerned a 22-year old Filipina-Italian model - [[Ambra Gutierrez|Ambra Battilana Gutierrez]], who went straight to the police after Weinstein lunged at her, groping her breasts and attempting to put a hand up her skirt while she protested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/oct/11/the-allegations-against-harvey-weinstein-what-we-know-so-far|title=Harvey Weinstein: the women who have accused him|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The next day she met with Weinstein, equipped with a NYPD wire tap. In the recording, published by The New Yorker and ABC News , Weinstein insists - \"I'm telling you right now, get in here.\" Gutierrez explicitly refuses, adding '''\"'''yesterday was kind of aggressive for me\" and asks why he had groped her breast the day before. \u201cOh, please, I\u2019m sorry, just come on in. I\u2019m used to that. Come on. Please\u201d he says. \u201cYou are used to that?\u201d Gutierrez asks. \u201cYes,\u201d Weinstein replies, later adding: \u201cDon\u2019t ruin your friendship with me for five minutes.\u201d<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-10-11/harvey-weinstein-full-transcript-of-audio-with-ambra-gutierrez/9037268|title=Harvey Weinstein: Full transcript of the 'horrifying' exchange with Ambra Gutierrez|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Joseph|first=Sandra Gonzalez and Elizabeth|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/19/entertainment/times-up-cyrus-vance/index.html|title=District attorney who didn't prosecute Weinstein will be investigated|work=CNN|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|last=Stelter|first=Lisa France and Brian|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/10/media/harvey-weinstein-new-yorker-magazine/index.html|title=Harvey Weinstein accused of rape in New Yorker story|work=CNNMoney|access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''The Guardian'', the investigators were at the time under the belief that Vance would undermine the case, given that he had previously dropped a similar case against Dominique Strauss-Kahn.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nVance has heavily prosecuted possession of [[gravity knife|gravity knives]], disproportionately arresting and indicting defendants of color.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Grant |first1=Melissa Gira |title=Manhattan D.A.\u2019s Office Still Prosecuting People for the Knives They Carry for Work |url=https://theappeal.org/manhattan-d-a-s-office-still-prosecuting-people-for-the-knives-they-carry-for-work/ |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The Appeal |publisher=The Appeal |date=26 November 2018 |language=en}}</ref> The law banning them, which was interpreted broadly by Vance and is enforced mainly in Manhattan, has been the subject of several repeal efforts in the New York state legislature. Governor Andrew Cuomo has vetoed two such repeal bills passed in two years by majority votes in both chambers of the state congress.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Victor |first1=Daniel |title=Cuomo Vetoes Bill to Overhaul \u2018Gravity Knife\u2019 Law for Second Straight Year |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/24/nyregion/gravity-knife-cuomo-veto.html |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The New York Times |publisher=The New York Times |date=24 October 2017}}</ref> Despite the 70,000 people arrested under this law in ten years, Vance declined to take action against the more than 100 hardware stores selling potential gravity knives in the city.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/new-york-just-saved-a-law-used-to-jail-thousands-of-minorities|title=New York Just Saved a Law Used to Jail Thousands of Minorities|last=Campbell|first=Jon|date=October 24, 2017|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=October 24, 2017}}</ref>  \n\nOn March 27, 2019, in Cracco v. Vance, No. 14 Civ. 8235 (SDNY), a federal judge  ruled that Vance's office had applied the  law unconstitutionally, resulting a in a lack of notice of prohibited behavior as well as allowing for arbitrary and discriminatory enforcement.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gothamist.com/2019/03/29/gravity_knife_unconstitutional.php|title=Federal Judge Rules Controversial Gravity Knife Law Is Too Vague To Enforce|last=Offenhartz|first=Jake|work=Gothamist|access-date=March 29, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330175545/http://gothamist.com/2019/03/29/gravity_knife_unconstitutional.php|archive-date=March 30, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Soon after, state lawmakers Dan Quart and Diane Savino introduced a third iteration of the bill repealing the gravity knife ban. On May 31, 2019, Governor Andrew Cuomo signed the bill into law, making gravity knives legal to possess in the state of New York.<ref>{{cite news |last1=OFFENHARTZ |first1=JAKE |title=Cuomo Signs Bill To End 'Absurd' Gravity Knife Ban That He Supported For Years |url=https://gothamist.com/2019/05/31/gravity_knife_ban_ends.php |accessdate=14 June 2019 |publisher=The Gothamist |date=31 May 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531213959/http://gothamist.com/2019/05/31/gravity_knife_ban_ends.php |archive-date=May 31, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=McKinley |first1=Jesse |title=The \u2018Gravity Knife\u2019 Led to Thousands of Questionable Arrests. Now It\u2019s Legal. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/31/nyregion/ny-gravity-knife-law.html |accessdate=14 June 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=31 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Affiliations==\nVance serves as a member of the Board of Directors of the [[Police Athletic League of New York City]], a non-profit youth development agency that helps inner-city children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palnyc.org/800-PAL-4KIDS/BoardOfDirectors.aspx |title=Board of Directors |publisher=Police Athletic League NYC |accessdate=July 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727162754/http://www.palnyc.org/800-PAL-4KIDS/BoardOfDirectors.aspx |archivedate=July 27, 2011  }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Tax returns of Donald Trump]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.manhattanda.com/ Manhattan District Attorney's Office (official website)]\n*[http://www.cyvanceforda.com/ Cyrus Vance For District Attorney (official campaign website)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090101114103/http://www.maglaw.com/attorneys/data/vance_cyrus Morvillo, Abramowitz, Grand, Isaon, Anello & Bohrer, P.C. Website on Cyrus Vance]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101004065212/http://www.criminaljustice.state.ny.us/pio/press_releases/2009-02-03_pressrelease.html Commission on Sentencing Reform Recommendation Announcement]\n*[https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/15/nyregion/district-attorney-vance-sees-dna-as-tool-to-solve-cold-cases.html?src=recg 'In Manhattan, District Attorney Sees DNA as Tool to Solve Cold Cases'], Al Baker, ''[[The New York Times]]'', June 14, 2011\n*{{C-SPAN|Cyrus Vance 02}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Robert Morgenthau]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[New York County District Attorney|District Attorney of New York County]]|years=2010\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Manhattan DA}}\n{{New York City District Attorneys}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vance, Cyrus Jr}}\n[[Category:American prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Politicians from New York City]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Democrats]]\n[[Category:New York (state) lawyers]]\n<!--[[Category:Liberal politicians]] Temporary, category is being considered for deletion.-->\n[[Category:New York County District Attorneys]]\n[[Category:Real property lawyers]]\n[[Category:Georgetown University Law Center alumni]]\n[[Category:Yale University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Manhattan]]\n[[Category:Seattle University faculty]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Buckley School (New York City) alumni]]\n[[Category:Groton School alumni]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyrus_Vance_Jr."}
{"title_page": "Cypriot nationality law", "text_new": "{{Infobox legislation\n|short_title         = Cypriot Citizenship Act \n|legislature         = [[Parliament of Cyprus]]\n|image               = \n|imagesize           = \n|imagealt            = \n|caption             = \n|long_title          = An Act relating to Cypriot citizenship\n|citation            = \n|territorial_extent  = \n|enacted_by          = [[Government of Cyprus]]\n|date_enacted        = \n|date_passed         = \n|enacted_by2         = \n|date_enacted2       = \n|date_passed2        = \n|date_assented       = \n|royal_assent        =\n|date_signed         = \n|signed_by           = \n|date_commenced      = \n|date_of_expiry      = \n|date_repealed       = \n|administered_by     = \n|bill                = \n|bill_citation       = \n|bill_date           = \n|introduced_by       = \n|1st_reading         = \n|2nd_reading         = \n|3rd_reading         = \n|conf_committee_passed  = \n|committee_report    = \n|bill2               = \n|bill_citation2      = \n|bill_date2          = \n|introduced_by2      = \n|1st_reading2        = \n|2nd_reading2        = \n|3rd_reading2        = \n|conf_committee_passed2 = \n|committee_report2   = \n|date_conf_committee = \n|white_paper         = \n|amendments          = \n|repeals             = \n|related_legislation = \n|summary             = \n|keywords            = \n|status              = current\n}}\n\nThe '''Cypriot Nationality Laws''' dates back to 1967. It is mainly based on ''[[jus sanguinis]]''.\n\n==Acquisition of Cypriot citizenship==\n\nThere are several ways to become a Cypriot citizen (citizen of The [[Republic of Cyprus]]) :\n\n===Marriage to a Cypriot National===\n\nThe first, being married to a Cypriot national, requires one to be married for at least 3 years, and have completed 2 years of residency in Cyprus prior to the date of the application. \n\nIn the case where the Cypriot national is living abroad, the applicant must either have been married to the Cypriot national for 3 years and submit an accompanying letter explaining why citizenship is desired, or have been married to the Cypriot national for 5 years and have at least one child (in which case an accompanying letter is not required).<ref name=spouse>{{cite web | title= Migration Section: Acquisition of Citizenship as a Spouse of a Cypriot Citizen (Type M125) | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department| url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/60D513972DB4D3ADC2257D1E00333668?OpenDocument|accessdate= 5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe documents required are:<ref name=spouse/>\n*Birth certificate of the applicant \n*Certificate of clean criminal record of the applicant\n*Marriage certificate\n*Birth certificate of the couple's children \n*Certificate of acquisition of the Cypriot citizenship of the Cypriot spouse (where applicable)\n*Statement of harmonious cohabitation signed before an Officer of the District Administration Office or the diplomatic authority \n*Statement of cohabitation from the local authority\n*The application should be submitted in duplicate and one of the two application forms should bear two stamps worth {{Euro|8.54}}.\n*Photocopy of receipt for the amount of {{Euro|300}} paid as fees \n\n===Having Cypriot Origins===\n\nTo apply through this method, one must be over 18 years old, and naturally, have Cypriot origins, as long as one was born abroad after the 16th of August 1960, with one's parent at the time of birth a Cypriot citizen. One can apply in this way if one is an individual born after the 11th of June 1999, whose mother was a Cypriot citizen at the time of one's birth.<ref name=\"moi.gov.cy\">{{cite web | title=Civil Registry Section: Acquisition of Citizenship Due to Cypriot Origins | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department | url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/3FCECD650C82D647C2257D2B00396BA2?OpenDocument&highlight=CITIZENSHIP%20DUE%20CYPRIOT%20ORIGINS | access-date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAccompanying the application must be:\n\n*Birth certificate of the applicant\n*Marriage certificate of the applicant's parents\n*Photocopy of the applicant's and the applicant's parents' passports \n*Certificate of registration of the Cypriot parent (where applicable)\n*Copy of proof of fees paid {{Euro|20}}\n*Stamp worth {{Euro|8.54}} attached to the application <ref name=\"moi.gov.cy\"/>\n\n=== Naturalisation / Citizenship by Investment ===\n\n[[Naturalisation]] is referred to as the process for which a non-citizen of a country, in this case Cyprus, may become a citizen of that country. The process may be done via a statute or an application to the relevant authorities. \n\nIn March 2014, the Cyprus Council of Ministers revised the \"Scheme for Naturalisation of Investors in Cyprus by Exception\" as part of the government's attempts to attract foreign investors to the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/moi.nsf/All/36DB428D50A58C00C2257C1B00218CAB|title=Grant of the Cypriot citizenship to non\u2013Cypriot entrepreneurs/ investors through the \"Scheme for Naturalization of Investors in Cyprus by exception|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Interior|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> One of these attempts included a program that granted applicants the right to live, work and study in Cyprus and in the European Union.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.henleyglobal.com/citizenship-cyprus-citizenship/|title=Citizenship-by-Investment in Cyprus - Henley & Partners|website=www.henleyglobal.com|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>\n\nOn September 13th, 2016 Council of Ministers of Cyprus approved a new program of financial criteria for investors wishing to obtain citizenship of Cyprus (Cyprus Investment Programme).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vizus-property.com/page/citizenship-for-investors---text-of-the-law|title=Cyprus Investment Programme - Text of the Law|last=|first=|date=|website=vizus-property.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-01}}</ref>\n\nApplicants applying for Cypriot citizenship through this citizenship-by-investment option must actively invest in the Cyprus economy, by primarily purchasing real estate at a minimum value of {{Euro|2}}m which must be held for at least 5 years, thereafter the property may be sold however they must maintain a property of at least {{Euro|500,000}} indefinitely. Citizenship by investment includes the main applicant and his her spouse and unmarried dependents aged 28 and under. The main applicants parents can also be added for an additional investment of {{Euro|500,000}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Cyprus Investment Programme |url=https://gk-lawfirm.com/practice-areas/cyprus-citizenship-by-investment-program/ |website=George K. Konstantinou Law Firm}}</ref>\nAccording to recent amendments also the applicants on approval need to make donations of total of 150.000 euros. The recent amendments also make a condition that the applicants holds a valid schengen visa.\n\nFollowing recent amendments to procedures, citizenship is now only approved after 6 months rather than 3 months as before.{{when|date=February 2020}}\n\n=== New baby born ===\n\nAccording to the Republic of Cyprus Citizenship Law of 1967, anyone born on or after 16 August 1960, and with at least one parent being a Cypriot citizen, automatically acquires Cypriot citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusembassy.net/home/index.php?module=page&cid=111|title=Official Website of the Embassy of the Republic of Cyprus in Washington D.C.|website=www.cyprusembassy.net|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref> Those who were born between 16 August 1960 and 1999 to a Cypriot mother abroad however, do not automatically become citizens of Cyprus, but they may register after they turn 21 years old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dualcitizenship.com/countries/cyprus.html|title=Dual Citizenship Cyprus|website=www.dualcitizenship.com|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Dual citizenship==\n\nCyprus allows its citizens to hold foreign citizenship in addition to their Cypriot citizenship. Some countries, however, do not permit multiple citizenship e.g. adults who acquired Cypriot and [[Japanese citizenship]] by birth must declare, to the latter's [[Ministry of Justice (Japan)|Ministry of Justice]], before turning 22, which citizenship they want to keep.\n\n==Citizenship of the Commonwealth of Nations==\n\nCypriot citizens are also [[Commonwealth citizen]]s as well.\n\n==Citizenship of the European Union==\n\nBecause Cyprus forms part of the [[European Union]], Cypriot citizens are also [[citizenship of the European Union|citizens of the European Union]] under [[European Union law]] and thus enjoy [[Freedom of movement for workers#Transitional provisions in new member states|rights of free movement]] and [[Cyprus (European Parliament constituency)|have the right to vote]] in [[Elections in the European Union|elections]] for the [[European Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://europa.eu/about-eu/countries/member-countries/cyprus/index_en.htm | title=Cyprus | publisher=European Union | accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref> When in a non-EU country where there is no Cypriot embassy, Cypriot citizens have the right to get consular protection from the embassy of any other EU country present in that country.<ref>Article 20(2)(c) of the [[s:Consolidated version of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union/Part Two: Non-Discrimination and Citizenship of the Union#Article 20|Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union]].</ref><ref>[[Citizenship_of_the_European_Union#Stated_rights|Rights abroad: Right to consular protection]]: a right to protection by the diplomatic or consular authorities of other Member States when in a non-EU Member State, if there are no diplomatic or consular authorities from the citizen's own state (Article 23): this is due to the fact that not all member states maintain embassies in every country in the world (14 countries have only one embassy from an EU state). [[Antigua and Barbuda]] (UK), [[Barbados]] (UK), [[Belize]] (UK), [[Central African Republic]] (France), [[Comoros]] (France), [[Gambia]] (UK), [[Guyana]] (UK), [[Liberia]] (Germany), [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]] (UK), [[San Marino]] (Italy), [[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]] (Portugal), [[Solomon Islands]] (UK), [[Timor-Leste]] (Portugal), [[Vanuatu]] (France)</ref> Cypriot citizens can live and work in any country within the EU as a result of the right of free movement and residence granted in [[Treaties of the European Union|Article 21 of the EU Treaty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:C:2008:115:0047:0199:EN:PDF |format=PDF|title=Treaty on the Function of the European Union  (consolidated version)|publisher=Eur-lex.europa.eu|accessdate=2015-07-10}}</ref>\n\n==Travel freedom of Cypriot citizens==\n\n{{Main| Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens}}\n[[File: Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens.png|450px|thumbnail|[[Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens]]]]\n\n{{As of|2019|03|26|post=,}} Cypriot citizens had visa-free or visa on arrival access to 173 countries and territories, ranking the [[Cypriot passport]] 16th in terms of travel freedom according to the [[Henley Passport Index]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The ''Henley Passport Index'' |url=https://www.henleyglobal.com/files/download/HPI2019/Full_Q2_2019_Ranking.pdf|publisher=Henley & Partners Holdings Ltd |accessdate=4 April 2019|date=26 March 2019 |quote=This graph shows the full Global Ranking of the 2019 Henley Passport Index. In certain cases, a rank is shared by multiple countries because these countries all have the same level of visa-free or visa-on-arrival access.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the Cypriot nationality was ranked twenty-fourth in the [[The Quality of Nationality Index|Nationality Index]] (QNI). This index differs from the [[Visa (document)#Visa restrictions|Visa Restrictions Index]], which focuses on external factors including travel freedom. The QNI considers, in addition to travel freedom, on internal factors such as peace & stability, economic strength, and human development as well. <ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.businessinsider.de/nationalities-with-the-best-quality-of-life-2016-6?r=UK&IR=T |title= The 41 nationalities with the best quality of life |date= 2016-02-06 |website=  www.businessinsider.de |access-date= 2018-09-10}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[British Overseas citizen#Cyprus]]\n*[[Commonwealth citizen]]\n*[[Greek nationality law]]\n*[[Northern Cyprus citizenship]]\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite web | title=Cyprus Investment Programme | website=Stelios A. Stylianou & Co LLC | date=1 March 2019 | url=https://www.sslawyersco.com/cyprus-investment-programme-current-policy/ }}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web | title= Migration Section | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department| url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/044601A0B7CE6062C2257D2C0037F93F?OpenDocument}}\n\n{{Commonwealth citizenship}}\n{{Nationality laws}}\n\n[[Category:Cyprus and the Commonwealth of Nations]]\n[[Category:Nationality law]]\n[[Category:Nationality in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Cyprus]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox legislation\n|short_title         = Cypriot Citizenship Act \n|legislature         = [[Parliament of Cyprus]]\n|image               = \n|imagesize           = \n|imagealt            = \n|caption             = \n|long_title          = An Act relating to Cypriot citizenship\n|citation            = \n|territorial_extent  = \n|enacted_by          = [[Government of Cyprus]]\n|date_enacted        = \n|date_passed         = \n|enacted_by2         = \n|date_enacted2       = \n|date_passed2        = \n|date_assented       = \n|royal_assent        =\n|date_signed         = \n|signed_by           = \n|date_commenced      = \n|date_of_expiry      = \n|date_repealed       = \n|administered_by     = \n|bill                = \n|bill_citation       = \n|bill_date           = \n|introduced_by       = \n|1st_reading         = \n|2nd_reading         = \n|3rd_reading         = \n|conf_committee_passed  = \n|committee_report    = \n|bill2               = \n|bill_citation2      = \n|bill_date2          = \n|introduced_by2      = \n|1st_reading2        = \n|2nd_reading2        = \n|3rd_reading2        = \n|conf_committee_passed2 = \n|committee_report2   = \n|date_conf_committee = \n|white_paper         = \n|amendments          = \n|repeals             = \n|related_legislation = \n|summary             = \n|keywords            = \n|status              = current\n}}\n\nThe '''Cypriot Nationality Laws''' dates back to 1967. It is mainly based on ''[[jus sanguinis]]''.\n\n==Acquisition of Cypriot citizenship==\n\nThere are several ways to become a Cypriot citizen (citizen of The [[Republic of Cyprus]]) :\n\n===Marriage to a Cypriot National===\n\nThe first, being married to a Cypriot national, requires one to be married for at least 3 years, and have completed 2 years of residency in Cyprus prior to the date of the application. \n\nIn the case where the Cypriot national is living abroad, the applicant must either have been married to the Cypriot national for 3 years and submit an accompanying letter explaining why citizenship is desired, or have been married to the Cypriot national for 5 years and have at least one child (in which case an accompanying letter is not required).<ref name=spouse>{{cite web | title= Migration Section: Acquisition of Citizenship as a Spouse of a Cypriot Citizen (Type M125) | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department| url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/60D513972DB4D3ADC2257D1E00333668?OpenDocument|accessdate= 5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe documents required are:<ref name=spouse/>\n*Birth certificate of the applicant \n*Certificate of clean criminal record of the applicant\n*Marriage certificate\n*Birth certificate of the couple's children \n*Certificate of acquisition of the Cypriot citizenship of the Cypriot spouse (where applicable)\n*Statement of harmonious cohabitation signed before an Officer of the District Administration Office or the diplomatic authority \n*Statement of cohabitation from the local authority\n*The application should be submitted in duplicate and one of the two application forms should bear two stamps worth {{Euro|8.54}}.\n*Photocopy of receipt for the amount of {{Euro|300}} paid as fees \n\n===Having Cypriot Origins===\n\nTo apply through this method, one must be over 18 years old, and naturally, have Cypriot origins, as long as one was born abroad after the 16th of August 1960, with one's parent at the time of birth a Cypriot citizen. One can apply in this way if one is an individual born after the 11th of June 1999, whose mother was a Cypriot citizen at the time of one's birth.<ref name=\"moi.gov.cy\">{{cite web | title=Civil Registry Section: Acquisition of Citizenship Due to Cypriot Origins | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department | url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/3FCECD650C82D647C2257D2B00396BA2?OpenDocument&highlight=CITIZENSHIP%20DUE%20CYPRIOT%20ORIGINS | access-date=5 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAccompanying the application must be:\n\n*Birth certificate of the applicant\n*Marriage certificate of the applicant's parents\n*Photocopy of the applicant's and the applicant's parents' passports \n*Certificate of registration of the Cypriot parent (where applicable)\n*Copy of proof of fees paid {{Euro|20}}\n*Stamp worth {{Euro|8.54}} attached to the application <ref name=\"moi.gov.cy\"/>\n\n=== Naturalisation / Citizenship by Investment ===\n\n[[Naturalisation]] is referred to as the process for which a non-citizen of a country, in this case Cyprus, may become a citizen of that country. The process may be done via a statute or an application to the relevant authorities. \n\nIn March 2014, the Cyprus Council of Ministers revised the \"Scheme for Naturalisation of Investors in Cyprus by Exception\" as part of the government's attempts to attract foreign investors to the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/moi.nsf/All/36DB428D50A58C00C2257C1B00218CAB|title=Grant of the Cypriot citizenship to non\u2013Cypriot entrepreneurs/ investors through the \"Scheme for Naturalization of Investors in Cyprus by exception|last=|first=|date=|website=Ministry of Interior|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> One of these attempts included a program that granted applicants the right to live, work and study in Cyprus and in the European Union.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.henleyglobal.com/citizenship-cyprus-citizenship/|title=Citizenship-by-Investment in Cyprus - Henley & Partners|website=www.henleyglobal.com|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>\n\nOn September 13th, 2016 Council of Ministers of Cyprus approved a new program of financial criteria for investors wishing to obtain citizenship of Cyprus (Cyprus Investment Programme)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vizus-property.com/page/citizenship-for-investors---text-of-the-law|title=Cyprus Investment Programme - Text of the Law|last=|first=|date=|website=vizus-property.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-01}}</ref>.\n\nApplicants applying for Cypriot citizenship through this citizenship-by-investment option must actively invest in the Cyprus economy, by primarily purchasing real estate at a minimum value of {{Euro|2}}m which must be held for at least 5 years, thereafter the property may be sold however they must maintain a property of at least {{Euro|500,000}} indefinitely. Citizenship by investment includes the main applicant and his her spouse and unmarried dependents aged 28 and under. The main applicants parents can also be added for an additional investment of {{Euro|500,000}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Cyprus Investment Programme |url=https://gk-lawfirm.com/practice-areas/cyprus-citizenship-by-investment-program/ |website=George K. Konstantinou Law Firm}}</ref>\nAccording to recent amendments also the applicants on approval need to make donations of total of 150.000 euros. The recent amendments also make a condition that the applicants holds a valid schengen visa.\n\nFollowing recent amendments to procedures, citizenship is now only approved after 6 months rather than 3 months as before.{{when|date=February 2020}}\n\n=== New baby born ===\n\nAccording to the Republic of Cyprus Citizenship Law of 1967, anyone born on or after 16 August 1960, and with at least one parent being a Cypriot citizen, automatically acquires Cypriot citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cyprusembassy.net/home/index.php?module=page&cid=111|title=Official Website of the Embassy of the Republic of Cyprus in Washington D.C.|website=www.cyprusembassy.net|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref> Those who were born between 16 August 1960 and 1999 to a Cypriot mother abroad however, do not automatically become citizens of Cyprus, but they may register after they turn 21 years old.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dualcitizenship.com/countries/cyprus.html|title=Dual Citizenship Cyprus|website=www.dualcitizenship.com|access-date=2016-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Dual citizenship==\n\nCyprus allows its citizens to hold foreign citizenship in addition to their Cypriot citizenship. Some countries, however, do not permit multiple citizenship e.g. adults who acquired Cypriot and [[Japanese citizenship]] by birth must declare, to the latter's [[Ministry of Justice (Japan)|Ministry of Justice]], before turning 22, which citizenship they want to keep.\n\n==Citizenship of the Commonwealth of Nations==\n\nCypriot citizens are also [[Commonwealth citizen]]s as well.\n\n==Citizenship of the European Union==\n\nBecause Cyprus forms part of the [[European Union]], Cypriot citizens are also [[citizenship of the European Union|citizens of the European Union]] under [[European Union law]] and thus enjoy [[Freedom of movement for workers#Transitional provisions in new member states|rights of free movement]] and [[Cyprus (European Parliament constituency)|have the right to vote]] in [[Elections in the European Union|elections]] for the [[European Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://europa.eu/about-eu/countries/member-countries/cyprus/index_en.htm | title=Cyprus | publisher=European Union | accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref> When in a non-EU country where there is no Cypriot embassy, Cypriot citizens have the right to get consular protection from the embassy of any other EU country present in that country.<ref>Article 20(2)(c) of the [[s:Consolidated version of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union/Part Two: Non-Discrimination and Citizenship of the Union#Article 20|Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union]].</ref><ref>[[Citizenship_of_the_European_Union#Stated_rights|Rights abroad: Right to consular protection]]: a right to protection by the diplomatic or consular authorities of other Member States when in a non-EU Member State, if there are no diplomatic or consular authorities from the citizen's own state (Article 23): this is due to the fact that not all member states maintain embassies in every country in the world (14 countries have only one embassy from an EU state). [[Antigua and Barbuda]] (UK), [[Barbados]] (UK), [[Belize]] (UK), [[Central African Republic]] (France), [[Comoros]] (France), [[Gambia]] (UK), [[Guyana]] (UK), [[Liberia]] (Germany), [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]] (UK), [[San Marino]] (Italy), [[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]] (Portugal), [[Solomon Islands]] (UK), [[Timor-Leste]] (Portugal), [[Vanuatu]] (France)</ref> Cypriot citizens can live and work in any country within the EU as a result of the right of free movement and residence granted in [[Treaties of the European Union|Article 21 of the EU Treaty]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:C:2008:115:0047:0199:EN:PDF |format=PDF|title=Treaty on the Function of the European Union  (consolidated version)|publisher=Eur-lex.europa.eu|accessdate=2015-07-10}}</ref>\n\n==Travel freedom of Cypriot citizens==\n\n{{Main| Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens}}\n[[File: Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens.png|450px|thumbnail|[[Visa requirements for Cypriot citizens]]]]\n\n{{As of|2019|03|26|post=,}} Cypriot citizens had visa-free or visa on arrival access to 173 countries and territories, ranking the [[Cypriot passport]] 16th in terms of travel freedom according to the [[Henley Passport Index]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The ''Henley Passport Index'' |url=https://www.henleyglobal.com/files/download/HPI2019/Full_Q2_2019_Ranking.pdf|publisher=Henley & Partners Holdings Ltd |accessdate=4 April 2019|date=26 March 2019 |quote=This graph shows the full Global Ranking of the 2019 Henley Passport Index. In certain cases, a rank is shared by multiple countries because these countries all have the same level of visa-free or visa-on-arrival access.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the Cypriot nationality was ranked twenty-fourth in the [[The Quality of Nationality Index|Nationality Index]] (QNI). This index differs from the [[Visa (document)#Visa restrictions|Visa Restrictions Index]], which focuses on external factors including travel freedom. The QNI considers, in addition to travel freedom, on internal factors such as peace & stability, economic strength, and human development as well. <ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.businessinsider.de/nationalities-with-the-best-quality-of-life-2016-6?r=UK&IR=T |title= The 41 nationalities with the best quality of life |date= 2016-02-06 |website=  www.businessinsider.de |access-date= 2018-09-10}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[British Overseas citizen#Cyprus]]\n*[[Commonwealth citizen]]\n*[[Greek nationality law]]\n*[[Northern Cyprus citizenship]]\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite web | title=Cyprus Investment Programme | website=Stelios A. Stylianou & Co LLC | date=1 March 2019 | url=https://www.sslawyersco.com/cyprus-investment-programme-current-policy/ }}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web | title= Migration Section | website=Government of Cyprus. Civil Registry And Migration Department| url=http://www.moi.gov.cy/moi/crmd/crmd.nsf/All/044601A0B7CE6062C2257D2C0037F93F?OpenDocument}}\n\n{{Commonwealth citizenship}}\n{{Nationality laws}}\n\n[[Category:Cyprus and the Commonwealth of Nations]]\n[[Category:Nationality law]]\n[[Category:Nationality in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Cyprus]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cypriot_nationality_law"}
{"title_page": "Cyperus esculentus", "text_new": "{{speciesbox\n|name = Chufa sedge\n|image = Cyperus esculentus L. (AM AK301430-1), white background.jpg\n|status =\n|status_system =\n|genus = Cyperus\n|species = esculentus\n|authority = [[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]\n| synonyms_ref = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl/record/kew-236532|title=Cyperus esculentus L. \u2014 The Plant List|website=www.theplantlist.org}}</ref>\n| synonyms = {{collapsible list|bullets = true\n|title=<small>Synonymy</small>\n|''Chlorocyperus aureus'' <small>(K.Richt.) Palla ex Kneuck.</small>\n|''Chlorocyperus phymatodes'' <small>(Muhl.) Palla</small>\n|''Cyperus aureus'' <small>Ten</small>\n|''Cyperus aureus'' <small>(L.) Nyman</small>\n|''Cyperus bahiensis'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus buchananii'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus callistus'' <small>Ridl.</small>\n|''Cyperus chrysostachys'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus cubensis'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus damiettensis'' <small>A.Dietr.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''angustispicatus'' <small>Britton</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''angustispicatus'' <small>(Britton) Fernald</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' subsp. ''aureus'' <small>K.Richt.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''cyclolepis'' <small>Boeckeler ex K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''evolutus'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''heermannii'' <small>(Buckley) Britton</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''helodes'' <small>(Schrad. ex Nees) C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''leptostachyus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''lutescens'' <small>(Torr. & Hook.) K\u00fck. ex Osten</small> \t\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''lutescens'' <small>(Torr. & Hook.) K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''macrostachyus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''macrostachyus'' <small>(Boeckeler) Fernald</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''phymatodes'' <small>(Muhl.) K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''princeps'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''sativus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''sprucei'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus fresenii'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus fulvescens'' <small>Liebm.</small>\n|''Cyperus gracilescens'' <small>Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus gracilis'' <small>Link</small>\n|''Cyperus heermannii'' <small>Buckley</small>\n|''Cyperus helodes'' <small>Schrad. ex Nees</small>\n|''Cyperus hydra'' <small>Kunth</small> \n|''Cyperus lutescens'' <small>Torr. & Hook.</small>\n|''Cyperus melanorhizus'' <small>Delile</small>\n|''Cyperus nervosus'' <small>Bertol.</small>\n|''Cyperus officinalis'' <small>T.Nees</small>\n|''Cyperus pallidus'' <small>Savi</small> \n|''Cyperus phymatodes'' <small>Muhl.</small>\n|''Cyperus phymatodes'' var. ''heermannii'' <small>(Buckley) S.Watson</small>\n|''Cyperus repens'' <small>Elliott</small>\n|''Cyperus ruficomus'' <small>Buckley</small>\n|''Cyperus scirpoides'' <small>R.Br.</small>\n|''Cyperus sieberianus'' <small>Link</small>\n|''Cyperus tenoreanus'' <small>Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus tenorei'' <small>C.Presl</small>\n|''Cyperus tenorianus'' <small>Roem. & Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus tuberosus'' <small>Pursh</small>\n|''Cyperus variabilis'' <small>Salzm. ex Steud.</small>\n|''Pterocyperus esculentus'' <small>(L.) Opiz</small>\n|''Pycreus esculentus'' <small>(L.) Hayek</small>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Cyperus esculentus''''' (also called '''chufa sedge''', '''nut grass''', '''yellow nutsedge''', '''tiger nutsedge''', '''edible galingale''', '''water grass''' or '''earth almond''') is a crop of the [[Cyperaceae|sedge]] family widespread across much of the world.<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1111/j.1541-4337.2012.00190.x| issn = 1541-4337| volume = 11| issue = 4| pages = 366\u2013377| last1 = S\u00e1nchez\u2010Zapata| first1 = Elena| last2 = Fern\u00e1ndez\u2010L\u00f3pez| first2 = Juana| last3 = P\u00e9rez\u2010Alvarez| first3 = Jos\u00e9 Angel| title = Tiger Nut (Cyperus esculentus) Commercialization: Health Aspects, Composition, Properties, and Food Applications| journal = Comprehensive Reviews in Food Science and Food Safety| date = 2012-07-01}}</ref> It is found in most of the [[Eastern Hemisphere]], including [[Southern Europe]], [[Africa]] and [[Madagascar]], as well as the [[Middle East]] and the [[Indian subcontinent]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=236532|title=World Checklist of Selected Plant Families: Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew|website=apps.kew.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bonap.net/MapGallery/County/Cyperus%20esculentus.png|title=Biota of North America Program, 2013 county distribution map}}</ref><ref>[http://luirig.altervista.org/flora/taxa/index1.php?scientific-name=cyperus+esculentus Altervista Flora Italiana, Zigolo dolce, Yellow Nutsedge, ''Cyperus esculentus'' L. ] includes photographs plus distribution maps for Europe and North America</ref><ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=250095841 Flora of China, Vol. 23 Page 232, you suo cao ''Cyperus esculentus'' Linnaeus var. ''sativus'' Boeckeler, Linnaea. 36: 290. 1870. ]</ref> ''C. esculentus'' is cultivated for its edible [[tuber]]s, called earth almonds or tiger nuts, as a [[snack food]] and for the preparation of ''[[horchata]] de chufa'', a sweet, milk-like beverage.<ref name=cabi/>\n\n''Cyperus esculentus'' can be found wild, as a weed, or as a crop. It is an [[invasive species]] outside its native range, and is readily transported accidentally to become invasive.<ref name=\"cabi\">{{cite web |title=''Cyperus esculentus'' (yellow nutsedge) |url=https://www.cabi.org/isc/datasheet/17496 |publisher=CABI |accessdate=31 October 2019 |date=19 November 2018}}</ref> In many countries, ''C. esculentus'' is considered a weed.<ref name=cabi/><ref name=tiger>{{cite journal | last1 = S\u00e1nchez-Zapata | first1 = E | last2 = Fern\u00e1ndez-L\u00f3pez | first2 = J | last3 = Angel P\u00e9rez-Alvarez | first3 = J | year = 2012 | title = Tiger Nut (''Cyperus esculentus'') Commercialization: Health Aspects, Composition, Properties, and Food Applications | url = | journal = Comprehensive Reviews in Food Science and Food Safety | volume = 11 | issue = 4| pages = 366\u201377 | doi=10.1111/j.1541-4337.2012.00190.x}}</ref> It is often found in wet soils such as rice paddies and peanut farms as well as well-irrigated lawns and golf courses during warm weather.\n\n==History==\nPrehistoric tools with traces of ''C. esculentus'' tuber starch granules have been recovered from the early [[Archaic period in North America]], from about 9,000 years ago, at the Sandy Hill excavation site at the Mashantucket Pequot Reservation in Mashantucket, [[Connecticut]]. The tubers are believed to have been a source of food for those [[Paleo-Indians]].<ref>{{cite journal|title= Preliminary Starch Grain Evidence of Ancient Stone Tool Use at the Early Archaic (9,000 B.P.) Site of Sandy Hill, Mashantucket, Connecticut |doi=10.14237/ebl.4.2013.87-95 | volume=4 |journal=Ethnobiology Letters |pages=87|year= 2013|last1= Hart|first1= Thomas C|last2= Ives|first2= Timothy H|doi-access= free}}</ref>\n\nZohary and Hopf estimate that  ''C. esculentus'' \"ranks among the oldest cultivated plants in [[Ancient Egypt]]\", although noting that \"chufa was no doubt an important food element in ancient Egypt during dynastic times, its cultivation in ancient times seems to have remained (totally or almost totally) an Egyptian specialty\".<ref>Daniel Zohary and Maria Hopf, ''Domestication of plants in the Old World'', third edition (Oxford: University Press, 2000), p. 198</ref> Its dry tubers have been found in tombs from predynastic times about 6000 years ago. In those times, ''C. esculentus'' tubers were consumed either boiled in beer, roasted, or as sweets made of ground tubers with honey.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Moshe | first1 = N | year = 1992 | title = A Sweetmeat Plant, a Perfume Plant and their Weedy Relatives: A Chapter in the History of C. Esculentus L. and C. Rotundus L. | url = | journal = Economic Botany | volume = 46 | issue = | pages = 64\u201371 | doi=10.1007/bf02985255}}</ref> The tubers were also used medicinally, taken orally, as an ointment, or as an enema, and used in fumigants to sweeten the smell of homes or clothing.<ref name=god>{{cite journal | last1 = Defelice | first1 = MS | year = 2002 | title = Yellow Nutsedge: ''Cyperus esculentus'' L. \u2014 Snack Food of the Gods1 | url = | journal = Weed Technology | volume = 16 | issue = 4| pages = 901\u20137 | doi=10.1614/0890-037x(2002)016[0901:yncels]2.0.co;2}}</ref> There are almost no contemporary records of this plant in other parts of the old World.\n\nBesides Egypt, at present ''C. esculentus'' is cultivated mainly in Spain, where it is extended for common commercial purposes in mild climate areas. The plant was introduced by the [[Arabs]], first in the [[Valencia (autonomous community)|Valencia]] region. They are found extensively too in [[California]] and were grown by the [[Northern Paiute|Paiute]] in [[Owens Valley]].<ref>citation needed</ref> \n''C. esculentus'' is also cultivated in countries such as [[Guatemala]], Mexico, [[Chile]], [[Brasil]], the United States, [[Lebanon]], [[Syria]], [[Jordan]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Oman]], [[Iran]], [[Iraq]], [[Pakistan]], [[India]], [[Yemen]], [[Morocco]], [[Ivory Coast]], [[Sudan]], [[South Sudan]], [[Gambia]], [[Guinea Bissau]], [[Ghana]], [[Niger]], [[Nigeria]], [[Burkina Faso]], [[Togo]], [[Benin]], [[Cameroon#Administrative divisions|Northern Cameroon]], and [[Mali]], where they are used primarily as animal feed or uncooked as a side dish, but in Hispanic countries they are used mainly to make ''horchata'', a sweet, milk-like beverage.\nIn [[Northern Nigeria]], it is called ''aya'' and it is usually eaten fresh. It is sometimes dried and later rehydrated and eaten. Also a snack is made by toasting the nuts and sugar coating it is popular among the [[Hausa people|Hausa]] children of [[Northern Nigeria]]. Also, a drink known as ''kunun aya'' is made by processing the nuts with [[Date (fruit)|dates]] and later sieved and served chilled.\n\nIt has been suggested that the extinct [[hominin]] ''[[Paranthropus boisei]]'', the ''Nutcracker Man'', subsisted on tiger nuts.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Macho | first1 = G. A. | editor1-last = Hardy | editor1-first = Karen | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0084942 | title = Baboon Feeding Ecology Informs the Dietary Niche of Paranthropus boisei | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 9 | issue = 1 | pages = e84942 | year = 2014 | pmid =  24416315| pmc = 3885648| bibcode = 2014PLoSO...984942M }}</ref>\n\n==Botany==\n[[image:Chufa.jpg|thumb|right|Young plant with tuber]]\n''Cyperus esculentus'' is an [[annual plant|annual]] or [[perennial]] plant, growing to {{convert|90|cm|ft|abbr=on}} tall, with solitary stems growing from a tuber. The plant is reproduced by seeds, creeping rhizomes, and tubers.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=Yellow Nut Sedge: A Menace in the Corn Belt (No. 1642)|last=Stoller|first=E.W.|publisher=US Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service.|year=1981|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> Due to its clonal nature, ''C. esculentus'' can take advantage of soil disturbances caused by anthropogenic or natural forces.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Renne|first=Ian J.|last2=Tracy|first2=Benjamin F.|date=2006-08-30|title=Disturbance persistence in managed grasslands: shifts in aboveground community structure and the weed seed bank|journal=Plant Ecology |language=en|volume=190|issue=1|pages=71\u201380|doi=10.1007/s11258-006-9191-7|issn=1385-0237}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Oldfield |first=Callie A.|last2=Evans|first2=Jonathan P.|date=2016-03-01|title=Twelve years of repeated wild hog activity promotes population maintenance of an invasive clonal plant in a coastal dune ecosystem|journal=Ecology and Evolution|language=en|pages=2569\u20132578 |doi=10.1002/ece3.2045 |pmid=27110354|pmc=4834338|issn=2045-7758|volume=6|issue=8}}</ref> The stems are triangular in section and bear slender [[leaf|leaves]] 3\u201310&nbsp;mm (1/8 to 1/2 inches) wide. The spikelets of the plant are distinctive, with a cluster of flat, oval seeds surrounded by four hanging, leaf-like [[bract]]s positioned 90 degrees from each other. They are 5 to 30&nbsp;mm (about 3/8 to 1 1/8 inches) long and linear to narrowly elliptic with pointed tips and 8 to 35 florets. The color varies from straw-colored to gold-brown. They can produce up to 2420 seeds per plant. The plant foliage is very tough and fibrous and is often mistaken for a [[grass]]. The roots are an extensive and complex system of fine, fibrous roots and scaly rhizomes with small, hard, spherical tubers and basal [[bulbs]] attached. \n\nThe tubers are 0.3 \u2013 1.9&nbsp;cm (1/8 to 3/4 inches) in diameter and the colors vary between yellow, brown, and black.<ref name=Factsheet>^ USGS Weeds in the West project: Status of introduced Plants in Southern Arizona Parks, Factsheets for Cyperus esculentus L., 2003, Tucson, Arizona</ref> One plant can produce several hundred to several thousand tubers during a single growing season. With cool temperatures, the foliage, roots, rhizomes, and basal bulbs die, but the tubers survive and resprout the following spring when soil temperatures remain above {{convert|6|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\":0\" /> They can resprout up to several years later.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stoller|first=E. W.|last2=Wax|first2=L. M.|date=1973-01-01|title=Yellow Nutsedge Shoot Emergence and Tuber Longevity|jstor=4042258|journal=Weed Science|volume=21|issue=1|pages=76\u201381|doi=10.1017/S004317450003174X}}</ref> When the tubers germinate, many rhizomes are initiated and end in a basal bulb near the soil surface. These basal bulbs initiate the stems and leaves above ground, and fibrous roots underground. ''C. esculentus'' is wind pollinated and requires [[cross pollination]] as it is self\u2013incompatible.\n\n==Invasiveness==\n''C. esculentus'' is a highly invasive species in [[Oceania]], [[Mexico]], some United States, and the [[Caribbean]], mainly by seed dispersion.<ref name=cabi/> It is readily transported internationally, and is adaptable to re-establish in varied climate and soil environments.<ref name=cabi/> In Japan, it is an exotic [[cloning|clonal]] weed favorable to establish in wet habitats.<ref name=cabi/>\n\n==Cultivation==\n[[File:Proc\u00e9s de cultiu de la xufa.jpeg|thumb|right|250px|Cultivation and growing of the ''xufa'' in the [[Land of Valencia]], file by [[Valencian Museum of Ethnology]]]]\n\n===Climate requirements===\n''Cyperus esculentus'' cultivation requires a mild climate. Low temperature, shade, and light intensity can inhibit flowering.<ref name=Factsheet/> Tuber initiation is inhibited by high levels of nitrogen, long photoperiods, and high levels of [[gibberellic acid]]. Flower initiation occurs under photoperiods of 12 to 14 hours per day.\n\n===Soil requirements===\nTubers can develop in soil depths  around 30&nbsp;cm (1-foot), but most occur in the top or upper part. They tolerate many adverse soil conditions including periods of drought and flooding and survive soil temperatures around {{convert|-5|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}. They grow best on sandy, moist soils at a pH between 5.0 \u2013 7.5.<ref name=Factsheet/> The densest populations of ''C. esculentus'' are often found in low-lying wetlands.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ross|first1=Merrill A.|last2=Lembi|first2=Carole A.|title=Applied Weed Science|publisher=Prentice Hall|edition=3|year=2008|page=322|isbn=978-0135028148}}</ref> They do not tolerate salinity.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\n==Agronomy==\n\n===Cultivation===\nPlanting is normally done on flat soils where ridges to favour the coming irrigations have previously been done. The separation between ridges is approximately {{convert|60|cm|ft|abbr=on}} and seeds are planted manually. Distances between seeds may vary from {{convert|15|to|20|cm|in|round=0.5|abbr=on}} and seeding depth is around {{convert|8|cm|in|frac=2|abbr=on}}. A typical seeding rate for chufa is about 120&nbsp;kg of tubers/ha (107&nbsp;lbs/acre).<ref>N. Pascual-Seva, et al., ''Furrow-irrigated chufa crops in Valencia (Spain)'' Spanish Journal of Agricultural Research 2013 11(1), 258-267.  http://revistas.inia.es/index.php/sjar/article/view/3385/1803</ref>\n\nThey are planted between April and May and must be irrigated every week until they are harvested in November and December. Tubers develop about 6 \u2013 8 weeks after seedling emergence and grow quickly during July and August. The maturing is around 90 \u2013 110 days. The average yield can approach between 10 and 19 t/ha.<ref>Pascual-Seva, N., San Bautista, A., L\u00f3pez Galarza, S., Maroto, J.V. and Pascual, B. 2012. Yield and Irrigation Water Use Efficiency for Ridge - and Bed - cultivated Chufa (''Cyperus Esculentus'' L. var. ''Sativus Boeck''). Acta Hort. (ISHS) 936:125-132</ref><ref>Reid WS, Hergert GB, Fagan WE, 1972. Development of a Prototype mechanical Harvester for Chufa (''Cyperus esculentus'' L. var ''sativus Boek''). Canadian Agricultural Engineering 14.</ref>\n\n===Harvest and drying process===\nHarvest usually occurs in November or December and the leaves are scorched during the harvest. With a combine harvester, the tiger nut is pulled out of the ground. Immediately after harvesting, the tiger nuts are washed with water in order to remove sand and small stones. The drying occurs usually in the sun and can take up to three months.<ref name=month>Tigernuts Traders, S.L., ''Tigernuts Oil'', 2012, http://www.tigernut.com</ref> The temperatures and humidity levels have to be monitored very carefully during this period. The tiger nuts have to be turned every day to ensure uniform drying. The drying process ensures a longer shelf life. This prevents rot or other bacterial infections, securing quality and high nutrition levels.\nDisadvantages in the drying process are shrinkage, skin wrinkles and hard nut texture.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n===Storage===\nTiger nut loses a considerable amount of water during drying and storage. The starch content of the tiger nut tubers decreases and the reducing sugar (invert sugar) content increases during storage.<ref>{{cite journal|title= Physical and chemical properties of chufa (Cyperus esculentus L) tubers grown in the \u00c7ukurova region of Turkey |doi=10.1002/jsfa.1091 | volume=82 |issue= 6|journal=Journal of the Science of Food and Agriculture |pages=625\u2013631|year= 2002|last1= Co\u015fkuner|first1= Yal\u00e7\u0131n|last2= Ercan|first2= Recai|last3= Karababa|first3= Er\u015fan|last4= Nazl\u0131can|first4= Ahmet Nedim}}</ref> Tiger nut can be stored dry and rehydrated by soaking without losing the crisp texture. Soaking is often done overnight. Dried tiger nuts have a hard texture and soaking is indispensable to render them edible with ease and to ensure acceptable sensory quality.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\nAccording to the ''Consejo Regulador de Chufa de Valencia'' (Regulating Council for Valencia's Tiger Nuts),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chufadevalencia.org/ |title=''Consejo Regulador de Chufa de Valencia'' |publisher=Chufadevalencia.org |date=2002-12-31 |accessdate=2012-06-05}}</ref> the nutritional composition/100 ml of the Spanish beverage horchata de chufas is as follows: energy content around 66 kcal, [[protein]]s around 0.5 g, [[carbohydrate]]s over 10 g with [[starch]] at least 1.9 g, [[fat]]s at least 2 g.\n\n==Uses==\nDried tiger nut has a smooth, tender, sweet, and nutty taste. It can be consumed raw, roasted, dried, baked or as tiger nut milk or oil.\n\n===Food===\n\n[[File:Cyperus esculentus MS 4388.jpg|thumb|right|Dried tubers sold at the market of [[Banfora]], [[Burkina Faso]].]]\n\nThe tubers are [[Eating|edible]], with a slightly sweet, nutty flavour, compared to the more bitter-tasting tuber of the related ''[[Cyperus rotundus]]'' (purple nutsedge). They are quite hard and are generally soaked in water before they can be eaten, making them much softer and giving them a better texture. They are a popular snack in West Africa.\n\nThey have various uses, such as [[horchata]], a nonalcoholic beverage of milky appearance derived from the tubers of the tiger nut plant mixed with sugar and water, and commonly consumed in Spain.<ref name=\"soto\">{{cite journal | last=Rosell\u00f3-Soto | first=Elena | last2=Poojary | first2=Mahesha M. | last3=Barba | first3=Francisco J. | last4=Koubaa | first4=Mohamed | last5=Lorenzo | first5=Jose M. | last6=Ma\u00f1es | first6=Jordi | last7=Molt\u00f3 | first7=Juan Carlos | title=Thermal and non-thermal preservation techniques of tiger nuts' beverage \"horchata de chufa\". Implications for food safety, nutritional and quality properties | journal=Food Research International  | volume=105 | year=2018 | issn=0963-9969 | pmid=29433293 | doi=10.1016/j.foodres.2017.12.014 | pages=945\u2013951}}</ref>\n\nFlour of roasted tiger nut is sometimes added to biscuits and other bakery products as well as in making oil, soap, and starch extracts. It is also used for the production of nougat, jam, beer, and as a flavoring agent in ice cream and in the preparation of [[kunnu]] (a local beverage in Nigeria).{{Citation needed|date=December 2019|reason=removed citation to predatory publisher content}}  Kunnu is a nonalcoholic beverage prepared mainly from cereals (such as millet or sorghum) by heating and mixing with spices (dandelion, alligator pepper, ginger, licorice) and sugar. To make up for the poor nutritional value of kunnu prepared from cereals, tiger nut was found to be a good substitute for cereal grains. Tiger nut oil can be used naturally with salads or for deep frying. It is considered to be a high quality oil. Tiger nut \u201cmilk\u201d has been tried as an alternative source of milk in fermented products, such as yogurt production, and other fermented products common in some African countries and can thus be useful replacing [[milk]] in the diet of people intolerant to [[lactose]] to a certain extent.<ref name=tiger />\n\n===Nutrition===\nDespite its name, tiger nutsedge is a tuber. However, its chemical composition shares characteristics with tubers and with nuts. This tuber is rich in energy content (starch, fat, sugar, and protein), and [[dietary mineral]]s (mainly [[phosphorus]] and [[potassium]]). The oil of the tuber was found to contain 18% saturated ([[palmitic acid]] and [[stearic acid]]) and 82% unsaturated ([[oleic acid]] and [[linoleic acid]]) [[fatty acid]]s.<ref name=zhang>{{cite journal|title= Yellow nut-sedge tuber oil as a fuel |doi=10.1016/0926-6690(96)89446-5 | volume=5 |issue= 3|journal=Industrial Crops and Products |pages=177\u2013181|year= 1996|last1= Zhang|first1= He Yuan|last2= Hanna|first2= Milford A|last3= Ali|first3= Yusuf|last4= Nan|first4= Lu}}</ref>\n\n===Oil===\nSince the tubers of ''C. esculentus'' contain 20-36% oil, it has been suggested as potential oil crop for the production of [[biodiesel]].<ref name=zhang/> One study found that chufa produced 1.5 metric tonnes of oil per hectare (174 gallons/acre) based on a tuber yield of 5.67 t/ha and an oil content of 26.4%.<ref name=\"sedge\">{{cite journal | last=Makareviciene | first=Violeta | last2=Gumbyte | first2=Milda | last3=Yunik | first3=Anatolii | last4=Kalenska | first4=Svitlana | last5=Kalenskii | first5=Viktor | last6=Rachmetov | first6=Dzhamal | last7=Sendzikiene | first7=Egle | title=Opportunities for the use of chufa sedge in biodiesel production | journal=Industrial Crops and Products | volume=50 | year=2013 | issn=0926-6690 | doi=10.1016/j.indcrop.2013.08.036 | pages=633\u2013637}}</ref> A similar 6-year study found tuber yields ranging from 4.02 to 6.75 t/ha, with an average oil content of 26.5% and an average oil yield of 1.47 t/ha.<ref>Bilali et al., \"Exploring Serbian consumers\u2019 attitude toward ethical values of organic, fair-trade and typical/traditional products\" The Fifth International Scientific Conference, Rural Development 2011, Proceedings, Volume 5, Book 1, p. 337.</ref>\n\n===Fishing bait===\nThe boiled nuts are used in the UK as a bait for [[Common carp|carp]]. The nuts have to be prepared in a prescribed manner to prevent harm to the fish. The nuts are soaked in water for 24 hours, and then boiled for 20 minutes or longer until fully expanded. Some anglers then leave the boiled nuts to ferment for 24\u201348 hours, which can enhance their effectiveness. If the nuts are not properly prepared, they can be  toxic to carp. This was originally thought to have been the cause of death of [[Benson (fish)|Benson]], a large, well-known female carp weighing {{Convert|54|lb|kg|abbr=on}} found floating dead in a fishing lake, with a bag of unprepared tiger nuts lying nearby, empty, on the bank. An examination of the fish by a [[taxidermist]] concluded tiger nut poisoning was not the cause of death, but rather the fish had died naturally.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bailey |first=John |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB125051804649836945 |title=The extraordinary life and suspicious death of Benson the giant carp |publisher=The Guardian |date=5 August 2009 |accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Compatibility with other crops==\n[[File:Cyperus esculentus NRCS-1.jpg|thumb|160px|The seed head of a ''Cyperus esculentus'' plant]]\n''C. esculentus'' is extremely difficult to remove completely once established. This is due to the plant having a stratified and layered root system, with tubers and roots being interconnected to a depth of 36&nbsp;cm or more.<ref name=Factsheet/> The tubers are connected by fragile roots that are prone to snapping when pulled, making the root system difficult to remove intact. Intermediate rhizomes can potentially reach a length of 60&nbsp;cm. The plant can quickly regenerate if a single tuber is left in place. By competing for light, water and nutrients it can reduce the vigour of neighbouring plants. It can develop into a dense colony. Patch boundaries can increase by more than one meter per year. Tubers and seed disperse with agricultural activities, soil movement or by water and wind. They are often known as a contaminant in crop seeds. When plants are small they are hard to distinguish from other weeds such as ''[[Dactylis glomerata]]'' and ''[[Elytrigia repens]]''. Thus it is hard to discover in an early stage and therefore hard to counteract. Once it is detected, mechanical removal, hand removal, grazing, damping, and herbicides can be used to inhibit ''C. esculentus''.\n\n===Similar native or non-native species that can confuse identification===\n* [[Sedges]] (''Cyperus'') have grass-like leaves and resemble each other in the appearance. They can mainly be distinguished from grasses by their triangular stems.\n* Purple nutsedge (''[[Cyperus rotundus|C. rotundus]]'') is another weedy sedge that is similar to the yellow nutsedge (''C. esculentus''). These two sedges are difficult to distinguish from each other and can be found growing on the same site. Some differences are the purple spikelets and the tubers formed by ''C. rotundus'' are often multiple instead of just one at the tip. In addition the tubers have a bitter taste instead of the mild almond-like flavour of ''C. esculentus''.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{WestAfricanPlants|Cyperus esculentus}}\n{{Commons category}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1165724}}\n\n[[Category:Flora of North America]]\n[[Category:Flora of Europe]]\n[[Category:Flora of Asia]]\n[[Category:Flora of Africa]]\n[[Category:Flora of South America]]\n[[Category:Flora of the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:Edible nuts and seeds]]\n[[Category:Cyperus|esculentus]]\n[[Category:Valencian Community]]\n[[Category:Root vegetables]]\n[[Category:Plants described in 1753]]\n", "text_old": "{{speciesbox\n|name = Chufa sedge\n|image = Cyperus esculentus L. (AM AK301430-1), white background.jpg\n|status =\n|status_system =\n|genus = Cyperus\n|species = esculentus\n|authority = [[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]\n| synonyms_ref = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theplantlist.org/tpl/record/kew-236532|title=Cyperus esculentus L. \u2014 The Plant List|website=www.theplantlist.org}}</ref>\n| synonyms = {{collapsible list|bullets = true\n|title=<small>Synonymy</small>\n|''Chlorocyperus aureus'' <small>(K.Richt.) Palla ex Kneuck.</small>\n|''Chlorocyperus phymatodes'' <small>(Muhl.) Palla</small>\n|''Cyperus aureus'' <small>Ten</small>\n|''Cyperus aureus'' <small>(L.) Nyman</small>\n|''Cyperus bahiensis'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus buchananii'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus callistus'' <small>Ridl.</small>\n|''Cyperus chrysostachys'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus cubensis'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus damiettensis'' <small>A.Dietr.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''angustispicatus'' <small>Britton</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''angustispicatus'' <small>(Britton) Fernald</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' subsp. ''aureus'' <small>K.Richt.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''cyclolepis'' <small>Boeckeler ex K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''evolutus'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''heermannii'' <small>(Buckley) Britton</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''helodes'' <small>(Schrad. ex Nees) C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''leptostachyus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''lutescens'' <small>(Torr. & Hook.) K\u00fck. ex Osten</small> \t\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''lutescens'' <small>(Torr. & Hook.) K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''macrostachyus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''macrostachyus'' <small>(Boeckeler) Fernald</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''phymatodes'' <small>(Muhl.) K\u00fck.</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' f. ''princeps'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''sativus'' <small>Boeckeler</small>\n|''Cyperus esculentus'' var. ''sprucei'' <small>C.B.Clarke</small>\n|''Cyperus fresenii'' <small>Steud.</small>\n|''Cyperus fulvescens'' <small>Liebm.</small>\n|''Cyperus gracilescens'' <small>Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus gracilis'' <small>Link</small>\n|''Cyperus heermannii'' <small>Buckley</small>\n|''Cyperus helodes'' <small>Schrad. ex Nees</small>\n|''Cyperus hydra'' <small>Kunth</small> \n|''Cyperus lutescens'' <small>Torr. & Hook.</small>\n|''Cyperus melanorhizus'' <small>Delile</small>\n|''Cyperus nervosus'' <small>Bertol.</small>\n|''Cyperus officinalis'' <small>T.Nees</small>\n|''Cyperus pallidus'' <small>Savi</small> \n|''Cyperus phymatodes'' <small>Muhl.</small>\n|''Cyperus phymatodes'' var. ''heermannii'' <small>(Buckley) S.Watson</small>\n|''Cyperus repens'' <small>Elliott</small>\n|''Cyperus ruficomus'' <small>Buckley</small>\n|''Cyperus scirpoides'' <small>R.Br.</small>\n|''Cyperus sieberianus'' <small>Link</small>\n|''Cyperus tenoreanus'' <small>Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus tenorei'' <small>C.Presl</small>\n|''Cyperus tenorianus'' <small>Roem. & Schult.</small>\n|''Cyperus tuberosus'' <small>Pursh</small>\n|''Cyperus variabilis'' <small>Salzm. ex Steud.</small>\n|''Pterocyperus esculentus'' <small>(L.) Opiz</small>\n|''Pycreus esculentus'' <small>(L.) Hayek</small>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Cyperus esculentus''''' (also called '''chufa sedge''', '''nut grass''', '''yellow nutsedge''', '''tiger nutsedge''', '''edible galingale''', '''water grass''' or '''earth almond''') is a crop of the [[Cyperaceae|sedge]] family widespread across much of the world.<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1111/j.1541-4337.2012.00190.x| issn = 1541-4337| volume = 11| issue = 4| pages = 366\u2013377| last1 = S\u00e1nchez\u2010Zapata| first1 = Elena| last2 = Fern\u00e1ndez\u2010L\u00f3pez| first2 = Juana| last3 = P\u00e9rez\u2010Alvarez| first3 = Jos\u00e9 Angel| title = Tiger Nut (Cyperus esculentus) Commercialization: Health Aspects, Composition, Properties, and Food Applications| journal = Comprehensive Reviews in Food Science and Food Safety| date = 2012-07-01}}</ref> It is found in most of the [[Eastern Hemisphere]], including [[Southern Europe]], [[Africa]] and [[Madagascar]], as well as the [[Middle East]] and the [[Indian subcontinent]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=236532|title=World Checklist of Selected Plant Families: Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew|website=apps.kew.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bonap.net/MapGallery/County/Cyperus%20esculentus.png|title=Biota of North America Program, 2013 county distribution map}}</ref><ref>[http://luirig.altervista.org/flora/taxa/index1.php?scientific-name=cyperus+esculentus Altervista Flora Italiana, Zigolo dolce, Yellow Nutsedge, ''Cyperus esculentus'' L. ] includes photographs plus distribution maps for Europe and North America</ref><ref>[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=250095841 Flora of China, Vol. 23 Page 232, you suo cao ''Cyperus esculentus'' Linnaeus var. ''sativus'' Boeckeler, Linnaea. 36: 290. 1870. ]</ref> ''C. esculentus'' is cultivated for its edible [[tuber]]s, called earth almonds or tiger nuts, as a [[snack food]] and for the preparation of ''[[horchata]] de chufa'', a sweet, milk-like beverage.<ref name=cabi/>\n\n''Cyperus esculentus'' can be found wild, as a weed, or as a crop. It is an [[invasive species]] outside its native range, and is readily transported accidentally to become invasive.<ref name=\"cabi\">{{cite web |title=''Cyperus esculentus'' (yellow nutsedge) |url=https://www.cabi.org/isc/datasheet/17496 |publisher=CABI |accessdate=31 October 2019 |date=19 November 2018}}</ref> In many countries, ''C. esculentus'' is considered a weed.<ref name=cabi/><ref name=tiger>{{cite journal | last1 = S\u00e1nchez-Zapata | first1 = E | last2 = Fern\u00e1ndez-L\u00f3pez | first2 = J | last3 = Angel P\u00e9rez-Alvarez | first3 = J | year = 2012 | title = Tiger Nut (''Cyperus esculentus'') Commercialization: Health Aspects, Composition, Properties, and Food Applications | url = | journal = Comprehensive Reviews in Food Science and Food Safety | volume = 11 | issue = 4| pages = 366\u201377 | doi=10.1111/j.1541-4337.2012.00190.x}}</ref> It is often found in wet soils such as rice paddies and peanut farms as well as well-irrigated lawns and golf courses during warm weather.\n\n==History==\nPrehistoric tools with traces of ''C. esculentus'' tuber starch granules have been recovered from the early [[Archaic period in North America]], from about 9,000 years ago, at the Sandy Hill excavation site at the Mashantucket Pequot Reservation in Mashantucket, [[Connecticut]]. The tubers are believed to have been a source of food for those [[Paleo-Indians]].<ref>{{cite journal|title= Preliminary Starch Grain Evidence of Ancient Stone Tool Use at the Early Archaic (9,000 B.P.) Site of Sandy Hill, Mashantucket, Connecticut |doi=10.14237/ebl.4.2013.87-95 | volume=4 |journal=Ethnobiology Letters |pages=87|year= 2013|last1= Hart|first1= Thomas C|last2= Ives|first2= Timothy H|doi-access= free}}</ref>\n\nZohary and Hopf estimate that  ''C. esculentus'' \"ranks among the oldest cultivated plants in [[Ancient Egypt]]\", although noting that \"chufa was no doubt an important food element in ancient Egypt during dynastic times, its cultivation in ancient times seems to have remained (totally or almost totally) an Egyptian specialty\".<ref>Daniel Zohary and Maria Hopf, ''Domestication of plants in the Old World'', third edition (Oxford: University Press, 2000), p. 198</ref> Its dry tubers have been found in tombs from predynastic times about 6000 years ago. In those times, ''C. esculentus'' tubers were consumed either boiled in beer, roasted, or as sweets made of ground tubers with honey.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Moshe | first1 = N | year = 1992 | title = A Sweetmeat Plant, a Perfume Plant and their Weedy Relatives: A Chapter in the History of C. Esculentus L. and C. Rotundus L. | url = | journal = Economic Botany | volume = 46 | issue = | pages = 64\u201371 | doi=10.1007/bf02985255}}</ref> The tubers were also used medicinally, taken orally, as an ointment, or as an enema, and used in fumigants to sweeten the smell of homes or clothing.<ref name=god>{{cite journal | last1 = Defelice | first1 = MS | year = 2002 | title = Yellow Nutsedge: ''Cyperus esculentus'' L. \u2014 Snack Food of the Gods1 | url = | journal = Weed Technology | volume = 16 | issue = 4| pages = 901\u20137 | doi=10.1614/0890-037x(2002)016[0901:yncels]2.0.co;2}}</ref> There are almost no contemporary records of this plant in other parts of the old World.\n\nBesides Egypt, at present ''C. esculentus'' is cultivated mainly in Spain, where it is extended for common commercial purposes in mild climate areas. The plant was introduced by the [[Arabs]], first in the [[Valencia (autonomous community)|Valencia]] region. They are found extensively too in [[California]] and were grown by the [[Northern Paiute|Paiute]] in [[Owens Valley]]<ref>citation needed</ref>. \n''C. esculentus'' is also cultivated in countries such as [[Guatemala]], Mexico, [[Chile]], [[Brasil]], the United States, [[Lebanon]], [[Syria]], [[Jordan]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Oman]], [[Iran]], [[Iraq]], [[Pakistan]], [[India]], [[Yemen]], [[Morocco]], [[Ivory Coast]], [[Sudan]], [[South Sudan]], [[Gambia]], [[Guinea Bissau]], [[Ghana]], [[Niger]], [[Nigeria]], [[Burkina Faso]], [[Togo]], [[Benin]], [[Cameroon#Administrative divisions|Northern Cameroon]], and [[Mali]], where they are used primarily as animal feed or uncooked as a side dish, but in Hispanic countries they are used mainly to make ''horchata'', a sweet, milk-like beverage.\nIn [[Northern Nigeria]], it is called ''aya'' and it is usually eaten fresh. It is sometimes dried and later rehydrated and eaten. Also a snack is made by toasting the nuts and sugar coating it is popular among the [[Hausa people|Hausa]] children of [[Northern Nigeria]]. Also, a drink known as ''kunun aya'' is made by processing the nuts with [[Date (fruit)|dates]] and later sieved and served chilled.\n\nIt has been suggested that the extinct [[hominin]] ''[[Paranthropus boisei]]'', the ''Nutcracker Man'', subsisted on tiger nuts.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Macho | first1 = G. A. | editor1-last = Hardy | editor1-first = Karen | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0084942 | title = Baboon Feeding Ecology Informs the Dietary Niche of Paranthropus boisei | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 9 | issue = 1 | pages = e84942 | year = 2014 | pmid =  24416315| pmc = 3885648| bibcode = 2014PLoSO...984942M }}</ref>\n\n==Botany==\n[[image:Chufa.jpg|thumb|right|Young plant with tuber]]\n''Cyperus esculentus'' is an [[annual plant|annual]] or [[perennial]] plant, growing to {{convert|90|cm|ft|abbr=on}} tall, with solitary stems growing from a tuber. The plant is reproduced by seeds, creeping rhizomes, and tubers.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|title=Yellow Nut Sedge: A Menace in the Corn Belt (No. 1642)|last=Stoller|first=E.W.|publisher=US Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service.|year=1981|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref> Due to its clonal nature, ''C. esculentus'' can take advantage of soil disturbances caused by anthropogenic or natural forces.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Renne|first=Ian J.|last2=Tracy|first2=Benjamin F.|date=2006-08-30|title=Disturbance persistence in managed grasslands: shifts in aboveground community structure and the weed seed bank|journal=Plant Ecology |language=en|volume=190|issue=1|pages=71\u201380|doi=10.1007/s11258-006-9191-7|issn=1385-0237}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Oldfield |first=Callie A.|last2=Evans|first2=Jonathan P.|date=2016-03-01|title=Twelve years of repeated wild hog activity promotes population maintenance of an invasive clonal plant in a coastal dune ecosystem|journal=Ecology and Evolution|language=en|pages=2569\u20132578 |doi=10.1002/ece3.2045 |pmid=27110354|pmc=4834338|issn=2045-7758|volume=6|issue=8}}</ref> The stems are triangular in section and bear slender [[leaf|leaves]] 3\u201310&nbsp;mm (1/8 to 1/2 inches) wide. The spikelets of the plant are distinctive, with a cluster of flat, oval seeds surrounded by four hanging, leaf-like [[bract]]s positioned 90 degrees from each other. They are 5 to 30&nbsp;mm (about 3/8 to 1 1/8 inches) long and linear to narrowly elliptic with pointed tips and 8 to 35 florets. The color varies from straw-colored to gold-brown. They can produce up to 2420 seeds per plant. The plant foliage is very tough and fibrous and is often mistaken for a [[grass]]. The roots are an extensive and complex system of fine, fibrous roots and scaly rhizomes with small, hard, spherical tubers and basal [[bulbs]] attached. \n\nThe tubers are 0.3 \u2013 1.9&nbsp;cm (1/8 to 3/4 inches) in diameter and the colors vary between yellow, brown, and black.<ref name=Factsheet>^ USGS Weeds in the West project: Status of introduced Plants in Southern Arizona Parks, Factsheets for Cyperus esculentus L., 2003, Tucson, Arizona</ref> One plant can produce several hundred to several thousand tubers during a single growing season. With cool temperatures, the foliage, roots, rhizomes, and basal bulbs die, but the tubers survive and resprout the following spring when soil temperatures remain above {{convert|6|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\":0\" /> They can resprout up to several years later.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stoller|first=E. W.|last2=Wax|first2=L. M.|date=1973-01-01|title=Yellow Nutsedge Shoot Emergence and Tuber Longevity|jstor=4042258|journal=Weed Science|volume=21|issue=1|pages=76\u201381|doi=10.1017/S004317450003174X}}</ref> When the tubers germinate, many rhizomes are initiated and end in a basal bulb near the soil surface. These basal bulbs initiate the stems and leaves above ground, and fibrous roots underground. ''C. esculentus'' is wind pollinated and requires [[cross pollination]] as it is self\u2013incompatible.\n\n==Invasiveness==\n''C. esculentus'' is a highly invasive species in [[Oceania]], [[Mexico]], some United States, and the [[Caribbean]], mainly by seed dispersion.<ref name=cabi/> It is readily transported internationally, and is adaptable to re-establish in varied climate and soil environments.<ref name=cabi/> In Japan, it is an exotic [[cloning|clonal]] weed favorable to establish in wet habitats.<ref name=cabi/>\n\n==Cultivation==\n[[File:Proc\u00e9s de cultiu de la xufa.jpeg|thumb|right|250px|Cultivation and growing of the ''xufa'' in the [[Land of Valencia]], file by [[Valencian Museum of Ethnology]]]]\n\n===Climate requirements===\n''Cyperus esculentus'' cultivation requires a mild climate. Low temperature, shade, and light intensity can inhibit flowering.<ref name=Factsheet/> Tuber initiation is inhibited by high levels of nitrogen, long photoperiods, and high levels of [[gibberellic acid]]. Flower initiation occurs under photoperiods of 12 to 14 hours per day.\n\n===Soil requirements===\nTubers can develop in soil depths  around 30&nbsp;cm (1-foot), but most occur in the top or upper part. They tolerate many adverse soil conditions including periods of drought and flooding and survive soil temperatures around {{convert|-5|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}. They grow best on sandy, moist soils at a pH between 5.0 \u2013 7.5.<ref name=Factsheet/> The densest populations of ''C. esculentus'' are often found in low-lying wetlands.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ross|first1=Merrill A.|last2=Lembi|first2=Carole A.|title=Applied Weed Science|publisher=Prentice Hall|edition=3|year=2008|page=322|isbn=978-0135028148}}</ref> They do not tolerate salinity.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\n==Agronomy==\n\n===Cultivation===\nPlanting is normally done on flat soils where ridges to favour the coming irrigations have previously been done. The separation between ridges is approximately {{convert|60|cm|ft|abbr=on}} and seeds are planted manually. Distances between seeds may vary from {{convert|15|to|20|cm|in|round=0.5|abbr=on}} and seeding depth is around {{convert|8|cm|in|frac=2|abbr=on}}. A typical seeding rate for chufa is about 120&nbsp;kg of tubers/ha (107&nbsp;lbs/acre).<ref>N. Pascual-Seva, et al., ''Furrow-irrigated chufa crops in Valencia (Spain)'' Spanish Journal of Agricultural Research 2013 11(1), 258-267.  http://revistas.inia.es/index.php/sjar/article/view/3385/1803</ref>\n\nThey are planted between April and May and must be irrigated every week until they are harvested in November and December. Tubers develop about 6 \u2013 8 weeks after seedling emergence and grow quickly during July and August. The maturing is around 90 \u2013 110 days. The average yield can approach between 10 and 19 t/ha.<ref>Pascual-Seva, N., San Bautista, A., L\u00f3pez Galarza, S., Maroto, J.V. and Pascual, B. 2012. Yield and Irrigation Water Use Efficiency for Ridge - and Bed - cultivated Chufa (''Cyperus Esculentus'' L. var. ''Sativus Boeck''). Acta Hort. (ISHS) 936:125-132</ref><ref>Reid WS, Hergert GB, Fagan WE, 1972. Development of a Prototype mechanical Harvester for Chufa (''Cyperus esculentus'' L. var ''sativus Boek''). Canadian Agricultural Engineering 14.</ref>\n\n===Harvest and drying process===\nHarvest usually occurs in November or December and the leaves are scorched during the harvest. With a combine harvester, the tiger nut is pulled out of the ground. Immediately after harvesting, the tiger nuts are washed with water in order to remove sand and small stones. The drying occurs usually in the sun and can take up to three months.<ref name=month>Tigernuts Traders, S.L., ''Tigernuts Oil'', 2012, http://www.tigernut.com</ref> The temperatures and humidity levels have to be monitored very carefully during this period. The tiger nuts have to be turned every day to ensure uniform drying. The drying process ensures a longer shelf life. This prevents rot or other bacterial infections, securing quality and high nutrition levels.\nDisadvantages in the drying process are shrinkage, skin wrinkles and hard nut texture.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n===Storage===\nTiger nut loses a considerable amount of water during drying and storage. The starch content of the tiger nut tubers decreases and the reducing sugar (invert sugar) content increases during storage.<ref>{{cite journal|title= Physical and chemical properties of chufa (Cyperus esculentus L) tubers grown in the \u00c7ukurova region of Turkey |doi=10.1002/jsfa.1091 | volume=82 |issue= 6|journal=Journal of the Science of Food and Agriculture |pages=625\u2013631|year= 2002|last1= Co\u015fkuner|first1= Yal\u00e7\u0131n|last2= Ercan|first2= Recai|last3= Karababa|first3= Er\u015fan|last4= Nazl\u0131can|first4= Ahmet Nedim}}</ref> Tiger nut can be stored dry and rehydrated by soaking without losing the crisp texture. Soaking is often done overnight. Dried tiger nuts have a hard texture and soaking is indispensable to render them edible with ease and to ensure acceptable sensory quality.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\nAccording to the ''Consejo Regulador de Chufa de Valencia'' (Regulating Council for Valencia's Tiger Nuts),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chufadevalencia.org/ |title=''Consejo Regulador de Chufa de Valencia'' |publisher=Chufadevalencia.org |date=2002-12-31 |accessdate=2012-06-05}}</ref> the nutritional composition/100 ml of the Spanish beverage horchata de chufas is as follows: energy content around 66 kcal, [[protein]]s around 0.5 g, [[carbohydrate]]s over 10 g with [[starch]] at least 1.9 g, [[fat]]s at least 2 g.\n\n==Uses==\nDried tiger nut has a smooth, tender, sweet, and nutty taste. It can be consumed raw, roasted, dried, baked or as tiger nut milk or oil.\n\n===Food===\n\n[[File:Cyperus esculentus MS 4388.jpg|thumb|right|Dried tubers sold at the market of [[Banfora]], [[Burkina Faso]].]]\n\nThe tubers are [[Eating|edible]], with a slightly sweet, nutty flavour, compared to the more bitter-tasting tuber of the related ''[[Cyperus rotundus]]'' (purple nutsedge). They are quite hard and are generally soaked in water before they can be eaten, making them much softer and giving them a better texture. They are a popular snack in West Africa.\n\nThey have various uses, such as [[horchata]], a nonalcoholic beverage of milky appearance derived from the tubers of the tiger nut plant mixed with sugar and water, and commonly consumed in Spain.<ref name=\"soto\">{{cite journal | last=Rosell\u00f3-Soto | first=Elena | last2=Poojary | first2=Mahesha M. | last3=Barba | first3=Francisco J. | last4=Koubaa | first4=Mohamed | last5=Lorenzo | first5=Jose M. | last6=Ma\u00f1es | first6=Jordi | last7=Molt\u00f3 | first7=Juan Carlos | title=Thermal and non-thermal preservation techniques of tiger nuts' beverage \"horchata de chufa\". Implications for food safety, nutritional and quality properties | journal=Food Research International  | volume=105 | year=2018 | issn=0963-9969 | pmid=29433293 | doi=10.1016/j.foodres.2017.12.014 | pages=945\u2013951}}</ref>\n\nFlour of roasted tiger nut is sometimes added to biscuits and other bakery products as well as in making oil, soap, and starch extracts. It is also used for the production of nougat, jam, beer, and as a flavoring agent in ice cream and in the preparation of [[kunnu]] (a local beverage in Nigeria).{{Citation needed|date=December 2019|reason=removed citation to predatory publisher content}}  Kunnu is a nonalcoholic beverage prepared mainly from cereals (such as millet or sorghum) by heating and mixing with spices (dandelion, alligator pepper, ginger, licorice) and sugar. To make up for the poor nutritional value of kunnu prepared from cereals, tiger nut was found to be a good substitute for cereal grains. Tiger nut oil can be used naturally with salads or for deep frying. It is considered to be a high quality oil. Tiger nut \u201cmilk\u201d has been tried as an alternative source of milk in fermented products, such as yogurt production, and other fermented products common in some African countries and can thus be useful replacing [[milk]] in the diet of people intolerant to [[lactose]] to a certain extent.<ref name=tiger />\n\n===Nutrition===\nDespite its name, tiger nutsedge is a tuber. However, its chemical composition shares characteristics with tubers and with nuts. This tuber is rich in energy content (starch, fat, sugar, and protein), and [[dietary mineral]]s (mainly [[phosphorus]] and [[potassium]]). The oil of the tuber was found to contain 18% saturated ([[palmitic acid]] and [[stearic acid]]) and 82% unsaturated ([[oleic acid]] and [[linoleic acid]]) [[fatty acid]]s.<ref name=zhang>{{cite journal|title= Yellow nut-sedge tuber oil as a fuel |doi=10.1016/0926-6690(96)89446-5 | volume=5 |issue= 3|journal=Industrial Crops and Products |pages=177\u2013181|year= 1996|last1= Zhang|first1= He Yuan|last2= Hanna|first2= Milford A|last3= Ali|first3= Yusuf|last4= Nan|first4= Lu}}</ref>\n\n===Oil===\nSince the tubers of ''C. esculentus'' contain 20-36% oil, it has been suggested as potential oil crop for the production of [[biodiesel]].<ref name=zhang/> One study found that chufa produced 1.5 metric tonnes of oil per hectare (174 gallons/acre) based on a tuber yield of 5.67 t/ha and an oil content of 26.4%.<ref name=\"sedge\">{{cite journal | last=Makareviciene | first=Violeta | last2=Gumbyte | first2=Milda | last3=Yunik | first3=Anatolii | last4=Kalenska | first4=Svitlana | last5=Kalenskii | first5=Viktor | last6=Rachmetov | first6=Dzhamal | last7=Sendzikiene | first7=Egle | title=Opportunities for the use of chufa sedge in biodiesel production | journal=Industrial Crops and Products | volume=50 | year=2013 | issn=0926-6690 | doi=10.1016/j.indcrop.2013.08.036 | pages=633\u2013637}}</ref> A similar 6-year study found tuber yields ranging from 4.02 to 6.75 t/ha, with an average oil content of 26.5% and an average oil yield of 1.47 t/ha.<ref>Bilali et al., \"Exploring Serbian consumers\u2019 attitude toward ethical values of organic, fair-trade and typical/traditional products\" The Fifth International Scientific Conference, Rural Development 2011, Proceedings, Volume 5, Book 1, p. 337.</ref>\n\n===Fishing bait===\nThe boiled nuts are used in the UK as a bait for [[Common carp|carp]]. The nuts have to be prepared in a prescribed manner to prevent harm to the fish. The nuts are soaked in water for 24 hours, and then boiled for 20 minutes or longer until fully expanded. Some anglers then leave the boiled nuts to ferment for 24\u201348 hours, which can enhance their effectiveness. If the nuts are not properly prepared, they can be  toxic to carp. This was originally thought to have been the cause of death of [[Benson (fish)|Benson]], a large, well-known female carp weighing {{Convert|54|lb|kg|abbr=on}} found floating dead in a fishing lake, with a bag of unprepared tiger nuts lying nearby, empty, on the bank. An examination of the fish by a [[taxidermist]] concluded tiger nut poisoning was not the cause of death, but rather the fish had died naturally.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bailey |first=John |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB125051804649836945 |title=The extraordinary life and suspicious death of Benson the giant carp |publisher=The Guardian |date=5 August 2009 |accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Compatibility with other crops==\n[[File:Cyperus esculentus NRCS-1.jpg|thumb|160px|The seed head of a ''Cyperus esculentus'' plant]]\n''C. esculentus'' is extremely difficult to remove completely once established. This is due to the plant having a stratified and layered root system, with tubers and roots being interconnected to a depth of 36&nbsp;cm or more.<ref name=Factsheet/> The tubers are connected by fragile roots that are prone to snapping when pulled, making the root system difficult to remove intact. Intermediate rhizomes can potentially reach a length of 60&nbsp;cm. The plant can quickly regenerate if a single tuber is left in place. By competing for light, water and nutrients it can reduce the vigour of neighbouring plants. It can develop into a dense colony. Patch boundaries can increase by more than one meter per year. Tubers and seed disperse with agricultural activities, soil movement or by water and wind. They are often known as a contaminant in crop seeds. When plants are small they are hard to distinguish from other weeds such as ''[[Dactylis glomerata]]'' and ''[[Elytrigia repens]]''. Thus it is hard to discover in an early stage and therefore hard to counteract. Once it is detected, mechanical removal, hand removal, grazing, damping, and herbicides can be used to inhibit ''C. esculentus''.\n\n===Similar native or non-native species that can confuse identification===\n* [[Sedges]] (''Cyperus'') have grass-like leaves and resemble each other in the appearance. They can mainly be distinguished from grasses by their triangular stems.\n* Purple nutsedge (''[[Cyperus rotundus|C. rotundus]]'') is another weedy sedge that is similar to the yellow nutsedge (''C. esculentus''). These two sedges are difficult to distinguish from each other and can be found growing on the same site. Some differences are the purple spikelets and the tubers formed by ''C. rotundus'' are often multiple instead of just one at the tip. In addition the tubers have a bitter taste instead of the mild almond-like flavour of ''C. esculentus''.<ref name=Factsheet/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{WestAfricanPlants|Cyperus esculentus}}\n{{Commons category}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q1165724}}\n\n[[Category:Flora of North America]]\n[[Category:Flora of Europe]]\n[[Category:Flora of Asia]]\n[[Category:Flora of Africa]]\n[[Category:Flora of South America]]\n[[Category:Flora of the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:Edible nuts and seeds]]\n[[Category:Cyperus|esculentus]]\n[[Category:Valencian Community]]\n[[Category:Root vegetables]]\n[[Category:Plants described in 1753]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyperus_esculentus"}
{"title_page": "Kenneth Copeland", "text_new": "{{short description|American televangelist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kenneth Copeland\n| residence          = [[Fort Worth, Texas]], U.S.\n| other_names        = \n| image              = File:Kenneth Copeland 2011.jpg\n| caption            = Kenneth Copeland in 2011\n| birth_name         = Kenneth Max Copeland\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1936|12|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lubbock, Texas]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| known              = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Author|speaker|pastor| demon}}\n| net_worth          = {{nowrap| [[US$]]760 million<ref name=\"Beliefnet profile\">{{cite web|title=8 Richest Pastors in America|url=https://www.beliefnet.com/faiths/christianity/8-richest-pastors-in-america.aspx?p=2|website=beliefnet|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> }} (October 2018)\n| salary             = \n| term               = \n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| predecessor        = \n| years active       = 1967-present\n| successor          = \n| influences         = [[Kenneth Hagan|Kenneth Hagan]]\n| boards             = \n| movement           = [[Word of Faith]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Ivy Bodiford|1955|1958}}<br /> {{marriage|Cynthia Davis |1958|1961}}<br /> {{marriage|Gloria Neece|1963}}\n| partner            = \n| children           = 3\n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| website            = {{URL|http://www.kcm.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| height             = \n| weight             = \n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Max Copeland''' (born December 6, 1936) is an American [[Televangelism|televangelist]], and demon, author associated with the [[Charismatic Movement]]. He runs the [[#Kenneth Copeland Ministries|Kenneth Copeland Ministries]] based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]].\n\nHe has been identified as preaching the [[Prosperity theology|prosperity gospel]]. As part of his evangelism, he calls for donations to his church, with the suggestion that parishioners will get a \"hundredfold\" return on their investment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2017/9/1/15951874/prosperity-gospel-explained-why-joel-osteen-believes-prayer-can-make-you-rich-trump|title=The prosperity gospel, explained: Why Joel Osteen believes that prayer can make you rich|last=Burton|first=Tara Isabella|date=2017-09-01|website=Vox|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> He has stirred controversy over his use of donations to finance mansions, private jets, an [[Kenneth Copeland Airport|airport]] and other lavish purchases.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Goodstein|first=Laurie|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/16/us/16gospel.html|title=Believers Invest in the Gospel of Getting Rich|date=2009-08-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/|title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019|date=2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|the pandemic of COVID-19]] in 2020, Copeland gained national attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. He repeatedly claimed that the pandemic had ended or would soon end, that he could heal followers of it, and that his followers should continue paying tithes if they lost their jobs in the economic crisis that the pandemic caused.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nKenneth Max Copeland was born in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]], [[Texas]], to Aubrey Wayne and Vinita Pearl (n\u00e9e Owens) Copeland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ancestrylibrary.com/interactive/8781/TXBTH_1936_000208e?pid=2675215|title=Texas Birth Index, 1903-1997|website=www.ancestrylibrary.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> He was raised in [[West Texas]] near a [[United States Army Air Forces]] [[List of United States Army airfields|airfield]], which inspired him to become a [[aviator|pilot.]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |title=Kenneth Copeland |publisher=biographyministries.com |year=2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081016102647/http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |archivedate=October 16, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/3275378|title=AP IMPACT: Relatives of televangelist prosper|last=Gorski|first=Eric|date=2008-07-27|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref>\n\nCopeland married Ivy Bodiford in October 1955 and became the parents of Terri Copeland Pearsons;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us/recorder/eagleweb/viewDoc.jsp?node=DOCCM-120611|title=Lubbock County Marriage Certificate|website=erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> they divorced in 1958. Kenneth married Gloria (n\u00e9e Neece) on April 13, 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kennethcopelandblog.com/2010/08/01/kenneth-and-gloria-copeland-the-untold-story/|title=Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, The Untold Story|publisher=KennethCopelandBlog.com |date=August 1, 2010 |accessdate=March 7, 2016}}</ref> They are the parents of John Copeland and Kellie Copeland. Gloria co-hosts the ministry's flagship broadcast, \"The Believer's Voice of Victory,\" alongside her husband. Kellie preaches throughout the United States, as does Terri, who also preaches at Eagle Mountain International Church, which is pastored by her husband, George Pearsons.\n\nPrior to becoming a [[born again Christian]] in November 1962, Copeland was a recording artist on the [[Imperial Records]] label, having one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Top 40 hit (\"Pledge of Love\", which charted in the Top 40 on April 20, 1957, stayed on the charts for 15 weeks, and peaked at #17).<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Billboard_Book_of_Top_40_Hits.html?id=drgq4g0rmVsC|title=The Billboard Book of Top 40 Hits|last=Whitburn|first=Joel|date=2000|publisher=Billboard Books|year=|isbn=9780823076901|location=|pages=151}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his conversion, Copeland devoted his life to the gospel and ministry work.<ref>Kenneth Copeland, \"The Word in My life...\", Kenneth Copeland Ministries Catalog (Fort Worth: Kenneth Copeland Ministries, n.d.), 3.</ref> In the fall of 1967, he enrolled in [[Oral Roberts University]], where he soon became pilot and chauffeur to [[Oral Roberts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|title=ORU alumni|accessdate=April 16, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210080448/http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|archivedate=February 10, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland sat on the evangelical executive advisory board that Donald Trump assembled during his campaign for the presidency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharman |first=Jon |date=February 6, 2018 |title=Trump adviser urges followers to 'inoculate yourself with the word of God' against flu |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/gloria-copeland-trump-adviser-flu-shot-jesus-god-christian-evangelical-healing-miracle-a8197801.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Appointment to the board did not require endorsement of his bid for presidency, <ref>{{cite news |last=Wing |first=Nick |date=June 21, 2016 |title=Donald Trump\u2019s New Evangelical Adviser Was Sure God Had Chosen Ted Cruz To Be President |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/donald-trump-kenneth-copeland_n_5769880de4b065534f47fb24 |work=HuffPost |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> and Copeland clarified that he did not endorse Trump at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |last2=Eekhoff Zylstra |first2=Sarah  |date=June 22, 2016 |title=Who\u2019s Who of Trump\u2019s \u2018Tremendous\u2019 Faith Advisers |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707085329/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archivedate=July 7, 2016 |work=Christianity Today |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Before the 2016 election, Copeland said that Christians that did not vote for Trump would be guilty of murder, referring to the abortion policy of Hillary Clinton.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pulliam Bailey  |first=Sarah |date=October 11, 2016 |title=Televangelist: Christians who don\u2019t vote are \u2018going to be guilty of murder\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/11/televangelist-christians-who-dont-vote-are-going-to-be-guilty-of-murder/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> In an interview after a state dinner at the White House that Copeland attended, he said that Trump was \"led by the Spirit of God\", and that his most important legacy as president would be the appointments of conservative judges.<ref>{{cite news |last=Strang |first=Steve |date=2018 |title=Kenneth Copeland on Trump's State Dinner: 'It Was Like a Really Anointed Church Service' |url=https://www.charismamag.com/blogs/the-strang-report/38641-kenneth-copeland-on-trump-s-state-dinner-it-was-like-a-really-anointed-church-service |work=Charisma Magazine |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nCopeland has amassed significant wealth during his career, and has referred to himself as a \"very wealthy man\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\" /> News media have cited different numbers of his net worth, from $300 million<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\">{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=May 28, 2019 |title=\u2018I'm a very wealthy man,\u2019 says Kenneth Copeland; he couldn\u2019t help but buy jet from Tyler Perry |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/prosperity-preacher-kenneth-copeland-says-ministry-brought-122-million-people-jesus-christ.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> to $760 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Swaak |first=Taylor |date=February 21, 2018 |title=Billy Graham Net Worth: Evangelist Was One of the Richest Pastors in America |url=https://www.newsweek.com/billy-graham-net-worth-814750 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==Kenneth Copeland Ministries==\nKenneth Copeland and his wife Gloria Copeland run Kenneth Copeland Ministries (KCM), based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]]. The ministry's motto is \"[[Jesus is Lord]]\" from {{bibleverse-lb||Romans|10:9|KJV}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries - About Us |publisher=Kenneth Copeland Ministries |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606124545/http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=June 26, 2019}}</ref> He has claimed in an interview that the ministry has \"brought over 122 million people to the Lord Jesus Christ\".<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\" />\n\n===Television and other programming===\nFor decades, Copeland's ministry has held three-to-six-day conventions across the United States. The number of longer set conventions has waned in recent years, although KCM still holds an annual Believer's Convention in his hometown of [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], Texas, during the week of July 4. Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, along with ministry friends including some family members, also preach at other conventions and conferences throughout the world.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} These events stream live on Copeland's website, kcm.org, as well as being shown on Christian television stations such as [[God TV]] and the [[Daystar Television Network]]. Portions of recorded conferences are shown Sundays. The Monday through Friday television broadcasts feature a Copeland family member, either alone or with another minister, discussing subjects from the [[Bible]].\nMost of these episodes are available on BVOV.tv.  In July 2015, KCM launched the Believer's Voice of Victory Network on channel 265 of [[Dish TV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dish.com/business/downloads/dish-general-channel-lineup.pdf |title=dish general channel linup |publisher=dish |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Facilities===\nKenneth Copeland Ministries is located at 14355 Morris Dido Road, Fort Worth, TX 76192 on 33 acres (13 ha), a property valued at $554,160 in 2008 by Tarrant Appraisal District. The site includes the Eagle Mountain International Church, television and radio production facilities, warehouse and distribution facilities, residences for the Copeland family, and [[Kenneth Copeland Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2008-07-27-copeland-evangelist-finances_N.htm |title=Analysis: Copeland's religious empire benefits his family |publisher=USA Today |date=July 27, 2008 |accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref> Approximately 500 people are employed by KCM. John Copeland is the ministry's chief operating officer.\n\nKCM also owns a 1998 [[Cessna Citation II|Cessna 550 Citation Bravo]], which it received from a donor in October 2007 and is used for [[domestic flight]]s, and a 2005 [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]], which it uses for [[international flight]]s. It also is [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|restoring]] a 1962 [[Beechcraft Model 18|Beech H-18 Twin]], which the ministry plans to use for [[Disaster response|disaster relief efforts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flightaware.com/resources/airport/4T2|title=Kenneth Copeland Airport FBOs (Fort Worth, TX) [4T2] \u2708 FlightAware|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104010640/http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |url=http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |archivedate=2013-11-04 |title=FAQ: Why does Kenneth Copeland Ministries own private aircraft? What types of aircraft are they? Why don't Kenneth and Gloria fly on commercial airlines? |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |work=Believers Stand United}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2007, Copeland was accused of using his ministry's Citation X for personal vacations and friends.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\">{{cite news |title=Jet flight records spur Copeland ministry questions |url=http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |publisher=[[WFAA-TV]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=October 17, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907124947/http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |archivedate=September 7, 2007}}</ref> The Copelands' financial records are not publicly available, and a list of the board of directors is not accessible as these details are protected but known confidentially by the [[Internal Revenue Service]].<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> Responding to media questions, Copeland pointed to what he asserted was an accounting firm's declaration that all jet travel complies with federal tax laws.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> In December 2008, KCM's Citation Bravo was denied tax exemption after KCM refused to submit a standardized [[Texas Comptroller of Public Accounts|Texas Comptroller]] form that some county appraisal districts use to make determinations, which would have required making public the salary of all ministry staff.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.star-telegram.com/804/story/1078037.html |title=Televangelist's $3.6 million jet not tax-exempt, county says |publisher=[[Fort Worth Star Telegram]] |date=December 5, 2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}} - dead link</ref><ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\">{{cite news |title=A Victory for Church Freedom |date=March 11, 2010 |url=http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |work=Church Law Group |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104224501/http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |archive-date=November 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> KCM subsequently [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with the [[Tarrant Appraisal District]] in January 2009 and its petition to have the aircraft's tax-exempt status restored was granted in March 2010.<ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Darren |last=Barbee |title=Appraisal district sued over tax exemption for private jet |date=February 25, 2009 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram |pages=B07 Metro }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=TAD, Copeland ministry settle suit over tax-exempt jet |date=March 10, 2010 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram }}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland Ministries has taken advantage of a [[Federal Aviation Administration]] program that keeps flights private from tracking websites, and the ministry owns five such aircraft whose flights are kept private, including the [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]] noted above and a [[North American T-28 Trojan]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\">{{cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2010-04-08-blocked-flights-inside_N.htm|title=Televangelist, college boosters, Hooters on stealth fliers list - USATODAY.com|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> [[United States Senator]] [[Chuck Grassley]] has questioned some of the flights taken by these aircraft, including layovers in [[Maui]], [[Fiji]], and [[Honolulu]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/> The ministries say that the stopovers were for preaching or for allowing pilot rest.<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===2006 Angel Flight 44 Controversy===\nAccording to ''[[The Christian Post]]'', Kenneth Copeland Ministries was criticized in 2010 for failing to fly disaster relief missions to [[Haiti]] after allegedly promising an aviation relief assistance program called '''Angel Flight 44'''.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-blasted-for-unfulfilled-vows-43561/|title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland Blasted for 'Unfulfilled Promises'|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> The Angel Flight 44 ministry was announced by Kenneth Copeland Ministries in 2006 and the ministry attempted to raise money to fund it.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Richard Vermillion, co-author of a book on Angel Flight 44 commissioned by Kenneth Copeland Ministries, said that Copeland promised to form the aviation ministry but now believes it was never created.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> A spokesperson for Kenneth Copeland Ministries, Stephen Swisher, told ''The Christian Post'', \"This was not a specific promise with a time line attached\", and said that the money was spent on airplane repairs, and that the airplane was \"not in airworthy condition\" and had \"structural issues\".<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/>\n\n===2008 Mike Huckabee controversy===\nIn late November 2007, [[Mike Huckabee]], a [[Republican Party (United States) presidential primaries, 2008|2008 Republican presidential primary]] candidate, made six appearances on Copeland's daily television program ''[[Believer's Voice of Victory]]'', discussing \"Integrity of Character\".{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} Huckabee, an ordained Baptist minister, was appearing on Copeland's daily broadcast to promote his book, ''Character IS the Issue: How People with Integrity Can Revolutionize America''. Through the years, Copeland has invited many church pastors and evangelists to appear on his daily program to discuss their respective books.  Subsequently, in January 2008, the Huckabee campaign paid for use of Kenneth Copeland Ministries' facilities for a fundraiser.<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\">{{cite news |url=http://www2.arkansasonline.com/news/2008/jan/29/plate-passed-huckabee-ministry-site |title=Plate passed for Huckabee at ministry site |publisher=[[Arkansas Democrat-Gazette]] |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-17}}</ref> The fundraising at the church was criticized by the [[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)|Trinity Foundation]].<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\" />\n\nAs a result of the Huckabee appearances, Kenneth Copeland Ministries was one of six approached by the [[United States Senate inquiry into the tax-exempt status of religious organizations]]. The Copelands responded with a [[financial statement]] and created a website, ''Believers Stand United'', to help explain their perspective.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}<ref>The investigation found no evidence of the Copelands making personal profit from financial donations. {{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/40960871/ns/politics-capitol_hill/t/televangelists-escape-penalty-senate-inquiry/#.URiVeTsiGYV |title=Televangelists escape penalty in Senate inquiry |publisher=www.nbcnews.com |date=2011-07-01 |accessdate=2013-02-11 |author=Zoll, Rachel}}</ref>\n\n===2013 vaccination controversy===\nIn 2013, a [[Measles outbreaks in the 21st century#United States|measles outbreak]] (20 confirmed cases as of August 26) in [[Tarrant County]] was attributed in the press to [[Vaccine controversies|anti-vaccination]] sentiments expressed by members of the Copeland Ministries. The church denied making any such statements and urged members to get vaccinations, even offering free immunizations through the church itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/texas-measles-outbreak-linked-to-church-led-by-kenneth-copelands-daughter-infection-spread-to-congregation-staff-day-care-103057/|title=Texas Measles Outbreak Linked to Church Led by Kenneth Copeland's Daughter; Infection Spreads to Congregation, Staff, Day Care|website=www.christianpost.com|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref> Pastor Terri Copeland Pearsons, who is Kenneth Copeland's daughter, offered free vaccination clinics and advised those who did not attend one of the clinics to [[quarantine]] themselves at home for two weeks. In a statement on the church website, Pearsons said she was not against immunizations, but also raised concerns about them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/09/01/217746942/texas-megachurch-at-center-of-measles-outbreak|title=Texas Megachurch At Center Of Measles Outbreak|work=NPR.org|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>\"Some people think I am against immunizations, but that is not true\", the statement said. \"Vaccinations help cut the mortality rate enormously. I believe it is wrong to be against vaccinations. The [[MMR vaccine controversy|concerns]] we have had are primarily with very young children who have family history of [[autism]] and with bundling too many immunizations at one time. There is no indication of the [[Controversies in autism|autism connection]] with vaccinations in older children. Furthermore, the new [[MMR vaccine|MMR vaccination]] is without [[thimerosal]] (mercury), which has also been [[Thiomersal controversy|a concern]] to many.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/texas-church-epicenter-measles-outbreak/story?id=20071644|title=Texas Church at Epicenter of Measles Outbreak|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=2013-08-27|website=ABC News|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n===2015 ''Last Week Tonight'' criticism===\nKenneth Copeland and his wife, Gloria Copeland, were featured in a 2015 episode of ''[[Last Week Tonight with John Oliver]]'' that gained media attention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Last Week Tonight with John Oliver: Televangelists (HBO)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7y1xJAVZxXg|website=YouTube|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=16 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Comedian John Oliver takes on the prosperity gospel by becoming a televangelist|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2015/08/17/comedian-john-oliver-takes-on-the-prosperity-gospel-by-becoming-a-televangelist/|website=The Washington Post|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=John Oliver Becomes a Televangelist and Finally Starts His Own Church|url=http://time.com/3999933/john-oliver-televangelist-church-alst-week-tonight/|website=Time Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Marlow|title=John Oliver Exposes Shady Televangelists Fleecing Americans For Millions|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/08/17/john-oliver-exposes-shady-televangelists-fleecing-americans-for-millions.html|website=The Daily Beast|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref> Comedian [[John Oliver (comedian)|John Oliver]] criticized the Copelands for using tax laws to live in a $6.3 million mansion as the [[parsonage]] allowance for their home is not subject to income taxes,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Burnett|first1=John|title=Can A Television Network Be A Church? The IRS Says Yes|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/04/01/282496855/can-a-television-network-be-a-church-the-irs-says-yes|website=NPR|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=1 April 2014}}</ref> for using church donations to buy a $20 million jet that was used for trips to a ski resort and a private game ranch,<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate audit critical of TV preacher Kenneth Copeland|url=http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|website=WFAA|accessdate=18 August 2015|location=Dallas, Texas|date=7 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019235219/http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|archive-date=October 19, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and for promotion of healing through faith and skepticism of medicine, which Oliver highlighted with a video of Gloria Copeland saying that doctors give patients \"poison that will make you sicker\" and that the church is an alternative to medical treatment: \"Which do you want to do? Do you want to do that\", Copeland asked of the doctor's \"poison\" treatment, \"or do you want to sit here on a Saturday morning, hear the word of God, and let faith come into your heart and be healed?\"\n\n===Private jets===\nIn 2009, Copeland's $3.6 million jet was denied tax-exempt status, opening up a possible investigation into the church's expenses; Copeland failed to disclose the salaries of his directors. In 2008 the ministry stated it owned five airplanes, one of which is valued at $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tax-Exempt Status For Televangelist's Jet Denied|publisher=Americans United|url=https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120124428/https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|archive-date=January 20, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's ministry bought a multi-million [[Gulfstream V]] jet airplane,<ref name=CP-KC>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Acquires New Gulfstream V Jet, Seeks $19.5M for Upgrades and Maintenance|publisher=Christian Post|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-acquires-new-gulfstream-v-jet-seeks-19-5m-for-upgrades-and-maintenance-214408/}}</ref> and Copeland thanked his followers and Jesus for buying it when it was delivered at the Fort Worth airstrip, wearing a [[Flight jacket|pilot jacket]] and sunglasses.<ref name=D5286955>{{cite web|title='Jesus bought this': Delighted televangelist Kenneth Copeland giggles with glee as he unveils new $3million private jet paid for by donations from his followers|publisher=Daily Mail|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5286955/Prosperity-Preacher-Kenneth-Copeland-giggles-GV.html}}</ref> The jet was bought from filmmaker and businessman [[Tyler Perry]].<ref name=D5286955/><ref name=CP-KC/> Now,{{when?|reason=This should be a \"As of\" fact. Saying \"Now\" introduces ambiguity.|date=April 2020}} the church is asking another $17<ref name=D5286955/> or $19.5 million for the building of a hangar, upgrading of the runway, and maintenance.<ref name=CP-KC/>\n\nIn 2015, Kenneth Copeland, in a broadcast alongside fellow televangelist [[Jesse Duplantis]], defended the use of private jets as a necessary part of their ministry, comparing flying in a commercial plane to getting \"in long tube with a bunch of demons\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\">{{cite news |last=Brice-Saddler |first=Michael |date=June 4, 2019 |title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/ |work=The Washingot Post |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bote |first=Joshua |date=December 15, 2019 |title='None of your business': A televangelist defending his private jets goes viral |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/06/04/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-private-jets-inside-edition/1337549001/ |work=USA Today |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Calicchio |first=Dom  |title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland defends use of private jets in TV interview, denies calling people 'demons' |url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-use-of-private-jets-in-tv-interview-denies-calling-people-demons |work=Fox News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brito |first=Christopher |date=June 4, 2019 |title=Televangelist defends lavish lifestyle and use of private jets, calls it a \"biblical thing\" |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kenneth-copeland-televangelist-defends-lavish-lifestyle-and-use-of-private-jets-2019-06-04/ |work=CBS News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's and other televangelists' use of private jets and other lavish houses and vehicles has been criticized.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries Ups Being a Scumonaut by Bragging About New G5 Jet|publisher=Pulpit&Pen|url=http://pulpitandpen.org/2018/01/16/kenneth-copeland-ministries-ups-being-a-scumonaut-by-bragging-about-new-g5-jet/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Loves His New $36 Million Jet|publisher=Patheos|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324233307/http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|archive-date=March 24, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Televagelist thanks Jesus for $36M private jet he uses to avoid demons|publisher=The Maven|url=https://www.themaven.net/beingliberal/room/televagelist-thanks-jesus-for-36m-private-jet-he-uses-to-avoid-demons-sldtGWfs-kq7Qisw941q5w}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19===\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic of COVID-19]], Copeland repeatedly got attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. On March 11, 2020, Copeland claimed to heal viewers of his TV show of the disease, asking them to touch the television set as he prayed for them.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lemon |first=Jason |date=March 12, 2020 |title=Conservative Pastor Claims He 'Healed' Viewers of Coronavirus Through Their TV Screens |url=https://www.newsweek.com/conservative-pastor-claims-he-healed-viewers-coronavirus-through-their-tv-screens-1492044 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nAs many lost their jobs in the [[Coronavirus recession|economic crisis]] that the outbreak caused, Copeland told followers to continue paying tithes even if they lost their jobs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gagn\u00e9 |first=Andr\u00e9 |date=March 29, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Trump and religious right rely on faith, not science |url=https://theconversation.com/coronavirus-trump-and-religious-right-rely-on-faith-not-science-134508 |work=The Conversation |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIn a broadcast, Copeland called it a weak strain of the flu, and that fear of it was sin and putting faith in the devil. Copeland said that he did not agree with pastors that cancelled their services due to the coronavirus, saying \"I want you in my church. If we have to pass out thermometers. If we find one with a fever, let\u2019s get him healed right there. What if you do get it? Big deal!\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=March 13, 2020 |title=Kenneth Copeland calls coronavirus \u2018very weak strain of flu,\u2019 says healthy people shouldn\u2019t fear |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-calls-coronavirus-very-weak-strain-of-flu-healthy-people-shouldnt-fear.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jason |date=April 4, 202 |title=The rightwing Christian preachers in deep denial over Covid-19's danger |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/04/america-rightwing-christian-preachers-virus-hoax |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland has repeatedly said during the pandemic that it has ended or will soon end.<ref name=\"independent-corona\">{{cite news |last=Woodward |first=Alex |date=April 6, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Televangelist Kenneth Copeland \u2018blows wind of God\u2019 at Covid-19 to \u2018destroy\u2019 pandemic  |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/kenneth-copeland-blow-coronavirus-pray-sermon-trump-televangelist-a9448561.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> He said at one point that God told him that it would soon be over as Christians' prayers have overwhelmed it, and that the pandemic was brought to America by \"displays of hate\" towards president Donald Trump by critics, which had intereferred with \"divine protection\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Sommer |first=Will |date=March 23, 2020 |title=Trump\u2019s Megachurch Allies Promise COVID-19 Snake Oil and \u2018Miracles\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/trump-friendly-megachurch-pastors-push-bogus-coronavirus-cures |work=The Daily Beast |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> On March 29, 2020, in a televised sermon, Copeland \"executed judgement\" on COVID-19. He claimed that it was \"finished\" and \"over\" and that the US was now \"healed and well again\".<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> In another sermon shortly thereafter, Copeland claimed to destroy the virus with the \"wind of God\", saying \"I blow the wind of God on you. You are destroyed forever, and you\u2019ll never be back. Thank you, God. Let it happen. Cause it to happen.\"<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Selected KCM publications and recordings==\n*''Load Up Pocket Devotional: 31 Devotions to Revolutionize Your Future'' (Harrison House, July 2004) {{ISBN|1-57794-399-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577943990}}\n*''You Are Healed'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, July 1999) {{ISBN|0-88114-733-8}} {{ISBN|978-0881147339}}\n*''A Ceremony of Marriage'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-938458-15-9}} {{ISBN|978-0938458159}}\n*''Prayer: Your Foundation for Success'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57794-155-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941552}}\n*''Kenneth Copeland Reference Bible \u2013 Leather Bound'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-88114-296-4}} {{ISBN|978-0881142969}}\n*''Becoming Subject to the Authority of Jesus'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-88114-972-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881149722}}\n*''How to Discipline Your Flesh'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57562-116-9}} {{ISBN|978-1575621166}}\n*''From Faith to Faith: A Daily Guide to Victory'' (Harrison House, May 2000) {{ISBN|1-57794-225-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577942252}}\n*''Pursuit of His Presence: Daily Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-137-3}} {{ISBN|978-1577941378}}\n*''The Wake-up Call'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2002) {{ISBN|1-57562-792-2}} {{ISBN|978-1575627922}}\n*''Classic Redemption'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-938458-58-2}} {{ISBN|978-0938458586}}\n*''The Laws of Prosperity'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1995) {{ISBN|0-88114-952-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149524}}\n*''Prosperity: The Choice Is Yours'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1992) {{ISBN|0-88114-728-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881147285}}\n*''Healing Promises'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, August 1994) {{ISBN|0-88114-949-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149494}}\n*''Over the Edge: Youth Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-138-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941385}}\n*''Big Band Gospel'' (KCP Records, 2003)\n*''Racism in the Church. Kill the Root, Destroy the Tree'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2016) {{ISBN|978-1604633252}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)]]\n*[[Neo-charismatic churches]]\n*[[Charismatic movement]]\n*[[Word of Faith]]\n*[[Prosperity Gospel]]\n*[[Tony Palmer (bishop)]]\n*[[Ulf Ekman]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kcm.org/ Kenneth Copeland Ministries official site]\n*[http://emic.org Eagle Mountain International Church]\n*[http://bvov.tv Believer's Voice of Victory streaming site]\n*[http://believersstandunited.com Believers Stand United for Religious Freedom in America]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Copeland, Kenneth}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Pentecostal pastors]]\n[[Category:American television evangelists]]\n[[Category:American Charismatics]]\n[[Category:Imperial Records artists]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University people]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Worth, Texas]]\n[[Category:People from Lubbock, Texas]]\n[[Category:Pentecostal writers]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University alumni]]\n[[Category:American faith healers]]\n[[Category:Prosperity theologians]]\n[[Category:Pentecostals from Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas Republicans]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American televangelist}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kenneth Copeland\n| residence          = [[Fort Worth, Texas]], U.S.\n| other_names        = \n| image              = File:Kenneth Copeland 2011.jpg\n| caption            = Kenneth Copeland in 2011\n| birth_name         = Kenneth Max Copeland\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1936|12|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Lubbock, Texas]], U.S.\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| known              = \n| occupation         = {{hlist|Author|speaker|pastor|televangelist}}\n| net_worth          = {{nowrap| [[US$]]760 million<ref name=\"Beliefnet profile\">{{cite web|title=8 Richest Pastors in America|url=https://www.beliefnet.com/faiths/christianity/8-richest-pastors-in-america.aspx?p=2|website=beliefnet|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> }} (October 2018)\n| salary             = \n| term               = \n| nationality        = [[United States|American]]\n| predecessor        = \n| years active       = 1967-present\n| successor          = \n| influences         = [[Kenneth Hagan|Kenneth Hagan]]\n| boards             = \n| movement           = [[Word of Faith]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Ivy Bodiford|1955|1958}}<br /> {{marriage|Cynthia Davis |1958|1961}}<br /> {{marriage|Gloria Neece|1963}}\n| partner            = \n| children           = 3\n| parents            = \n| relations          = \n| website            = {{URL|http://www.kcm.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n| party              = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| height             = \n| weight             = \n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Max Copeland''' (born December 6, 1936) is an American [[Televangelism|televangelist]], and author associated with the [[Charismatic Movement]]. He runs the [[#Kenneth Copeland Ministries|Kenneth Copeland Ministries]] based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]].\n\nHe has been identified as preaching the [[Prosperity theology|prosperity gospel]]. As part of his evangelism, he calls for donations to his church, with the suggestion that parishioners will get a \"hundredfold\" return on their investment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2017/9/1/15951874/prosperity-gospel-explained-why-joel-osteen-believes-prayer-can-make-you-rich-trump|title=The prosperity gospel, explained: Why Joel Osteen believes that prayer can make you rich|last=Burton|first=Tara Isabella|date=2017-09-01|website=Vox|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref> He has stirred controversy over his use of donations to finance mansions, private jets, an [[Kenneth Copeland Airport|airport]] and other lavish purchases.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Goodstein|first=Laurie|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/16/us/16gospel.html|title=Believers Invest in the Gospel of Getting Rich|date=2009-08-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/|title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019|date=2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|the pandemic of COVID-19]] in 2020, Copeland gained national attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. He repeatedly claimed that the pandemic had ended or would soon end, that he could heal followers of it, and that his followers should continue paying tithes if they lost their jobs in the economic crisis that the pandemic caused.<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nKenneth Max Copeland was born in [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]], [[Texas]], to Aubrey Wayne and Vinita Pearl (n\u00e9e Owens) Copeland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ancestrylibrary.com/interactive/8781/TXBTH_1936_000208e?pid=2675215|title=Texas Birth Index, 1903-1997|website=www.ancestrylibrary.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> He was raised in [[West Texas]] near a [[United States Army Air Forces]] [[List of United States Army airfields|airfield]], which inspired him to become a [[aviator|pilot.]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |title=Kenneth Copeland |publisher=biographyministries.com |year=2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081016102647/http://www.biographyministries.com/kenneth-copeland.html |archivedate=October 16, 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://newsok.com/article/3275378|title=AP IMPACT: Relatives of televangelist prosper|last=Gorski|first=Eric|date=2008-07-27|work=NewsOK.com|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref>\n\nCopeland married Ivy Bodiford in October 1955 and became the parents of Terri Copeland Pearsons;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us/recorder/eagleweb/viewDoc.jsp?node=DOCCM-120611|title=Lubbock County Marriage Certificate|website=erecord.co.lubbock.tx.us|access-date=2018-04-18}}</ref> they divorced in 1958. Kenneth married Gloria (n\u00e9e Neece) on April 13, 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kennethcopelandblog.com/2010/08/01/kenneth-and-gloria-copeland-the-untold-story/|title=Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, The Untold Story|publisher=KennethCopelandBlog.com |date=August 1, 2010 |accessdate=March 7, 2016}}</ref> They are the parents of John Copeland and Kellie Copeland. Gloria co-hosts the ministry's flagship broadcast, \"The Believer's Voice of Victory,\" alongside her husband. Kellie preaches throughout the United States, as does Terri, who also preaches at Eagle Mountain International Church, which is pastored by her husband, George Pearsons.\n\nPrior to becoming a [[born again Christian]] in November 1962, Copeland was a recording artist on the [[Imperial Records]] label, having one ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Top 40 hit (\"Pledge of Love\", which charted in the Top 40 on April 20, 1957, stayed on the charts for 15 weeks, and peaked at #17).<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Billboard_Book_of_Top_40_Hits.html?id=drgq4g0rmVsC|title=The Billboard Book of Top 40 Hits|last=Whitburn|first=Joel|date=2000|publisher=Billboard Books|year=|isbn=9780823076901|location=|pages=151}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his conversion, Copeland devoted his life to the gospel and ministry work.<ref>Kenneth Copeland, \"The Word in My life...\", Kenneth Copeland Ministries Catalog (Fort Worth: Kenneth Copeland Ministries, n.d.), 3.</ref> In the fall of 1967, he enrolled in [[Oral Roberts University]], where he soon became pilot and chauffeur to [[Oral Roberts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|title=ORU alumni|accessdate=April 16, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090210080448/http://www.oru.edu/alumni/excell/spring06/feature1.html|archivedate=February 10, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland sat on the evangelical executive advisory board that Donald Trump assembled during his campaign for the presidency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharman |first=Jon |date=February 6, 2018 |title=Trump adviser urges followers to 'inoculate yourself with the word of God' against flu |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/gloria-copeland-trump-adviser-flu-shot-jesus-god-christian-evangelical-healing-miracle-a8197801.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Appointment to the board did not require endorsement of his bid for presidency, <ref>{{cite news |last=Wing |first=Nick |date=June 21, 2016 |title=Donald Trump\u2019s New Evangelical Adviser Was Sure God Had Chosen Ted Cruz To Be President |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/donald-trump-kenneth-copeland_n_5769880de4b065534f47fb24 |work=HuffPost |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> and Copeland clarified that he did not endorse Trump at the time.<ref>{{cite news |last=Shellnutt |first=Kate |last2=Eekhoff Zylstra |first2=Sarah  |date=June 22, 2016 |title=Who\u2019s Who of Trump\u2019s \u2018Tremendous\u2019 Faith Advisers |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160707085329/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2016/june-web-only/whos-who-of-trumps-tremendous-faith-advisors.html |archivedate=July 7, 2016 |work=Christianity Today |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> Before the 2016 election, Copeland said that Christians that did not vote for Trump would be guilty of murder, referring to the abortion policy of Hillary Clinton.<ref>{{cite news |last=Pulliam Bailey  |first=Sarah |date=October 11, 2016 |title=Televangelist: Christians who don\u2019t vote are \u2018going to be guilty of murder\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2016/10/11/televangelist-christians-who-dont-vote-are-going-to-be-guilty-of-murder/ |work=The Washington Post |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref> In an interview after a state dinner at the White House that Copeland attended, he said that Trump was \"led by the Spirit of God\", and that his most important legacy as president would be the appointments of conservative judges.<ref>{{cite news |last=Strang |first=Steve |date=2018 |title=Kenneth Copeland on Trump's State Dinner: 'It Was Like a Really Anointed Church Service' |url=https://www.charismamag.com/blogs/the-strang-report/38641-kenneth-copeland-on-trump-s-state-dinner-it-was-like-a-really-anointed-church-service |work=Charisma Magazine |access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nCopeland has amassed significant wealth during his career, and has referred to himself as a \"very wealthy man\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\" /> News media have cited different numbers of his net worth, from $300 million<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\">{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=May 28, 2019 |title=\u2018I'm a very wealthy man,\u2019 says Kenneth Copeland; he couldn\u2019t help but buy jet from Tyler Perry |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/prosperity-preacher-kenneth-copeland-says-ministry-brought-122-million-people-jesus-christ.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> to $760 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Swaak |first=Taylor |date=February 21, 2018 |title=Billy Graham Net Worth: Evangelist Was One of the Richest Pastors in America |url=https://www.newsweek.com/billy-graham-net-worth-814750 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==Kenneth Copeland Ministries==\nKenneth Copeland and his wife Gloria Copeland run Kenneth Copeland Ministries (KCM), based in [[Tarrant County]], [[Texas]]. The ministry's motto is \"[[Jesus is Lord]]\" from {{bibleverse-lb||Romans|10:9|KJV}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries - About Us |publisher=Kenneth Copeland Ministries |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606124545/http://kcm.org/about-us-0 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=June 26, 2019}}</ref> He has claimed in an interview that the ministry has \"brought over 122 million people to the Lord Jesus Christ\".<ref name=\"christianpost-very-wealthy-man\" />\n\n===Television and other programming===\nFor decades, Copeland's ministry has held three-to-six-day conventions across the United States. The number of longer set conventions has waned in recent years, although KCM still holds an annual Believer's Convention in his hometown of [[Fort Worth, Texas|Fort Worth]], Texas, during the week of July 4. Kenneth and Gloria Copeland, along with ministry friends including some family members, also preach at other conventions and conferences throughout the world.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} These events stream live on Copeland's website, kcm.org, as well as being shown on Christian television stations such as [[God TV]] and the [[Daystar Television Network]]. Portions of recorded conferences are shown Sundays. The Monday through Friday television broadcasts feature a Copeland family member, either alone or with another minister, discussing subjects from the [[Bible]].\nMost of these episodes are available on BVOV.tv.  In July 2015, KCM launched the Believer's Voice of Victory Network on channel 265 of [[Dish TV]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dish.com/business/downloads/dish-general-channel-lineup.pdf |title=dish general channel linup |publisher=dish |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Facilities===\nKenneth Copeland Ministries is located at 14355 Morris Dido Road, Fort Worth, TX 76192 on 33 acres (13 ha), a property valued at $554,160 in 2008 by Tarrant Appraisal District. The site includes the Eagle Mountain International Church, television and radio production facilities, warehouse and distribution facilities, residences for the Copeland family, and [[Kenneth Copeland Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/religion/2008-07-27-copeland-evangelist-finances_N.htm |title=Analysis: Copeland's religious empire benefits his family |publisher=USA Today |date=July 27, 2008 |accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref> Approximately 500 people are employed by KCM. John Copeland is the ministry's chief operating officer.\n\nKCM also owns a 1998 [[Cessna Citation II|Cessna 550 Citation Bravo]], which it received from a donor in October 2007 and is used for [[domestic flight]]s, and a 2005 [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]], which it uses for [[international flight]]s. It also is [[Maintenance, repair, and operations|restoring]] a 1962 [[Beechcraft Model 18|Beech H-18 Twin]], which the ministry plans to use for [[Disaster response|disaster relief efforts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://flightaware.com/resources/airport/4T2|title=Kenneth Copeland Airport FBOs (Fort Worth, TX) [4T2] \u2708 FlightAware|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104010640/http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |url=http://www.believersstandunited.com/faq/ |archivedate=2013-11-04 |title=FAQ: Why does Kenneth Copeland Ministries own private aircraft? What types of aircraft are they? Why don't Kenneth and Gloria fly on commercial airlines? |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |work=Believers Stand United}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2007, Copeland was accused of using his ministry's Citation X for personal vacations and friends.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\">{{cite news |title=Jet flight records spur Copeland ministry questions |url=http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |publisher=[[WFAA-TV]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=October 17, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907124947/http://www.wfaa.com/sharedcontent/dws/wfaa/latestnews/stories/wfaa070228_mo_churchjet.87be631.html |archivedate=September 7, 2007}}</ref> The Copelands' financial records are not publicly available, and a list of the board of directors is not accessible as these details are protected but known confidentially by the [[Internal Revenue Service]].<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> Responding to media questions, Copeland pointed to what he asserted was an accounting firm's declaration that all jet travel complies with federal tax laws.<ref name=\"Jetrecords\" /> In December 2008, KCM's Citation Bravo was denied tax exemption after KCM refused to submit a standardized [[Texas Comptroller of Public Accounts|Texas Comptroller]] form that some county appraisal districts use to make determinations, which would have required making public the salary of all ministry staff.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.star-telegram.com/804/story/1078037.html |title=Televangelist's $3.6 million jet not tax-exempt, county says |publisher=[[Fort Worth Star Telegram]] |date=December 5, 2008 |accessdate=December 17, 2008}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}} - dead link</ref><ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\">{{cite news |title=A Victory for Church Freedom |date=March 11, 2010 |url=http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |work=Church Law Group |accessdate=May 14, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104224501/http://churchlawgroup.com/blog/uncategorized/a-victory-for-church-freedom/ |archive-date=November 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> KCM subsequently [[lawsuit|filed suit]] with the [[Tarrant Appraisal District]] in January 2009 and its petition to have the aircraft's tax-exempt status restored was granted in March 2010.<ref name=\"CLG 2010-03-11\" /><ref>{{cite news |first=Darren |last=Barbee |title=Appraisal district sued over tax exemption for private jet |date=February 25, 2009 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram |pages=B07 Metro }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=TAD, Copeland ministry settle suit over tax-exempt jet |date=March 10, 2010 |work=Fort Worth Star-Telegram }}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland Ministries has taken advantage of a [[Federal Aviation Administration]] program that keeps flights private from tracking websites, and the ministry owns five such aircraft whose flights are kept private, including the [[Cessna Citation X|Cessna 750 Citation X]] noted above and a [[North American T-28 Trojan]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\">{{cite web|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/washington/2010-04-08-blocked-flights-inside_N.htm|title=Televangelist, college boosters, Hooters on stealth fliers list - USATODAY.com|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> [[United States Senator]] [[Chuck Grassley]] has questioned some of the flights taken by these aircraft, including layovers in [[Maui]], [[Fiji]], and [[Honolulu]].<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/> The ministries say that the stopovers were for preaching or for allowing pilot rest.<ref name=\"usatoday30.usatoday.com\"/>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n===2006 Angel Flight 44 Controversy===\nAccording to ''[[The Christian Post]]'', Kenneth Copeland Ministries was criticized in 2010 for failing to fly disaster relief missions to [[Haiti]] after allegedly promising an aviation relief assistance program called '''Angel Flight 44'''.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-blasted-for-unfulfilled-vows-43561/|title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland Blasted for 'Unfulfilled Promises'|publisher=|accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> The Angel Flight 44 ministry was announced by Kenneth Copeland Ministries in 2006 and the ministry attempted to raise money to fund it.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> Richard Vermillion, co-author of a book on Angel Flight 44 commissioned by Kenneth Copeland Ministries, said that Copeland promised to form the aviation ministry but now believes it was never created.<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/> A spokesperson for Kenneth Copeland Ministries, Stephen Swisher, told ''The Christian Post'', \"This was not a specific promise with a time line attached\", and said that the money was spent on airplane repairs, and that the airplane was \"not in airworthy condition\" and had \"structural issues\".<ref name=\"christianpost.com\"/>\n\n===2008 Mike Huckabee controversy===\nIn late November 2007, [[Mike Huckabee]], a [[Republican Party (United States) presidential primaries, 2008|2008 Republican presidential primary]] candidate, made six appearances on Copeland's daily television program ''[[Believer's Voice of Victory]]'', discussing \"Integrity of Character\".{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} Huckabee, an ordained Baptist minister, was appearing on Copeland's daily broadcast to promote his book, ''Character IS the Issue: How People with Integrity Can Revolutionize America''. Through the years, Copeland has invited many church pastors and evangelists to appear on his daily program to discuss their respective books.  Subsequently, in January 2008, the Huckabee campaign paid for use of Kenneth Copeland Ministries' facilities for a fundraiser.<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\">{{cite news |url=http://www2.arkansasonline.com/news/2008/jan/29/plate-passed-huckabee-ministry-site |title=Plate passed for Huckabee at ministry site |publisher=[[Arkansas Democrat-Gazette]] |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-17}}</ref> The fundraising at the church was criticized by the [[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)|Trinity Foundation]].<ref name=\"2008-01-29 ADG\" />\n\nAs a result of the Huckabee appearances, Kenneth Copeland Ministries was one of six approached by the [[United States Senate inquiry into the tax-exempt status of religious organizations]]. The Copelands responded with a [[financial statement]] and created a website, ''Believers Stand United'', to help explain their perspective.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}}<ref>The investigation found no evidence of the Copelands making personal profit from financial donations. {{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/40960871/ns/politics-capitol_hill/t/televangelists-escape-penalty-senate-inquiry/#.URiVeTsiGYV |title=Televangelists escape penalty in Senate inquiry |publisher=www.nbcnews.com |date=2011-07-01 |accessdate=2013-02-11 |author=Zoll, Rachel}}</ref>\n\n===2013 vaccination controversy===\nIn 2013, a [[Measles outbreaks in the 21st century#United States|measles outbreak]] (20 confirmed cases as of August 26) in [[Tarrant County]] was attributed in the press to [[Vaccine controversies|anti-vaccination]] sentiments expressed by members of the Copeland Ministries. The church denied making any such statements and urged members to get vaccinations, even offering free immunizations through the church itself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/texas-measles-outbreak-linked-to-church-led-by-kenneth-copelands-daughter-infection-spread-to-congregation-staff-day-care-103057/|title=Texas Measles Outbreak Linked to Church Led by Kenneth Copeland's Daughter; Infection Spreads to Congregation, Staff, Day Care|website=www.christianpost.com|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref> Pastor Terri Copeland Pearsons, who is Kenneth Copeland's daughter, offered free vaccination clinics and advised those who did not attend one of the clinics to [[quarantine]] themselves at home for two weeks. In a statement on the church website, Pearsons said she was not against immunizations, but also raised concerns about them.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2013/09/01/217746942/texas-megachurch-at-center-of-measles-outbreak|title=Texas Megachurch At Center Of Measles Outbreak|work=NPR.org|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>\"Some people think I am against immunizations, but that is not true\", the statement said. \"Vaccinations help cut the mortality rate enormously. I believe it is wrong to be against vaccinations. The [[MMR vaccine controversy|concerns]] we have had are primarily with very young children who have family history of [[autism]] and with bundling too many immunizations at one time. There is no indication of the [[Controversies in autism|autism connection]] with vaccinations in older children. Furthermore, the new [[MMR vaccine|MMR vaccination]] is without [[thimerosal]] (mercury), which has also been [[Thiomersal controversy|a concern]] to many.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/texas-church-epicenter-measles-outbreak/story?id=20071644|title=Texas Church at Epicenter of Measles Outbreak|last=News|first=A. B. C.|date=2013-08-27|website=ABC News|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n===2015 ''Last Week Tonight'' criticism===\nKenneth Copeland and his wife, Gloria Copeland, were featured in a 2015 episode of ''[[Last Week Tonight with John Oliver]]'' that gained media attention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Last Week Tonight with John Oliver: Televangelists (HBO)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7y1xJAVZxXg|website=YouTube|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=16 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ohlheiser|first1=Abby|title=Comedian John Oliver takes on the prosperity gospel by becoming a televangelist|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/acts-of-faith/wp/2015/08/17/comedian-john-oliver-takes-on-the-prosperity-gospel-by-becoming-a-televangelist/|website=The Washington Post|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|title=John Oliver Becomes a Televangelist and Finally Starts His Own Church|url=http://time.com/3999933/john-oliver-televangelist-church-alst-week-tonight/|website=Time Magazine|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Marlow|title=John Oliver Exposes Shady Televangelists Fleecing Americans For Millions|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/08/17/john-oliver-exposes-shady-televangelists-fleecing-americans-for-millions.html|website=The Daily Beast|accessdate=18 August 2015|date=17 August 2015}}</ref> Comedian [[John Oliver (comedian)|John Oliver]] criticized the Copelands for using tax laws to live in a $6.3 million mansion as the [[parsonage]] allowance for their home is not subject to income taxes,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Burnett|first1=John|title=Can A Television Network Be A Church? The IRS Says Yes|url=https://www.npr.org/2014/04/01/282496855/can-a-television-network-be-a-church-the-irs-says-yes|website=NPR|accessdate=18 August 2015|format=1 April 2014}}</ref> for using church donations to buy a $20 million jet that was used for trips to a ski resort and a private game ranch,<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate audit critical of TV preacher Kenneth Copeland|url=http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|website=WFAA|accessdate=18 August 2015|location=Dallas, Texas|date=7 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019235219/http://www.wfaa.com/story/news/local/investigates/2014/08/10/13660222/|archive-date=October 19, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and for promotion of healing through faith and skepticism of medicine, which Oliver highlighted with a video of Gloria Copeland saying that doctors give patients \"poison that will make you sicker\" and that the church is an alternative to medical treatment: \"Which do you want to do? Do you want to do that\", Copeland asked of the doctor's \"poison\" treatment, \"or do you want to sit here on a Saturday morning, hear the word of God, and let faith come into your heart and be healed?\"\n\n===Private jets===\nIn 2009, Copeland's $3.6 million jet was denied tax-exempt status, opening up a possible investigation into the church's expenses; Copeland failed to disclose the salaries of his directors. In 2008 the ministry stated it owned five airplanes, one of which is valued at $17.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tax-Exempt Status For Televangelist's Jet Denied|publisher=Americans United|url=https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120124428/https://au.org/church-state/january-2009-church-state/au-bulletin/tax-exempt-status-for-televangelist%E2%80%99s-jet-denied|archive-date=January 20, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's ministry bought a multi-million [[Gulfstream V]] jet airplane,<ref name=CP-KC>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Acquires New Gulfstream V Jet, Seeks $19.5M for Upgrades and Maintenance|publisher=Christian Post|url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-acquires-new-gulfstream-v-jet-seeks-19-5m-for-upgrades-and-maintenance-214408/}}</ref> and Copeland thanked his followers and Jesus for buying it when it was delivered at the Fort Worth airstrip, wearing a [[Flight jacket|pilot jacket]] and sunglasses.<ref name=D5286955>{{cite web|title='Jesus bought this': Delighted televangelist Kenneth Copeland giggles with glee as he unveils new $3million private jet paid for by donations from his followers|publisher=Daily Mail|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5286955/Prosperity-Preacher-Kenneth-Copeland-giggles-GV.html}}</ref> The jet was bought from filmmaker and businessman [[Tyler Perry]].<ref name=D5286955/><ref name=CP-KC/> Now,{{when?|reason=This should be a \"As of\" fact. Saying \"Now\" introduces ambiguity.|date=April 2020}} the church is asking another $17<ref name=D5286955/> or $19.5 million for the building of a hangar, upgrading of the runway, and maintenance.<ref name=CP-KC/>\n\nIn 2015, Kenneth Copeland, in a broadcast alongside fellow televangelist [[Jesse Duplantis]], defended the use of private jets as a necessary part of their ministry, comparing flying in a commercial plane to getting \"in long tube with a bunch of demons\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost-private-jet\">{{cite news |last=Brice-Saddler |first=Michael |date=June 4, 2019 |title=A wealthy televangelist explains his fleet of private jets: \u2018It\u2019s a biblical thing\u2019 |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/religion/2019/06/04/wealthy-televangelist-explains-his-fleet-private-jets-its-biblical-thing/ |work=The Washingot Post |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bote |first=Joshua |date=December 15, 2019 |title='None of your business': A televangelist defending his private jets goes viral |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/06/04/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-private-jets-inside-edition/1337549001/ |work=USA Today |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Calicchio |first=Dom  |title=Televangelist Kenneth Copeland defends use of private jets in TV interview, denies calling people 'demons' |url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/televangelist-kenneth-copeland-defends-use-of-private-jets-in-tv-interview-denies-calling-people-demons |work=Fox News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brito |first=Christopher |date=June 4, 2019 |title=Televangelist defends lavish lifestyle and use of private jets, calls it a \"biblical thing\" |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/kenneth-copeland-televangelist-defends-lavish-lifestyle-and-use-of-private-jets-2019-06-04/ |work=CBS News |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\nCopeland's and other televangelists' use of private jets and other lavish houses and vehicles has been criticized.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Ministries Ups Being a Scumonaut by Bragging About New G5 Jet|publisher=Pulpit&Pen|url=http://pulpitandpen.org/2018/01/16/kenneth-copeland-ministries-ups-being-a-scumonaut-by-bragging-about-new-g5-jet/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kenneth Copeland Loves His New $36 Million Jet|publisher=Patheos|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|access-date=December 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324233307/http://www.patheos.com/blogs/warrenthrockmorton/2018/01/18/kenneth-copeland-36-million-jet/|archive-date=March 24, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Televagelist thanks Jesus for $36M private jet he uses to avoid demons|publisher=The Maven|url=https://www.themaven.net/beingliberal/room/televagelist-thanks-jesus-for-36m-private-jet-he-uses-to-avoid-demons-sldtGWfs-kq7Qisw941q5w}}</ref>\n\n=== COVID-19===\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic of COVID-19]], Copeland repeatedly got attention for his comments and actions in response to the outbreak. On March 11, 2020, Copeland claimed to heal viewers of his TV show of the disease, asking them to touch the television set as he prayed for them.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lemon |first=Jason |date=March 12, 2020 |title=Conservative Pastor Claims He 'Healed' Viewers of Coronavirus Through Their TV Screens |url=https://www.newsweek.com/conservative-pastor-claims-he-healed-viewers-coronavirus-through-their-tv-screens-1492044 |work=Newsweek |access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nAs many lost their jobs in the [[Coronavirus recession|economic crisis]] that the outbreak caused, Copeland told followers to continue paying tithes even if they lost their jobs.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gagn\u00e9 |first=Andr\u00e9 |date=March 29, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Trump and religious right rely on faith, not science |url=https://theconversation.com/coronavirus-trump-and-religious-right-rely-on-faith-not-science-134508 |work=The Conversation |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nIn a broadcast, Copeland called it a weak strain of the flu, and that fear of it was sin and putting faith in the devil. Copeland said that he did not agree with pastors that cancelled their services due to the coronavirus, saying \"I want you in my church. If we have to pass out thermometers. If we find one with a fever, let\u2019s get him healed right there. What if you do get it? Big deal!\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Blair |first=Leonardo |date=March 13, 2020 |title=Kenneth Copeland calls coronavirus \u2018very weak strain of flu,\u2019 says healthy people shouldn\u2019t fear |url=https://www.christianpost.com/news/kenneth-copeland-calls-coronavirus-very-weak-strain-of-flu-healthy-people-shouldnt-fear.html |work=The Christian Post |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jason |date=April 4, 202 |title=The rightwing Christian preachers in deep denial over Covid-19's danger |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/apr/04/america-rightwing-christian-preachers-virus-hoax |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Copeland has repeatedly said during the pandemic that it has ended or will soon end.<ref name=\"independent-corona\">{{cite news |last=Woodward |first=Alex |date=April 6, 2020 |title=Coronavirus: Televangelist Kenneth Copeland \u2018blows wind of God\u2019 at Covid-19 to \u2018destroy\u2019 pandemic  |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/kenneth-copeland-blow-coronavirus-pray-sermon-trump-televangelist-a9448561.html |work=The Independent |access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref> He said at one point that God told him that it would soon be over as Christians' prayers have overwhelmed it, and that the pandemic was brought to America by \"displays of hate\" towards president Donald Trump by critics, which had intereferred with \"divine protection\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Sommer |first=Will |date=March 23, 2020 |title=Trump\u2019s Megachurch Allies Promise COVID-19 Snake Oil and \u2018Miracles\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/trump-friendly-megachurch-pastors-push-bogus-coronavirus-cures |work=The Daily Beast |access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> On March 29, 2020, in a televised sermon, Copeland \"executed judgement\" on COVID-19. He claimed that it was \"finished\" and \"over\" and that the US was now \"healed and well again\".<ref name=\"independent-corona\" /> In another sermon shortly thereafter, Copeland claimed to destroy the virus with the \"wind of God\", saying \"I blow the wind of God on you. You are destroyed forever, and you\u2019ll never be back. Thank you, God. Let it happen. Cause it to happen.\"<ref name=\"independent-corona\" />\n\n==Selected KCM publications and recordings==\n*''Load Up Pocket Devotional: 31 Devotions to Revolutionize Your Future'' (Harrison House, July 2004) {{ISBN|1-57794-399-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577943990}}\n*''You Are Healed'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, July 1999) {{ISBN|0-88114-733-8}} {{ISBN|978-0881147339}}\n*''A Ceremony of Marriage'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-938458-15-9}} {{ISBN|978-0938458159}}\n*''Prayer: Your Foundation for Success'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57794-155-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941552}}\n*''Kenneth Copeland Reference Bible \u2013 Leather Bound'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1996) {{ISBN|0-88114-296-4}} {{ISBN|978-0881142969}}\n*''Becoming Subject to the Authority of Jesus'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-88114-972-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881149722}}\n*''How to Discipline Your Flesh'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1999) {{ISBN|1-57562-116-9}} {{ISBN|978-1575621166}}\n*''From Faith to Faith: A Daily Guide to Victory'' (Harrison House, May 2000) {{ISBN|1-57794-225-6}} {{ISBN|978-1577942252}}\n*''Pursuit of His Presence: Daily Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-137-3}} {{ISBN|978-1577941378}}\n*''The Wake-up Call'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2002) {{ISBN|1-57562-792-2}} {{ISBN|978-1575627922}}\n*''Classic Redemption'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2001) {{ISBN|0-938458-58-2}} {{ISBN|978-0938458586}}\n*''The Laws of Prosperity'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, December 1995) {{ISBN|0-88114-952-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149524}}\n*''Prosperity: The Choice Is Yours'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, June 1992) {{ISBN|0-88114-728-1}} {{ISBN|978-0881147285}}\n*''Healing Promises'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, August 1994) {{ISBN|0-88114-949-7}} {{ISBN|978-0881149494}}\n*''Over the Edge: Youth Devotional'' (Harrison House, September 1998) {{ISBN|1-57794-138-1}} {{ISBN|978-1577941385}}\n*''Big Band Gospel'' (KCP Records, 2003)\n*''Racism in the Church. Kill the Root, Destroy the Tree'' (Kenneth Copeland Publications, 2016) {{ISBN|978-1604633252}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Trinity Foundation (Dallas)]]\n*[[Neo-charismatic churches]]\n*[[Charismatic movement]]\n*[[Word of Faith]]\n*[[Prosperity Gospel]]\n*[[Tony Palmer (bishop)]]\n*[[Ulf Ekman]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.kcm.org/ Kenneth Copeland Ministries official site]\n*[http://emic.org Eagle Mountain International Church]\n*[http://bvov.tv Believer's Voice of Victory streaming site]\n*[http://believersstandunited.com Believers Stand United for Religious Freedom in America]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Copeland, Kenneth}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Pentecostal pastors]]\n[[Category:American television evangelists]]\n[[Category:American Charismatics]]\n[[Category:Imperial Records artists]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University people]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Worth, Texas]]\n[[Category:People from Lubbock, Texas]]\n[[Category:Pentecostal writers]]\n[[Category:Oral Roberts University alumni]]\n[[Category:American faith healers]]\n[[Category:Prosperity theologians]]\n[[Category:Pentecostals from Texas]]\n[[Category:Texas Republicans]]\n", "name_user": "47.55.217.243", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenneth_Copeland"}
{"title_page": "Cycling in Cardiff", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n[[File:Heath cycling sign.JPG|thumb|right|A directional sign for cyclists in [[Llanishen]]]]\n'''Cycling in Cardiff''', capital of [[Wales]], is facilitated by its easy gradients and large parks.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/wales/southeast/travel/pages/cycling.shtml BBC South East Wales | Cycling]</ref>{{failed verification|date=August 2012}} In the mid-2000s between 2.7% and 4.3% of people [[Bicycle commuting|commuted]] to work by cycling in the city.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2017 12.4% of workers cycled to work at least 5 days a week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/Your-Council/Have-your-say/Ask%20Cardiff%20Library/Transport%20Survey%202017%20Report.pdf|title=Transport Survey, 2017|last=|first=|date=January 2018|website=Cardiff Research Centre|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> However, cyclists in the city are deterred from cycling by poor facilities and aggressive traffic, according to research by [[Cardiff University]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dft.gov.uk/rmd/project.asp?intProjectID=10041 |title=DfT {{!}} Project: Evaluating the Success of Urban Cycle Networks |access-date=29 April 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090512083557/http://www.dft.gov.uk/rmd/project.asp?intProjectID=10041 |archive-date=12 May 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAs the busiest city, [[Cardiff]] is statistically the most dangerous place to cycle in Wales. Between 1999 and 2008, 1,000 cyclists were injured on the road, 20% of all cycling accidents in Wales, although the number of injuries to cyclists continues to fall.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2010/04/08/cardiff-is-the-most-dangerous-place-in-wales-to-cycle-91466-26196759/ Wales Online | Cardiff is the most dangerous place in Wales to cycle]</ref>\n\nThe Cardiff cycle network is over {{convert|94|km|mi|disp=flip}} long with an additional {{convert|3|-|6|mi|km|0}} completed each year.<ref>[http://www.keepingcardiffmoving.co.uk/_media/file/City%20Hall%20Travel%20Plan.pdf Keep Cardiff Moving | City Hall Travel Plan | p6]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Council policy==\nAccording to their Cycling Strategy (see below), [[Cardiff County Council]] aims to encourage citizens to cycle more, citing the improved health through increased fitness, reduced pollution and congestion of the local environment, economic gains through cycle tourism and leisure, independence for those people who cannot or do not wish to use a car, and the fact that cycling can be the quickest and most convenient form of transport in urban areas such as Cardiff.<ref name=\"cardiff.gov.uk\">[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?Object_ID=10140 Cardiff Council | Cycling Strategy July 2007]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2002 they appointed a full-time Cycling Officer.<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?Object_ID=10140 Cardiff Council | Cycling Strategy July 2007]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} p.10</ref>\n\nThe council's Transport, Infrastructure and Waste service aims to ensure that an increase in cycling is matched with a reduction in the number of collisions involving cyclists.\n\nCardiff Council also provides off-road cycle training for school pupils to develop basic cycling skills based upon the National Cycling Proficiency Scheme. Training covers the Highway Code, negotiating obstacles, turning left and right, emergency stops and basic cycle maintenance.<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=2870%2C4048%2C4196%2C4606&parent_directory_id=2865 Cardiff Council | Cycling: Contacts]</ref> More than 1,500 children participate in this course every year in Cardiff, according to the council's Cycling Strategy.\n\nThe council produces a free map of the city, available from its offices or from cycle shops, highlighting cycle paths, lanes and suggested cycle routes.\n\n===Strategy===\nThe council's Cycling Strategy was adopted in 1998. The 2007 update showed that 2.7% of people living in Cardiff cycled to work in 2001, an increase from 2.6% in 1991. However, an Omnibus survey showed that in 2003 and 2005, 3.6% and 4.3% of people cycled to work respectively. Although, the number of children cycling to school fell from 5% to 2% since 1989\u201391. In the strategy, the council intends to:<ref name=\"cardiff.gov.uk\"/>\n*encourage and promote cycling\n*provide safe facilities such as wider cycle lanes and advanced stop lines at traffic signals\n*conduct a trial scheme to assess the viability of allowing cycling through pedestrian areas in the city centre\n*improve cycle links between residential and commercial areas\n*facilitate integration with other modes of transport\n*improve and maintain the cycle network\n*develop and clearly sign routes\n\n=== Cycleways ===\nCardiff Council are in the process of developing 5 cycleways across the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/|title=Cardiff Council|website=www.cardiff.gov.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> This falls in line with its strategy to provide far more segregation from motorised traffic for cyclists.\n\nWhile work on the routes has already broken ground<ref>{{Citation|title=Cycleway 1, Cardiff (under construction)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2XTvUpUryBE|language=en|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>, some have criticised both certain design flaws<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/travel/cycle-super-highways/Documents/CSH1.1%20Consultation%20Report%20ENG.pdf|title=CSH1.1 St Andrew\u2019s Crescent, St Andrew\u2019s Place and Senghennydd Road Consultation Report|date=2018-10-17|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> and how long it is taking for consultations to be published, with only two published within as many years. While some routes are essentially brand new, others are facelifts or changes of priority for current routes, such as Cycleway 3 on Lloyd George Avenue, and Cycleway 2 on Newport Road.\n\nThe proposed Cycleway routes are:\n\n* Cycleway 1: City Centre to Cathays, University Hospital Wales, Heath High Level and Heath Low Level Rail Stations, and North East Cardiff Strategic Development Site\n* Cycleway 2: City Centre to Adamsdown, Newport Road retail parks, Rumney, Llanrumney and St Mellons Business Park\n* Cycleway 3: City Centre to Cardiff Bay\n* Cycleway 4: City Centre to Llandaff, Danescourt and North West Strategic Development Site\n* Cycleway 5: City Centre to Riverside, Ely and Caerau.\n\n==Cycle facilities==\n[[File:Cycle lane in Excalibur Drive, Cardiff.jpg|right|thumb|Example from Excalibur Drive of the red cycle lanes used in Cardiff.]]\n\n===Cycle Shops===\nThe 2011 Cardiff Council cycle map listed 12 cycle shops (down from 14 in 2009) in the city: in [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]], [[Cathays]] (Crwys Road), [[Cathays]] (Woodville Road), [[Gabalfa]], [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]], [[Llandaff North]], [[Llanrumney]], [[Pontcanna]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bikeshedwales.com/|title=The Bike Shed, Cardiff. Electric Bikes, Road, Mountain, Hybrid, E Bikes, E-Bikes, Ebikes, Emtb, Kids. Trek, Genesis, Merida, Ridgeback, Bianchi, Raleigh, Electra, Pashley, Ragley, Dahon, Adventure. Sales and repair. The Friendly Bike Shop, Cathedral Road. Cardiff.|website=www.bikeshedwales.com|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>, [[Rhiwbina]], [[Roath]] (Broadway), [[Roath]] ([[Newport Road]]) and [[Whitchurch, Cardiff|Whitchurch]].<ref>Cardiff Council ''Cardiff Cycling map'' 6th edition (2011)</ref> Braddicks on Broadway, Roath, closed in January 2015 after 70 years trading.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/local-news/cardiff-cycle-shop-founded-empire-8544816 \"Cardiff cycle shop founded by Empire Games hero Reg Braddick closes after 70 years\"], ''Wales Online'', 29 January 2015.</ref>\n\n===Cycle lanes===\nSome roads in the city provide distinct cycle lanes to the left of the vehicle lane. According to the Cardiff Cycle Map, these include:\n;West Cardiff\n*''Cowbridge Road East'' and ''Castle Street'': main western approach from [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] to the city centre\n*''Wellington Street'': parallel to Cowbridge Road East and part of the [[A4161 road]]\n*''Pen-Hill Road'' and ''Cathedral Road'': in [[Pontcanna]]\n*''St Fagans Road and Pencisely Road'': roads approaching [[Waun-Gron Park railway station]] in [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]]\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''Caerphilly Road'': a main road in [[Birchgrove, Cardiff|Birchgrove]] from the city centre to northern suburbs and part of the [[A469 road]]\n*''Excalibur Drive'': leads from Caerphilly Road to [[Lisvane and Thornhill railway station]] in [[Thornhill, Cardiff|Thornhill]]\n*''Ty-Glas Road'': leads from Caerphilly Road through [[Llanishen]]\n*''Cathays Terrace'': connects Crwys Road (the main road through [[Cathays]]) and Corbett Road (around [[Cardiff University]])\n*''Fairoak Road'': connects Crwys Road and Wedal Road (near [[Roath Park]])\n\n[[File:Cycle only sign united kingdom.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Sign denoting a path only to be used by cyclists]]\n;South Cardiff\n*''Penarth Road'': part of the [[A4160 road]] leads from Callaghan Square near [[Cardiff Central railway station|Cardiff Central]] to [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]\n*''James Street:'' leads from [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] to [[Cardiff Bay]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''Llanrumney Avenue'': a main suburban road running through [[Llanrumney]]\n\n===Bus and cycle lanes===\nThere are also lanes that cyclists share with buses, motorcycles and taxis, in which it is illegal to drive on in any other motor vehicle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/1522524.thousands_of_motorists_to_be_caught_by_bus_lane_spy_cam/ |title=Thousands of motorists to be caught by bus lane spy cam (From The Argus) |publisher=Theargus.co.uk |date=5 July 2007 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> Such lanes are on:\n*''Newport Road'': in [[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]] and [[Roath]], East Cardiff\n*''Westgate Street'', ''St Mary Street'' and ''Wood Street'': in the City Centre\n*''Boulevard de Nantes'' and ''Dumfries Place'': leading from [[Cathays Park]] in the centre to Newport Road and East Cardiff\n*''Cowbridge Road East'': from [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] to [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely Bridge]] in West Cardiff\n*''Tudor Street'': a main city centre approach from [[Riverside, Cardiff|Riverside]] in West Cardiff\n\n===Segregated / off-road cycle paths===\n[[Segregated cycle facilities]] can be a shared [[Sidewalk|pavement]] with pedestrians, running alongside a road or through a park for example. This is denoted by a blue circular sign showing a bicycle and pedestrians. A cycle only route is denoted by blue circular sign showing only a bicycle. Much of the ''Taff Trail, Ely Trail'' and ''Rumney Trail'' are segregated from traffic. Other such routes in the city include:\n\n;West Cardiff\n*''[[Llandaff Fields]]'': through parkland area in [[Pontcanna]], connecting with the ''Taff Trail''\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''M4 Junction 32'': routes run under the junction from [[Coryton, Cardiff|Coryton]] to [[Tongwynlais]]\n*''Gabalfa Interchange'': routes run over and round the junction as an alternative to vehicle routes \n*''[[University Hospital of Wales]]'': routes run around Heath Hospital through King George Field\n\n;South Cardiff\n*North Road<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/transport-projects/Consultations/Documents/09.01.18/North%20Road%20Consultation%20Report%20ENG%2008.01.18.pdf|title=North Road / Corbett Road Cycleway Upgrade and Pedestrian Facilities|date=2019-08-22|website=North Road / Corbett Road Cycleway Upgrade and Pedestrian Facilities|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/transport-projects/Consultations/Documents/CO18041-%2801-05%29-B%20Concept%20Design.pdf|title=North Road Cycleway Upgrade Phase 2|date=2019-08-22|website=North Road Cycleway Upgrade Phase 2|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>: from the [[Royal Welsh College of Music & Drama]] to Llys Talybont, connecting to the ''Taff Trail''.\n*''Leckwith Road'': from [[Ninian Park railway station]] in [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] connecting to the ''Ely Trail.''\n*''[[Cardiff International Sports Village]]'': the vicinity has a network of segregated routes connected to the ''Ely Trail'' in the west, [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] in the north, and [[Cardiff Bay]] in the east.\n*''Lloyd George Avenue'': from the City Centre to Cardiff Bay, part of Route 8\n*''Central Link'': parallel to the east of Lloyd George Avenue\n*''[[Butetown]]: a route runs through a housing estate to Cardiff Bay, parallel to the west of Lloyd George Avenue\n*''Rover Way'': through an industrial and commercial estate between [[Adamsdown]] and [[Tremorfa]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''[[Llanedeyrn]]'': a route runs through the housing estate from St Mellons Road to Llanedeyrn Interchange\n*''Pentwyn Drive'': a route runs along this road in [[Pentwyn, Cardiff|Pentwyn]] around Wern-goch Park and connects with the ''Rumney Trail''\n*''[[St Mellons]]'': routes connect various parts of the suburb\n*''[[Llanrumney]]'': a route connects Llanrumney Avenue with Ball Road, near the ''Rumney Trail''\n\n===Cycle parking===\nThere are [[bicycle stand]]s for parking in locations including the following:\n\n;West Cardiff\n*''[[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]]'': Cowbridge Road East, Wellington Street and Llandaff Road\n*''[[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]]'': Fairwater Library\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''[[Rhiwbina]]'': [[Rhiwbina railway station]]\n*''[[Cathays]]'': North Road ([[A470 road]]) and [[Cathays Library]]\n*''[[Penylan]]'': Penylan Library\n\n;South Cardiff\n*''[[Cardiff Bay]]'': around [[Mermaid Quay]], [[Wales Millennium Centre]], [[Atlantic Wharf]] and West Bute Street\n\n;[[Cardiff City Centre]]\n*''Central Square'': for [[Cardiff Central bus station|Central bus]] and [[Cardiff Central railway station|railway stations]]\n*''Castle Street'': near [[Millennium Stadium]]\n*''Wood Street'': at Millennium Plaza\n*''The Hayes'': for [[Cardiff Central Library]]\n*''Westgate Street'': opposite Millennium Stadium\n*''The Friary'': for Queen Street\n*''Park Place'': for Queen Street\n*''Charles Street'': for Queen Street\n*''Churchill Way'': for Queen Street and [[Capitol Shopping Centre]]\n*''Queen Street'': near junction with Newport Road\n*''[[Cardiff Queen Street railway station]]''\n*''Callahagn Square''\n*''[[Cathays Park]]'': at [[City Hall, Cardiff|City Hall]]\n*''[[Adamsdown]]'': [[Roath Library]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''[[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]]'': Rumney Library\n*''[[Llanrumney]]'': Llanrumney Library\n*''[[St Mellons]]'': St Mellons Library\n\n===Cycle hire===\n[[File:Cardiff cycle hire 2010.jpg|thumb|2009 scheme cycle hire station on<br>Queen Street/Churchill Way]]\nPedal Power is a charity with their main bike centre in [[Pontcanna]] offering cycle hire facilities. Cycle training and cycle assessments are also available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffpedalpower.org/ |title=Home |publisher=Cardiffpedalpower.org |date=23 June 2010 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n====OYBike====\nIn March 2009 the [[Welsh Assembly Government]] and Cardiff Council announced plans to introduce a free cycle hire scheme, with bike racks placed around the city, allowing people to pick up bikes and ride them to another point, where they would leave the bike. Money would also be put into creating more strategic cycle routes and cycle lanes.<ref>{{cite web|author=Abby Alford |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/cardiff-news/2009/03/12/cardiff-transport-shake-up-must-work-91466-23125436/ |title=News \u2013 Cardiff News \u2013 Cardiff transport shake-up 'must work' |publisher=WalesOnline |date=12 March 2009 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> The system, similar to those in other large cities, launched in September 2009,<ref>[http://www.bikeradar.com/news/article/oybike-rental-scheme-a-success-in-cardiff-25570/ \"OYBike rental scheme a success in Cardiff: Council hopes for more fairweather converts\" 4 April 2010 at bikeradar.com] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/cardiff/2010/apr/07/cardiff-oybike-scheme-paris-velib \"OYBike fails to ring my bell\" Opinion \"With Cardiff's answer to the Parisian V\u00e9lib relaunching this spring, we decided to take a city SmartBike for a whirl\"] 8 April 2010, at theguardian.com, Accessed 14 September 2017</ref> and included 70 bikes and 35 hire points (initially 7) around the centre and the south of the city. The stations (in 2010) were: Central Station; Cardiff Castle; Central Library; Queen Street Station; Churchill Way; City Hall; eastern Queen Street; Cardiff Bay Station; County Hall; and Cardiff Bay Visitors\u2019 Centre.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmMap?OpenForm&ParentUNID=241B7D69F515D518802576380073E8D9 |title=Reinventing the wheel &#124; Rental Locations |publisher=OYBike |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100625215540/http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmMap?OpenForm&ParentUNID=241B7D69F515D518802576380073E8D9 |archivedate=25 June 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It was necessary to register before using a bike. The first half an hour was free after which a small hourly fee was payable. The scheme, which was part of a \u00a328.5&nbsp;million plan to encourage residents in the capital to use sustainable transport and ease congestion, was welcomed by campaigners.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/wales/south_east/8267199.stm |title=UK &#124; Wales &#124; South East Wales &#124; Public bike hire scheme for city |publisher=BBC News |date=22 September 2009 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Abby Alford |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/cardiff-news/2009/09/22/smart-bike-system-launch-91466-24747392/ |title=News \u2013 Cardiff News \u2013 Smart bike system launch |publisher=WalesOnline |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe cycle scheme run by [[OYBike]] ended in December 2011 after funding was removed by Cardiff council; the operator did not have other sponsors so the bikes along with their smart locks were removed from the city centre.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/local-news/brakes-put-bike-hire-scheme-1796236 \"Brakes put on bike hire scheme: A bike hire scheme is to be scrapped next month after Cardiff council ended its financial support.\" 16 November 2011 at walesonline.co.uk] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref>\n\n====Nextbike====\nIn June 2017 [[Nextbike]] was announced as the new provider of a public bike hire scheme for Cardiff. This would integrate new technology into the bikes, rather than the docking stations.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/cardiffs-new-bike-hire-scheme-13201489 Ruth Mosalski: \"Cardiff's new bike hire scheme expected to be up and running by this autumn\", 19 June 2017 at walesonline.co.uk] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref> Fifty bikes went 'live' in March 2018, with an official launch in May 2018 when the numbers would increase to 250.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/wales/2018-03-26/first-wave-of-nextbikes-arrive-in-cardiff-in-bid-to-reduce-congestion/ |title=First wave of nextbikes arrive in Cardiff in bid to reduce congestion |work=ITV News |date=26 March 2018 |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> The bikes could be rented via a website, a telephone hotline, or by downloading a [[mobile app]]. Standard charges were \u00a31 for every half hour period. Annual subscriptions were also available.<ref name=hugecyclingboom>{{cite news|author=Jessica Walford|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/cardiff-seeing-huge-cycling-boom-14778283 |title=Cardiff is seeing a huge cycling boom on back of city's new bike-hire scheme |work=Wales Online |date=13 June 2018 |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> Almost 7,800 people were registered for the scheme by June 2018.<ref name=hugecyclingboom /> Nextbike has been both popular and successful, with Cardiff Council backing the scheme.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/|title=Cardiff Council|website=www.cardiff.gov.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>\n\n===Cycle refurbishment===\nCardiff Cycle Workshop, a bike workshop launched in July 2010 in [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely]], refurbishes and repairs unwanted cycles, saving old bikes from the landfill and revitalises them for new owners at cheaper prices. Cardiff Cycle Workshop has an agreement with [[Cardiff Council]] for cages to be placed in the waste facilities in [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]] and [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] for members of the public to leave their unwanted bicycles. Then the bikes are refurbished, checked for safety and have parts replaced. The bikes are then sold for anything from \u00a310 to \u00a3150. Three year funding has come from the [[Big Lottery Fund]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/cardiff/2010/jul/07/cardiff-cycle-workshop-vintage-bikes-ely-dr-bike-cycle-training-wales Guardian Cardiff | New Cardiff Cycle Workshop opens as city sees vintage bike revival]</ref>\n\n==Cycling routes==\n\n===Ely Trail===\n[[File:Ely Trail Picnic Area.JPG|thumb|right|150px|A picnic area on the Ely Trail]]\nThe off-road ''Ely Trail'' is under development in the west and south of the city as of 2010, funded by the County Council, Visit Wales, and Countryside Council for Wales.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=7845 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182655/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=7845 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> So far completed is the northern section through [[St Fagans]], [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]] and [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely]], and the southern section running from [[Leckwith]] to the south along the [[River Ely]] through [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]], finishing at the [[Cardiff International Sports Village]]. However, these sections are yet to be connected.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=5987 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182824/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=5987 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe route is connected to [[Cardiff City Centre]] via an off-road north-south route through [[Butetown]].<ref>Cardiff Cycling Map 2007</ref> The ''Taff Trail'' at [[Cardiff Bay]] can also be joined from the trail via Grangetown and Butetown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=10831 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182945/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=10831 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:Ely Trail Fairwater.JPG|The Ely Trail in Fairwater\nFile:Ely Trail St Fagans.JPG|The end of the Ely Trail in St Fagans\n</gallery>\n\n===Rhymney Trail===\nThe off-road ''Rhymney Trail'' is being developed by the Council as a commuting and recreational route along the [[Rhymney River]] in the east of the city. Currently completed is the section between [[Llanedeyrn]] and [[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=3620 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609183218/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=3620 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The Cardiff Cycle Map shows the route running off-road from Llanedeyrn Interchange, bypassing [[Llanrumney]] to the west, briefly joining Newport Road (B4487), and then heading south of Rumney to Wentloog Avenue (B4239). However, an off-road section also runs north-south through [[Pentwyn, Cardiff|Pentwyn]] from Llanedeyrn.\n\n===Taff Trail===\n[[File:Taff Trail sign, Grangetown.jpg|thumb|upright|100px|Taff Trail route sign in [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]]]\nThe 55-mile long ''[[Taff Trail]]'' runs from [[Cardiff Bay]] through [[Pontypridd]] and [[Merthyr Tydfil]] to [[Brecon]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ |title=Cycle the Taff Trail \u2013 Breath the Contrasts across South Wales |publisher=Tafftrail.org.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050707013107/http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ |archivedate=7 July 2005 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> forming part of the ''[[L\u00f4n Las Cymru]]'' \u2013 the [[National Cycle Network]] ''[[National Cycle Route 8|Route 8]]'' to [[Holyhead]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sustrans.org.uk/default.asp?sID=1215165108687 |title=Route 8 |publisher=Sustrans |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe route begins at [[Roald Dahl Plass]] in [[Cardiff Bay]] and runs mostly off-road through the city for {{convert|7.5|mi|km}} north around [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://greenergrangetown.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/taff-embankment.pdf|title=Taff Embankment|website=Greener Grangetown|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> and the [[Cardiff City Centre|City Centre]], joining the [[River Taff]] in [[Bute Park]] before heading north-west through [[Llandaff]] and [[Radyr]], leaving the city at [[Tongwynlais]].\n\n===Route 88: Coastal route===\n[[File:Pont y Werin construction.JPG|thumb|left|150px|Pont y Werin under construction]]\n''Route 88'' is a proposed coastal route from [[Newport, Wales|Newport]] to [[Margam Country Park]] via [[Cardiff]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sustrans.org.uk/default.asp?sID=1099920442406 |title=Route 88 |publisher=Sustrans |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Pont y Werin===\n'''Pont y Werin''' ([[Welsh language|Welsh]] for ''The People's Bridge'') is a pedestrian and cyclist bridge spanning the [[River Ely]] between [[Cardiff Bay]] and [[Penarth]]. Costing approximately [[GBP|\u00a3]]4.5&nbsp;million, Pont y Werin crosses between the [[Cardiff International Sports Village]] and [[Penarth]], allowing the public to travel to the Sports Village via [[Cogan railway station]].<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=&id=5034&Positioning_Article_ID=&Language=&d1=0 Cardiff Council's proposed bridge] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609170317/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=&id=5034&Positioning_Article_ID=&Language=&d1=0 |date=9 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\nOpened on 14 July 2010, the [[bascule bridge]] completes the {{convert|6.5|mi|km|adj=on}} Cardiff Bay circular walk and cycle route,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/southeastwales/hi/people_and_places/nature/newsid_8599000/8599389.stm BBC News: ''First steps on bridge between Cardiff and the Vale'']</ref> and incorporates a 20-metre opening section to allow river traffic to pass.\n\n===Penarth===\nIn 2010 it was announced a commuter route for cyclists would be installed, aiming to improve transport links between Penarth and Cardiff Bay.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2010/10/29/cycle-lane-plan-for-penarth-to-cardiff-bay-route-91466-27562766/#ixzz13l3qcBn2 \"Cycle lane plan for Penarth to Cardiff Bay route\"], WalesOnline \u2013 29 October 2010</ref>{{update inline|date=August 2013}}\n\n==Integration==\n\n===Cardiff rail network===\nCycling is integrated into the city's [[Valley Lines|urban rail network]], which is operated by [[Transport for Wales Rail]]. Most trains have spaces for two cycles. However they are not permitted on services from [[Caerphilly railway station|Caerphilly]], [[Radyr railway station|Radyr]] (except the [[Cardiff City Line|City Line]]), [[Cadoxton railway station|Cadoxton]], and [[Ebbw Vale Town railway station|Ebbw Vale Town]] to [[Cardiff Queen Street railway station|Cardiff Queen Street]] or [[Cardiff Central railway station|Cardiff Central]] between 07:00 and 09:30, or services in the reverse direction 16:00 to 18:00 on weekdays. Outside these times, carriage is still at the discretion of the [[Conductor (transportation)#Train guard|guard]]. [[Folding bicycle|Folding cycles]] can be carried folded-up at any time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arrivatrainswales.co.uk/WorkArea/showcontent.aspx?id=5300 |title=showcontent |publisher=Arrivatrainswales.co.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525204448/http://www.arrivatrainswales.co.uk/WorkArea/showcontent.aspx?id=5300 |archivedate=25 May 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThere is cycle storage at Cardiff Central station on all platforms, at the front and rear entrances to the station, and in the Riverside car park.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/stations/CDF.html#Accessibility |title=National Rail Enquiries \u2013 Station Facilities for Cardiff Central |publisher=Nationalrail.co.uk |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n===National rail network===\nCycles are also permitted free of charge on the wider national network provided they can be safely stored in the designated areas and reservations through the [[train operating company|train operator]] are recommended. Bikes must be carried in the designated area of the train and can't be stored in aisles or vestibule areas. Cycles can not be carried on rail-replacement coach services. Folding bikes can be carried at all times as normal hand luggage.\n\nArriva Trains Wales also operates most of the [[Transport in Wales#Railways|Welsh rail network]] and its cycle policies apply to other services as well without the restrictions applied to the Cardiff rail network.\n\n===Buses===\nCycles can not be carried on bus services in Cardiff. However, a ''Beacons Bus'' runs on Sundays and Bank Holidays in summer to [[Brecon]] which tows a cycle trailer to carry cycles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclebreconbeacons.com/en/contactus_transport.html |title=How to get here \u2013 Cycling in the Brecon Beacons National Park |publisher=Cyclebreconbeacons.com |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930192528/http://www.cyclebreconbeacons.com/en/contactus_transport.html |archivedate=30 September 2009 }}</ref> Efforts have been made to ensure there is bike parking next to bus stops.\n\n==Cycling Campaigns in Cardiff==\n\n=== Sustrans Cymru ===\nSustrans is a UK sustainable transport charity that constructs safe cycle routes and other inititiatives to encourage people to walk or cycle. Their ''Valleys Cycle Network'' project aims to add 100 miles of vehicle-free routes in the Valleys of South Wales.<ref>[http://www.sustrans.org.uk/sustrans-near-you/wales Sustrans website \"Wales\"] Retrieved 10 September 2011.</ref>\n\nIn September 2011 it was announced that Sustrans Cymru were launching a new project in Cardiff funded by the Wales Government. This involved offering expert consultation to Cardiff householders to draw up personal travel plans, designed to reduce car journeys and encourage, amongst other things, increased use of bicycles.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2011/09/07/cardiff-to-spearhead-a-commuter-revolution-91466-29376067/ ''Cardiff to spearhead a commuter revolution''] Wales Online, 11 September 2011 (Retrieved 10 September 2011)</ref>\n\n===Cardiff Cycling Campaign===\nThe ''Cardiff Cycling Campaign'' campaigns for better provisions for cyclists in the city,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffcyclingcampaign.org.uk/ |title=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |date=11 March 2008 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> believing that the council's attitude is inadequate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffcyclingcampaign.org.uk/modules.php?name=FAQ&myfaq=yes&id_cat=1&categories= |title=FAQ |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> While it welcomes the Council's commitment to consider the needs of cyclists, it argues that these should not be marginal in relation to the management of cars and buses. A sea-change in thinking is required and available Council funds need to be used imaginatively to create 'coherent and continuous routes' through the city for cyclists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cardiff-cycling-campaign.co.uk/information/useful-information/ |title=Useful Information |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign website |date= |accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref> For example, safe cycling routes through the city centre were lost with the construction of the new St Davids 2 shopping centre.\n\nIn April 2006 the Campaign pointed out that only 2.7% of people cycled to work in Cardiff. Campaigners cycled through Cardiff city centre during a rush hour period, accompanied by local councillors and a Welsh Assembly Member. A participating councillor was quoted as saying 'I was happy to rise to the challenge but at times it was frightening. The cycle lanes were sometimes inadequate and complicated, and if I hadn't been with the campaign I probably would have got lost'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Councillors+are+told%3A+%27Get+on+your+bikes%27.-a0144554176 |title=''Councillors are told: 'Get on your bikes'.'' |publisher=South Wales Echo article reproduced by thefreelibrary.com |year=2006 |accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Cycle Cardiff===\n''Cycle Cardiff'' aims to raise awareness of cycling and organises bike rides in and around the city.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclecardiff.org.uk/ |title=Cycle Cardiff |publisher=www.cyclecardiff.org.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100327144130/http://www.cyclecardiff.org.uk/ |archive-date=27 March 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===World Naked Bike Ride===\nThe ''Cardiff World Naked Bike Ride'' has taken place annually since 2008. This is part of a globally coordinated [[World Naked Bike Ride]], designed to highlight the vulnerability of cyclists on the road and campaign for better cycling facilities. In June 2011 80 cyclists reportedly took part riding through the centre of Cardiff, many of them naked.<ref>[http://yourcardiff.walesonline.co.uk/2011/06/13/naked-bike-ride-takes-over-cardiffs-streets/ ''\"Naked bike ride takes over Cardiff's streets\"''] WalesOnline, 13 June 2011</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Outline of cycling]]\n*[https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/travel/cycle-super-highways/Pages/default.aspx Cycleways - Cardiff.gov.uk]\n\n==References==\n{{Primary sources|date=April 2009}}\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Cycling in Cardiff}}\n*[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=2870%2C4048%2C4196&parent_directory_id=2865 Cardiff Council cycling home page]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050707013107/http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ Unofficial Taff Trail Website]\n*[http://www.sustrans.co.uk/webfiles/leaflets/Sustrans_Taff%20Trail_Nov08.pdf Official Taff Trail Leaflet]{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://www.routes2ride.org.uk/wales/routes2ride/taff_trail_cardiff_to_castell_coch/ Taff Trail in Cardiff]\n*[http://www.keepingcardiffmoving.co.uk/ Keeping Cardiff Moving]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091015212242/http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmHome?OpenForm&ParentUNID=5E8F660D1D16E66B80257638007563B5 OYBike \u2013 Cardiff Smart Bike hire]\n*[http://wiki.worldnakedbikeride.org/index.php?title=Cardiff World Naked Bike Ride, Cardiff] \n*[http://www.cardiffpedalpower.org/ Pedal Power Bike Hire ]\n{{Transport in Cardiff}}\n{{Cycling in different countries and cities}}\n\n[[Category:Cycling in Wales]]\n[[Category:Transport in Cardiff]]\n[[Category:Transport in Wales]]\n[[Category:Cycling by city|Cardiff]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=September 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n[[File:Heath cycling sign.JPG|thumb|right|A directional sign for cyclists in [[Llanishen]]]]\n'''Cycling in Cardiff''', capital of [[Wales]], is facilitated by its easy gradients and large parks.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/wales/southeast/travel/pages/cycling.shtml BBC South East Wales | Cycling]</ref>{{failed verification|date=August 2012}} In the mid-2000s between 2.7% and 4.3% of people [[Bicycle commuting|commuted]] to work by cycling in the city.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2017 12.4% of workers cycled to work at least 5 days a week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/Your-Council/Have-your-say/Ask%20Cardiff%20Library/Transport%20Survey%202017%20Report.pdf|title=Transport Survey, 2017|last=|first=|date=January 2018|website=Cardiff Research Centre|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> However, cyclists in the city are deterred from cycling by poor facilities and aggressive traffic, according to research by [[Cardiff University]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dft.gov.uk/rmd/project.asp?intProjectID=10041 |title=DfT {{!}} Project: Evaluating the Success of Urban Cycle Networks |access-date=29 April 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090512083557/http://www.dft.gov.uk/rmd/project.asp?intProjectID=10041 |archive-date=12 May 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAs the busiest city, [[Cardiff]] is statistically the most dangerous place to cycle in Wales. Between 1999 and 2008, 1,000 cyclists were injured on the road, 20% of all cycling accidents in Wales, although the number of injuries to cyclists continues to fall.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2010/04/08/cardiff-is-the-most-dangerous-place-in-wales-to-cycle-91466-26196759/ Wales Online | Cardiff is the most dangerous place in Wales to cycle]</ref>\n\nThe Cardiff cycle network is over {{convert|94|km|mi|disp=flip}} long with an additional {{convert|3|-|6|mi|km|0}} completed each year.<ref>[http://www.keepingcardiffmoving.co.uk/_media/file/City%20Hall%20Travel%20Plan.pdf Keep Cardiff Moving | City Hall Travel Plan | p6]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Council policy==\nAccording to their Cycling Strategy (see below), [[Cardiff County Council]] aims to encourage citizens to cycle more, citing the improved health through increased fitness, reduced pollution and congestion of the local environment, economic gains through cycle tourism and leisure, independence for those people who cannot or do not wish to use a car, and the fact that cycling can be the quickest and most convenient form of transport in urban areas such as Cardiff.<ref name=\"cardiff.gov.uk\">[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?Object_ID=10140 Cardiff Council | Cycling Strategy July 2007]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In 2002 they appointed a full-time Cycling Officer.<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?Object_ID=10140 Cardiff Council | Cycling Strategy July 2007]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} p.10</ref>\n\nThe council's Transport, Infrastructure and Waste service aims to ensure that an increase in cycling is matched with a reduction in the number of collisions involving cyclists.\n\nCardiff Council also provides off-road cycle training for school pupils to develop basic cycling skills based upon the National Cycling Proficiency Scheme. Training covers the Highway Code, negotiating obstacles, turning left and right, emergency stops and basic cycle maintenance.<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=2870%2C4048%2C4196%2C4606&parent_directory_id=2865 Cardiff Council | Cycling: Contacts]</ref> More than 1,500 children participate in this course every year in Cardiff, according to the council's Cycling Strategy.\n\nThe council produces a free map of the city, available from its offices or from cycle shops, highlighting cycle paths, lanes and suggested cycle routes.\n\n===Strategy===\nThe council's Cycling Strategy was adopted in 1998. The 2007 update showed that 2.7% of people living in Cardiff cycled to work in 2001, an increase from 2.6% in 1991. However, an Omnibus survey showed that in 2003 and 2005, 3.6% and 4.3% of people cycled to work respectively. Although, the number of children cycling to school fell from 5% to 2% since 1989\u201391. In the strategy, the council intends to:<ref name=\"cardiff.gov.uk\"/>\n*encourage and promote cycling\n*provide safe facilities such as wider cycle lanes and advanced stop lines at traffic signals\n*conduct a trial scheme to assess the viability of allowing cycling through pedestrian areas in the city centre\n*improve cycle links between residential and commercial areas\n*facilitate integration with other modes of transport\n*improve and maintain the cycle network\n*develop and clearly sign routes\n\n=== Cycleways ===\nCardiff Council are in the process of developing 5 cycleways across the city<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/|title=Cardiff Council|website=www.cardiff.gov.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>. This falls in line with its strategy to provide far more segregation from motorised traffic for cyclists.\n\nWhile work on the routes has already broken ground<ref>{{Citation|title=Cycleway 1, Cardiff (under construction)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2XTvUpUryBE|language=en|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>, some have criticised both certain design flaws<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/travel/cycle-super-highways/Documents/CSH1.1%20Consultation%20Report%20ENG.pdf|title=CSH1.1 St Andrew\u2019s Crescent, St Andrew\u2019s Place and Senghennydd Road Consultation Report|date=2018-10-17|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> and how long it is taking for consultations to be published, with only two published within as many years. While some routes are essentially brand new, others are facelifts or changes of priority for current routes, such as Cycleway 3 on Lloyd George Avenue, and Cycleway 2 on Newport Road.\n\nThe proposed Cycleway routes are:\n\n* Cycleway 1: City Centre to Cathays, University Hospital Wales, Heath High Level and Heath Low Level Rail Stations, and North East Cardiff Strategic Development Site\n* Cycleway 2: City Centre to Adamsdown, Newport Road retail parks, Rumney, Llanrumney and St Mellons Business Park\n* Cycleway 3: City Centre to Cardiff Bay\n* Cycleway 4: City Centre to Llandaff, Danescourt and North West Strategic Development Site\n* Cycleway 5: City Centre to Riverside, Ely and Caerau.\n\n==Cycle facilities==\n[[File:Cycle lane in Excalibur Drive, Cardiff.jpg|right|thumb|Example from Excalibur Drive of the red cycle lanes used in Cardiff.]]\n\n===Cycle Shops===\nThe 2011 Cardiff Council cycle map listed 12 cycle shops (down from 14 in 2009) in the city: in [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]], [[Cathays]] (Crwys Road), [[Cathays]] (Woodville Road), [[Gabalfa]], [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]], [[Llandaff North]], [[Llanrumney]], [[Pontcanna]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bikeshedwales.com/|title=The Bike Shed, Cardiff. Electric Bikes, Road, Mountain, Hybrid, E Bikes, E-Bikes, Ebikes, Emtb, Kids. Trek, Genesis, Merida, Ridgeback, Bianchi, Raleigh, Electra, Pashley, Ragley, Dahon, Adventure. Sales and repair. The Friendly Bike Shop, Cathedral Road. Cardiff.|website=www.bikeshedwales.com|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>, [[Rhiwbina]], [[Roath]] (Broadway), [[Roath]] ([[Newport Road]]) and [[Whitchurch, Cardiff|Whitchurch]].<ref>Cardiff Council ''Cardiff Cycling map'' 6th edition (2011)</ref> Braddicks on Broadway, Roath, closed in January 2015 after 70 years trading.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/local-news/cardiff-cycle-shop-founded-empire-8544816 \"Cardiff cycle shop founded by Empire Games hero Reg Braddick closes after 70 years\"], ''Wales Online'', 29 January 2015.</ref>\n\n===Cycle lanes===\nSome roads in the city provide distinct cycle lanes to the left of the vehicle lane. According to the Cardiff Cycle Map, these include:\n;West Cardiff\n*''Cowbridge Road East'' and ''Castle Street'': main western approach from [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] to the city centre\n*''Wellington Street'': parallel to Cowbridge Road East and part of the [[A4161 road]]\n*''Pen-Hill Road'' and ''Cathedral Road'': in [[Pontcanna]]\n*''St Fagans Road and Pencisely Road'': roads approaching [[Waun-Gron Park railway station]] in [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]]\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''Caerphilly Road'': a main road in [[Birchgrove, Cardiff|Birchgrove]] from the city centre to northern suburbs and part of the [[A469 road]]\n*''Excalibur Drive'': leads from Caerphilly Road to [[Lisvane and Thornhill railway station]] in [[Thornhill, Cardiff|Thornhill]]\n*''Ty-Glas Road'': leads from Caerphilly Road through [[Llanishen]]\n*''Cathays Terrace'': connects Crwys Road (the main road through [[Cathays]]) and Corbett Road (around [[Cardiff University]])\n*''Fairoak Road'': connects Crwys Road and Wedal Road (near [[Roath Park]])\n\n[[File:Cycle only sign united kingdom.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Sign denoting a path only to be used by cyclists]]\n;South Cardiff\n*''Penarth Road'': part of the [[A4160 road]] leads from Callaghan Square near [[Cardiff Central railway station|Cardiff Central]] to [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]\n*''James Street:'' leads from [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] to [[Cardiff Bay]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''Llanrumney Avenue'': a main suburban road running through [[Llanrumney]]\n\n===Bus and cycle lanes===\nThere are also lanes that cyclists share with buses, motorcycles and taxis, in which it is illegal to drive on in any other motor vehicle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/1522524.thousands_of_motorists_to_be_caught_by_bus_lane_spy_cam/ |title=Thousands of motorists to be caught by bus lane spy cam (From The Argus) |publisher=Theargus.co.uk |date=5 July 2007 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> Such lanes are on:\n*''Newport Road'': in [[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]] and [[Roath]], East Cardiff\n*''Westgate Street'', ''St Mary Street'' and ''Wood Street'': in the City Centre\n*''Boulevard de Nantes'' and ''Dumfries Place'': leading from [[Cathays Park]] in the centre to Newport Road and East Cardiff\n*''Cowbridge Road East'': from [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] to [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely Bridge]] in West Cardiff\n*''Tudor Street'': a main city centre approach from [[Riverside, Cardiff|Riverside]] in West Cardiff\n\n===Segregated / off-road cycle paths===\n[[Segregated cycle facilities]] can be a shared [[Sidewalk|pavement]] with pedestrians, running alongside a road or through a park for example. This is denoted by a blue circular sign showing a bicycle and pedestrians. A cycle only route is denoted by blue circular sign showing only a bicycle. Much of the ''Taff Trail, Ely Trail'' and ''Rumney Trail'' are segregated from traffic. Other such routes in the city include:\n\n;West Cardiff\n*''[[Llandaff Fields]]'': through parkland area in [[Pontcanna]], connecting with the ''Taff Trail''\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''M4 Junction 32'': routes run under the junction from [[Coryton, Cardiff|Coryton]] to [[Tongwynlais]]\n*''Gabalfa Interchange'': routes run over and round the junction as an alternative to vehicle routes \n*''[[University Hospital of Wales]]'': routes run around Heath Hospital through King George Field\n\n;South Cardiff\n*North Road<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/transport-projects/Consultations/Documents/09.01.18/North%20Road%20Consultation%20Report%20ENG%2008.01.18.pdf|title=North Road / Corbett Road Cycleway Upgrade and Pedestrian Facilities|date=2019-08-22|website=North Road / Corbett Road Cycleway Upgrade and Pedestrian Facilities|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/transport-projects/Consultations/Documents/CO18041-%2801-05%29-B%20Concept%20Design.pdf|title=North Road Cycleway Upgrade Phase 2|date=2019-08-22|website=North Road Cycleway Upgrade Phase 2|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>: from the [[Royal Welsh College of Music & Drama]] to Llys Talybont, connecting to the ''Taff Trail''.\n*''Leckwith Road'': from [[Ninian Park railway station]] in [[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]] connecting to the ''Ely Trail.''\n*''[[Cardiff International Sports Village]]'': the vicinity has a network of segregated routes connected to the ''Ely Trail'' in the west, [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] in the north, and [[Cardiff Bay]] in the east.\n*''Lloyd George Avenue'': from the City Centre to Cardiff Bay, part of Route 8\n*''Central Link'': parallel to the east of Lloyd George Avenue\n*''[[Butetown]]: a route runs through a housing estate to Cardiff Bay, parallel to the west of Lloyd George Avenue\n*''Rover Way'': through an industrial and commercial estate between [[Adamsdown]] and [[Tremorfa]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''[[Llanedeyrn]]'': a route runs through the housing estate from St Mellons Road to Llanedeyrn Interchange\n*''Pentwyn Drive'': a route runs along this road in [[Pentwyn, Cardiff|Pentwyn]] around Wern-goch Park and connects with the ''Rumney Trail''\n*''[[St Mellons]]'': routes connect various parts of the suburb\n*''[[Llanrumney]]'': a route connects Llanrumney Avenue with Ball Road, near the ''Rumney Trail''\n\n===Cycle parking===\nThere are [[bicycle stand]]s for parking in locations including the following:\n\n;West Cardiff\n*''[[Canton, Cardiff|Canton]]'': Cowbridge Road East, Wellington Street and Llandaff Road\n*''[[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]]'': Fairwater Library\n\n;North Cardiff\n*''[[Rhiwbina]]'': [[Rhiwbina railway station]]\n*''[[Cathays]]'': North Road ([[A470 road]]) and [[Cathays Library]]\n*''[[Penylan]]'': Penylan Library\n\n;South Cardiff\n*''[[Cardiff Bay]]'': around [[Mermaid Quay]], [[Wales Millennium Centre]], [[Atlantic Wharf]] and West Bute Street\n\n;[[Cardiff City Centre]]\n*''Central Square'': for [[Cardiff Central bus station|Central bus]] and [[Cardiff Central railway station|railway stations]]\n*''Castle Street'': near [[Millennium Stadium]]\n*''Wood Street'': at Millennium Plaza\n*''The Hayes'': for [[Cardiff Central Library]]\n*''Westgate Street'': opposite Millennium Stadium\n*''The Friary'': for Queen Street\n*''Park Place'': for Queen Street\n*''Charles Street'': for Queen Street\n*''Churchill Way'': for Queen Street and [[Capitol Shopping Centre]]\n*''Queen Street'': near junction with Newport Road\n*''[[Cardiff Queen Street railway station]]''\n*''Callahagn Square''\n*''[[Cathays Park]]'': at [[City Hall, Cardiff|City Hall]]\n*''[[Adamsdown]]'': [[Roath Library]]\n\n;East Cardiff\n*''[[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]]'': Rumney Library\n*''[[Llanrumney]]'': Llanrumney Library\n*''[[St Mellons]]'': St Mellons Library\n\n===Cycle hire===\n[[File:Cardiff cycle hire 2010.jpg|thumb|2009 scheme cycle hire station on<br>Queen Street/Churchill Way]]\nPedal Power is a charity with their main bike centre in [[Pontcanna]] offering cycle hire facilities. Cycle training and cycle assessments are also available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffpedalpower.org/ |title=Home |publisher=Cardiffpedalpower.org |date=23 June 2010 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n====OYBike====\nIn March 2009 the [[Welsh Assembly Government]] and Cardiff Council announced plans to introduce a free cycle hire scheme, with bike racks placed around the city, allowing people to pick up bikes and ride them to another point, where they would leave the bike. Money would also be put into creating more strategic cycle routes and cycle lanes.<ref>{{cite web|author=Abby Alford |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/cardiff-news/2009/03/12/cardiff-transport-shake-up-must-work-91466-23125436/ |title=News \u2013 Cardiff News \u2013 Cardiff transport shake-up 'must work' |publisher=WalesOnline |date=12 March 2009 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> The system, similar to those in other large cities, launched in September 2009,<ref>[http://www.bikeradar.com/news/article/oybike-rental-scheme-a-success-in-cardiff-25570/ \"OYBike rental scheme a success in Cardiff: Council hopes for more fairweather converts\" 4 April 2010 at bikeradar.com] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/cardiff/2010/apr/07/cardiff-oybike-scheme-paris-velib \"OYBike fails to ring my bell\" Opinion \"With Cardiff's answer to the Parisian V\u00e9lib relaunching this spring, we decided to take a city SmartBike for a whirl\"] 8 April 2010, at theguardian.com, Accessed 14 September 2017</ref> and included 70 bikes and 35 hire points (initially 7) around the centre and the south of the city. The stations (in 2010) were: Central Station; Cardiff Castle; Central Library; Queen Street Station; Churchill Way; City Hall; eastern Queen Street; Cardiff Bay Station; County Hall; and Cardiff Bay Visitors\u2019 Centre.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmMap?OpenForm&ParentUNID=241B7D69F515D518802576380073E8D9 |title=Reinventing the wheel &#124; Rental Locations |publisher=OYBike |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100625215540/http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmMap?OpenForm&ParentUNID=241B7D69F515D518802576380073E8D9 |archivedate=25 June 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It was necessary to register before using a bike. The first half an hour was free after which a small hourly fee was payable. The scheme, which was part of a \u00a328.5&nbsp;million plan to encourage residents in the capital to use sustainable transport and ease congestion, was welcomed by campaigners.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/wales/south_east/8267199.stm |title=UK &#124; Wales &#124; South East Wales &#124; Public bike hire scheme for city |publisher=BBC News |date=22 September 2009 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Abby Alford |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/cardiff-news/2009/09/22/smart-bike-system-launch-91466-24747392/ |title=News \u2013 Cardiff News \u2013 Smart bike system launch |publisher=WalesOnline |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe cycle scheme run by [[OYBike]] ended in December 2011 after funding was removed by Cardiff council; the operator did not have other sponsors so the bikes along with their smart locks were removed from the city centre.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/local-news/brakes-put-bike-hire-scheme-1796236 \"Brakes put on bike hire scheme: A bike hire scheme is to be scrapped next month after Cardiff council ended its financial support.\" 16 November 2011 at walesonline.co.uk] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref>\n\n====Nextbike====\nIn June 2017 [[Nextbike]] was announced as the new provider of a public bike hire scheme for Cardiff. This would integrate new technology into the bikes, rather than the docking stations.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/cardiffs-new-bike-hire-scheme-13201489 Ruth Mosalski: \"Cardiff's new bike hire scheme expected to be up and running by this autumn\", 19 June 2017 at walesonline.co.uk] Accessed 14 September 2017</ref> Fifty bikes went 'live' in March 2018, with an official launch in May 2018 when the numbers would increase to 250.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/wales/2018-03-26/first-wave-of-nextbikes-arrive-in-cardiff-in-bid-to-reduce-congestion/ |title=First wave of nextbikes arrive in Cardiff in bid to reduce congestion |work=ITV News |date=26 March 2018 |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> The bikes could be rented via a website, a telephone hotline, or by downloading a [[mobile app]]. Standard charges were \u00a31 for every half hour period. Annual subscriptions were also available.<ref name=hugecyclingboom>{{cite news|author=Jessica Walford|url=https://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/cardiff-seeing-huge-cycling-boom-14778283 |title=Cardiff is seeing a huge cycling boom on back of city's new bike-hire scheme |work=Wales Online |date=13 June 2018 |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> Almost 7,800 people were registered for the scheme by June 2018.<ref name=hugecyclingboom /> Nextbike has been both popular and successful, with Cardiff Council backing the scheme<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/|title=Cardiff Council|website=www.cardiff.gov.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>.\n\n===Cycle refurbishment===\nCardiff Cycle Workshop, a bike workshop launched in July 2010 in [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely]], refurbishes and repairs unwanted cycles, saving old bikes from the landfill and revitalises them for new owners at cheaper prices. Cardiff Cycle Workshop has an agreement with [[Cardiff Council]] for cages to be placed in the waste facilities in [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]] and [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]] for members of the public to leave their unwanted bicycles. Then the bikes are refurbished, checked for safety and have parts replaced. The bikes are then sold for anything from \u00a310 to \u00a3150. Three year funding has come from the [[Big Lottery Fund]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/cardiff/2010/jul/07/cardiff-cycle-workshop-vintage-bikes-ely-dr-bike-cycle-training-wales Guardian Cardiff | New Cardiff Cycle Workshop opens as city sees vintage bike revival]</ref>\n\n==Cycling routes==\n\n===Ely Trail===\n[[File:Ely Trail Picnic Area.JPG|thumb|right|150px|A picnic area on the Ely Trail]]\nThe off-road ''Ely Trail'' is under development in the west and south of the city as of 2010, funded by the County Council, Visit Wales, and Countryside Council for Wales.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=7845 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182655/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=7845 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> So far completed is the northern section through [[St Fagans]], [[Fairwater, Cardiff|Fairwater]] and [[Ely, Cardiff|Ely]], and the southern section running from [[Leckwith]] to the south along the [[River Ely]] through [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]], finishing at the [[Cardiff International Sports Village]]. However, these sections are yet to be connected.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=5987 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182824/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=5987 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe route is connected to [[Cardiff City Centre]] via an off-road north-south route through [[Butetown]].<ref>Cardiff Cycling Map 2007</ref> The ''Taff Trail'' at [[Cardiff Bay]] can also be joined from the trail via Grangetown and Butetown.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=10831 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609182945/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=10831 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n<gallery>\nFile:Ely Trail Fairwater.JPG|The Ely Trail in Fairwater\nFile:Ely Trail St Fagans.JPG|The end of the Ely Trail in St Fagans\n</gallery>\n\n===Rhymney Trail===\nThe off-road ''Rhymney Trail'' is being developed by the Council as a commuting and recreational route along the [[Rhymney River]] in the east of the city. Currently completed is the section between [[Llanedeyrn]] and [[Rumney, Cardiff|Rumney]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=3620 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-04-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609183218/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/objview.asp?object_id=3620 |archivedate=9 June 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The Cardiff Cycle Map shows the route running off-road from Llanedeyrn Interchange, bypassing [[Llanrumney]] to the west, briefly joining Newport Road (B4487), and then heading south of Rumney to Wentloog Avenue (B4239). However, an off-road section also runs north-south through [[Pentwyn, Cardiff|Pentwyn]] from Llanedeyrn.\n\n===Taff Trail===\n[[File:Taff Trail sign, Grangetown.jpg|thumb|upright|100px|Taff Trail route sign in [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]]]\nThe 55-mile long ''[[Taff Trail]]'' runs from [[Cardiff Bay]] through [[Pontypridd]] and [[Merthyr Tydfil]] to [[Brecon]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ |title=Cycle the Taff Trail \u2013 Breath the Contrasts across South Wales |publisher=Tafftrail.org.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050707013107/http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ |archivedate=7 July 2005 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> forming part of the ''[[L\u00f4n Las Cymru]]'' \u2013 the [[National Cycle Network]] ''[[National Cycle Route 8|Route 8]]'' to [[Holyhead]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sustrans.org.uk/default.asp?sID=1215165108687 |title=Route 8 |publisher=Sustrans |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe route begins at [[Roald Dahl Plass]] in [[Cardiff Bay]] and runs mostly off-road through the city for {{convert|7.5|mi|km}} north around [[Grangetown, Cardiff|Grangetown]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://greenergrangetown.files.wordpress.com/2016/11/taff-embankment.pdf|title=Taff Embankment|website=Greener Grangetown|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> and the [[Cardiff City Centre|City Centre]], joining the [[River Taff]] in [[Bute Park]] before heading north-west through [[Llandaff]] and [[Radyr]], leaving the city at [[Tongwynlais]].\n\n===Route 88: Coastal route===\n[[File:Pont y Werin construction.JPG|thumb|left|150px|Pont y Werin under construction]]\n''Route 88'' is a proposed coastal route from [[Newport, Wales|Newport]] to [[Margam Country Park]] via [[Cardiff]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sustrans.org.uk/default.asp?sID=1099920442406 |title=Route 88 |publisher=Sustrans |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Pont y Werin===\n'''Pont y Werin''' ([[Welsh language|Welsh]] for ''The People's Bridge'') is a pedestrian and cyclist bridge spanning the [[River Ely]] between [[Cardiff Bay]] and [[Penarth]]. Costing approximately [[GBP|\u00a3]]4.5&nbsp;million, Pont y Werin crosses between the [[Cardiff International Sports Village]] and [[Penarth]], allowing the public to travel to the Sports Village via [[Cogan railway station]].<ref>[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=&id=5034&Positioning_Article_ID=&Language=&d1=0 Cardiff Council's proposed bridge] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609170317/http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=&id=5034&Positioning_Article_ID=&Language=&d1=0 |date=9 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\nOpened on 14 July 2010, the [[bascule bridge]] completes the {{convert|6.5|mi|km|adj=on}} Cardiff Bay circular walk and cycle route,<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/southeastwales/hi/people_and_places/nature/newsid_8599000/8599389.stm BBC News: ''First steps on bridge between Cardiff and the Vale'']</ref> and incorporates a 20-metre opening section to allow river traffic to pass.\n\n===Penarth===\nIn 2010 it was announced a commuter route for cyclists would be installed, aiming to improve transport links between Penarth and Cardiff Bay.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2010/10/29/cycle-lane-plan-for-penarth-to-cardiff-bay-route-91466-27562766/#ixzz13l3qcBn2 \"Cycle lane plan for Penarth to Cardiff Bay route\"], WalesOnline \u2013 29 October 2010</ref>{{update inline|date=August 2013}}\n\n==Integration==\n\n===Cardiff rail network===\nCycling is integrated into the city's [[Valley Lines|urban rail network]], which is operated by [[Transport for Wales Rail]]. Most trains have spaces for two cycles. However they are not permitted on services from [[Caerphilly railway station|Caerphilly]], [[Radyr railway station|Radyr]] (except the [[Cardiff City Line|City Line]]), [[Cadoxton railway station|Cadoxton]], and [[Ebbw Vale Town railway station|Ebbw Vale Town]] to [[Cardiff Queen Street railway station|Cardiff Queen Street]] or [[Cardiff Central railway station|Cardiff Central]] between 07:00 and 09:30, or services in the reverse direction 16:00 to 18:00 on weekdays. Outside these times, carriage is still at the discretion of the [[Conductor (transportation)#Train guard|guard]]. [[Folding bicycle|Folding cycles]] can be carried folded-up at any time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arrivatrainswales.co.uk/WorkArea/showcontent.aspx?id=5300 |title=showcontent |publisher=Arrivatrainswales.co.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525204448/http://www.arrivatrainswales.co.uk/WorkArea/showcontent.aspx?id=5300 |archivedate=25 May 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThere is cycle storage at Cardiff Central station on all platforms, at the front and rear entrances to the station, and in the Riverside car park.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/stations/CDF.html#Accessibility |title=National Rail Enquiries \u2013 Station Facilities for Cardiff Central |publisher=Nationalrail.co.uk |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n===National rail network===\nCycles are also permitted free of charge on the wider national network provided they can be safely stored in the designated areas and reservations through the [[train operating company|train operator]] are recommended. Bikes must be carried in the designated area of the train and can't be stored in aisles or vestibule areas. Cycles can not be carried on rail-replacement coach services. Folding bikes can be carried at all times as normal hand luggage.\n\nArriva Trains Wales also operates most of the [[Transport in Wales#Railways|Welsh rail network]] and its cycle policies apply to other services as well without the restrictions applied to the Cardiff rail network.\n\n===Buses===\nCycles can not be carried on bus services in Cardiff. However, a ''Beacons Bus'' runs on Sundays and Bank Holidays in summer to [[Brecon]] which tows a cycle trailer to carry cycles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cyclebreconbeacons.com/en/contactus_transport.html |title=How to get here \u2013 Cycling in the Brecon Beacons National Park |publisher=Cyclebreconbeacons.com |accessdate=10 July 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090930192528/http://www.cyclebreconbeacons.com/en/contactus_transport.html |archivedate=30 September 2009 }}</ref> Efforts have been made to ensure there is bike parking next to bus stops.\n\n==Cycling Campaigns in Cardiff==\n\n=== Sustrans Cymru ===\nSustrans is a UK sustainable transport charity that constructs safe cycle routes and other inititiatives to encourage people to walk or cycle. Their ''Valleys Cycle Network'' project aims to add 100 miles of vehicle-free routes in the Valleys of South Wales.<ref>[http://www.sustrans.org.uk/sustrans-near-you/wales Sustrans website \"Wales\"] Retrieved 10 September 2011.</ref>\n\nIn September 2011 it was announced that Sustrans Cymru were launching a new project in Cardiff funded by the Wales Government. This involved offering expert consultation to Cardiff householders to draw up personal travel plans, designed to reduce car journeys and encourage, amongst other things, increased use of bicycles.<ref>[http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2011/09/07/cardiff-to-spearhead-a-commuter-revolution-91466-29376067/ ''Cardiff to spearhead a commuter revolution''] Wales Online, 11 September 2011 (Retrieved 10 September 2011)</ref>\n\n===Cardiff Cycling Campaign===\nThe ''Cardiff Cycling Campaign'' campaigns for better provisions for cyclists in the city,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffcyclingcampaign.org.uk/ |title=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |date=11 March 2008 |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> believing that the council's attitude is inadequate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiffcyclingcampaign.org.uk/modules.php?name=FAQ&myfaq=yes&id_cat=1&categories= |title=FAQ |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign |date= |accessdate=10 July 2010}}</ref> While it welcomes the Council's commitment to consider the needs of cyclists, it argues that these should not be marginal in relation to the management of cars and buses. A sea-change in thinking is required and available Council funds need to be used imaginatively to create 'coherent and continuous routes' through the city for cyclists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cardiff-cycling-campaign.co.uk/information/useful-information/ |title=Useful Information |publisher=Cardiff Cycling Campaign website |date= |accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref> For example, safe cycling routes through the city centre were lost with the construction of the new St Davids 2 shopping centre.\n\nIn April 2006 the Campaign pointed out that only 2.7% of people cycled to work in Cardiff. Campaigners cycled through Cardiff city centre during a rush hour period, accompanied by local councillors and a Welsh Assembly Member. A participating councillor was quoted as saying 'I was happy to rise to the challenge but at times it was frightening. The cycle lanes were sometimes inadequate and complicated, and if I hadn't been with the campaign I probably would have got lost'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Councillors+are+told%3A+%27Get+on+your+bikes%27.-a0144554176 |title=''Councillors are told: 'Get on your bikes'.'' |publisher=South Wales Echo article reproduced by thefreelibrary.com |year=2006 |accessdate=4 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Cycle Cardiff===\n''Cycle Cardiff'' aims to raise awareness of cycling and organises bike rides in and around the city.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclecardiff.org.uk/ |title=Cycle Cardiff |publisher=www.cyclecardiff.org.uk |accessdate=10 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100327144130/http://www.cyclecardiff.org.uk/ |archive-date=27 March 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===World Naked Bike Ride===\nThe ''Cardiff World Naked Bike Ride'' has taken place annually since 2008. This is part of a globally coordinated [[World Naked Bike Ride]], designed to highlight the vulnerability of cyclists on the road and campaign for better cycling facilities. In June 2011 80 cyclists reportedly took part riding through the centre of Cardiff, many of them naked.<ref>[http://yourcardiff.walesonline.co.uk/2011/06/13/naked-bike-ride-takes-over-cardiffs-streets/ ''\"Naked bike ride takes over Cardiff's streets\"''] WalesOnline, 13 June 2011</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Outline of cycling]]\n*[https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Parking-roads-and-travel/travel/cycle-super-highways/Pages/default.aspx Cycleways - Cardiff.gov.uk]\n\n==References==\n{{Primary sources|date=April 2009}}\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Cycling in Cardiff}}\n*[http://www.cardiff.gov.uk/content.asp?nav=2870%2C4048%2C4196&parent_directory_id=2865 Cardiff Council cycling home page]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050707013107/http://www.tafftrail.org.uk/ Unofficial Taff Trail Website]\n*[http://www.sustrans.co.uk/webfiles/leaflets/Sustrans_Taff%20Trail_Nov08.pdf Official Taff Trail Leaflet]{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://www.routes2ride.org.uk/wales/routes2ride/taff_trail_cardiff_to_castell_coch/ Taff Trail in Cardiff]\n*[http://www.keepingcardiffmoving.co.uk/ Keeping Cardiff Moving]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091015212242/http://www.oybike.com/oybike/cms.nsf/customFrmHome?OpenForm&ParentUNID=5E8F660D1D16E66B80257638007563B5 OYBike \u2013 Cardiff Smart Bike hire]\n*[http://wiki.worldnakedbikeride.org/index.php?title=Cardiff World Naked Bike Ride, Cardiff] \n*[http://www.cardiffpedalpower.org/ Pedal Power Bike Hire ]\n{{Transport in Cardiff}}\n{{Cycling in different countries and cities}}\n\n[[Category:Cycling in Wales]]\n[[Category:Transport in Cardiff]]\n[[Category:Transport in Wales]]\n[[Category:Cycling by city|Cardiff]]\n", "name_user": "DannyS712", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixing the location of periods / full stops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cycling_in_Cardiff"}
{"title_page": "42 (number)", "text_new": "{{Infobox number\n| number = 42\n| divisor = 1, 2, 3, 6, 7, 14, 21, 42\n| unicode = *\n| greek prefix =\n| latin prefix =\n}}\n\n'''42''' ('''forty-two''') is the [[natural number]] that follows [[41 (number)|41]] and precedes [[43 (number)|43]].\n\n==Mathematics==\nit is very good because 42 is a good number\n\n==Science==\n* 42 is the [[atomic number]] of [[molybdenum]].\n* 42 is the [[atomic mass]] of one of the naturally occurring stable isotopes of [[calcium]].\n* The angle rounded to whole degrees for which a [[Water lens|rainbow]] appears (the critical angle).\n* In 1966, mathematician Paul Cooper theorized that the fastest, most efficient way to travel across continents would be to bore a straight hollow tube directly through the [[Earth]], connecting a set of [[antipodes]], remove the air from the tube and fall through.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Cooper |first=Paul W. |journal=American Journal of Physics |title=Through the Earth in Forty Minutes |volume=34 |year=1966 |issue=1 |pages=68\u201369 |doi=10.1119/1.1972773 |bibcode=1966AmJPh..34...68C }}</ref> The first half of the journey consists of free-fall acceleration, while the second half consists of an exactly equal deceleration. The time for such a journey works out to be 42&nbsp;minutes. Even if the tube does not pass through the exact center of the Earth, the time for a journey powered entirely by gravity (known as a [[gravity train]]) always works out to be 42&nbsp;minutes, so long as the tube remains friction-free, as while the force of gravity would be lessened, the distance traveled is reduced at an equal rate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,842469,00.html |title=To Everywhere in 42 Minutes |accessdate=2008-05-18 |work=Time |date=February 11, 1966 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512131156/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C842469%2C00.html |archivedate=12 May 2008 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FAFUSbIs5KA |title=Jumping into a 7,965&nbsp;mile deep hole |accessdate=2008-05-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080602142755/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FAFUSbIs5KA |archivedate=June 2, 2008 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> (The same idea was proposed, without calculation by [[Lewis Carroll]] in 1893 in ''[[Sylvie and Bruno Concluded]]''.<ref>{{cite book\n|last=Carroll |first=Lewis |authorlink=Lewis Carroll |others=illustrated by [[Harry Furniss]] |title=Sylvie and Bruno Concluded\n|volume=2 |date=29 December 1893 |publisher=Macmillan and Co. |location=United Kingdom |chapter=Chapter 7\n|quote=Each railway is in a long tunnel, perfectly straight: so of course the ''middle'' of it is nearer the centre of the globe than the two ends: so every train runs half-way ''down''-hill, and that gives it force enough to run the ''other'' half ''up''-hill.\n|title-link=Sylvie and Bruno Concluded }}</ref>) Now we know that is not true, and it only would take about [https://www.livescience.com/50312-how-long-to-fall-through-earth.html 38 minutes.]\n* As determined by the Babylonians, in 79 years Mars orbits the Sun almost exactly 42 times.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Martin J|title=Ancient astronomy and the naked-eye planets|url=http://www.eternalgadgetry.com/ancient_astronomy.html|website=Eternal Gadgetry|publisher=MS|accessdate=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Technology==\n* [[Magic number (programming)|Magic numbers]] used by [[programmer]]s:\n** In [[Tagged Image File Format|TIFF]] (Tagged Image File Format), the second [[16-bit]] [[Word (data type)|word]] of every file is 42, \"an arbitrary but carefully chosen number that further identifies the file as a TIFF file\".\n** In the [[reiser4]] file system, 42 is the [[inode]] number of the [[root directory]].\n** In the military [http://www.irig106.org/docs/106-09/chapter10.pdf IRIG 106 Chapter 10] data recording standard, the hex value 0x464F52545974776F (ASCII \"FORTYtwo\") is used as a magic number to identify directory blocks.\n* The [[GNU C Library]], a set of standard routines available for use in [[computer programming]], contains a [[subroutine|function]]\u2014'''<kbd>memfrob()</kbd>'''\u2014which performs an [[exclusive or|XOR]] combination of a given variable and the [[Binary numeral system|binary]] pattern 00101010 (42) as an [[XOR cipher]].\n* [[Hexagonal tiling|Tiling a plane using regular hexagons]], which is [[honeycomb]] in appearance, is [[Hexagonal tiling#Topologically equivalent tilings|approximated in a topological sense]] to an accuracy of better than 1% using a [[Brickwork#Bonds|stretcher bond brick pattern]] with bricks of 42 squares (6 by 7).<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Lee Middleton|author2=Jayanthi Sivaswamy|title=Framework for practical hexagonal-image processing|journal=Journal of Electronic Imaging|volume=11|issue=104|pages=104|year=2002|doi=10.1117/1.1426078|bibcode=2002JEI....11..104M}}</ref>\n* The password expiration policy for a [[Windows domain|Microsoft Windows domain]] defaults to 42 days.<ref>{{cite web|title=Maximum password age|url=https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/hh994573.aspx|publisher=Microsoft TechNet|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref>\n* The [[ASCII]] code 42 is for the [[asterisk]] symbol, being a [[Wildcard character|wildcard]] for everything.\n\n==Astronomy==\n* [[Messier object]] [[Orion Nebula|M42]], a [[apparent magnitude|magnitude]] 5.0 [[diffuse nebula]] in the [[constellation]] [[Orion (constellation)|Orion]], also known as the [[Orion Nebula]].\n* The [[New General Catalogue]] object [[NGC 42]], a [[spiral galaxy]] in the constellation [[Pegasus (constellation)|Pegasus]].\n* In January 2004, [[asteroid]] {{mp|2001 DA|42}} was given the permanent name [[25924 Douglasadams]], for the author [[Douglas Adams]] who popularized the number 42 and died in 2001. [[Brian G. Marsden]], the director of the [[Minor Planet Center]] and the secretary for the naming committee, remarked that, with even his initials in the provisional designation, \"This was sort of made for him, wasn't it?\".\n* [[Kepler-42]], a red dwarf in the constellation [[Cygnus (constellation)|Cygnus]] which hosts the three smallest [[exoplanets]] found to date.\n* [[42 Isis]], a large [[main-belt]] [[asteroid]] measuring about 100&nbsp;km in diameter.\n\n==Religion==\n* [[Western religions]]\n** ''[[Ancient Egypt]]'': Over most of pharonic Egyptian history, the empire was divided into 42 [[Nome (Egypt) | nomes]].  Ancient Egyptian religion and mythological structure frequently model this terrestrial structure. <ref>{{cite book |last1=Assman |first1=Jan |title=Of God and Gods: Egypt, Israel, and the Rise of Monotheism (George L. Mosse Series in Modern European Cultural and Intellectual History) |date=2008 |publisher=The University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=978-0299225544 |page=Kindle Location 195 |edition=Kindle}}</ref>  \n*** ''42 body parts of Osiris'': In some traditions of the [[Osiris#Mythology|Osiris]] myth, Seth slays Osiris and distributes his 42 body parts all over Egypt.  (In others, the number is fourteen and sixteen).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Assman |first1=Jan |title=Of God and Gods: Egypt, Israel, and the Rise of Monotheism (George L. Mosse Series in Modern European Cultural and Intellectual History) |date=2008 |publisher=The University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=978-0299225544 |page=Kindle Location 576 |edition=Kindle}}</ref>\n*** ''42 books in the core library'': Clement of Alexandria states that the Egyptian temple library is divided into 42 \"absolutely necessary\" books that formed the stock of a core library.  36 contain the entire philosophy of the Egyptians which are memorized by the priests. While the remaining 6, are learned by the Pastophoroi (image-bearers).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Assman |first1=Jan |title=Of God and Gods: Egypt, Israel, and the Rise of Monotheism (George L. Mosse Series in Modern European Cultural and Intellectual History) |date=2008 |publisher=The University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=978-0299225544 |page=Kindle Location 1364|edition=Kindle}}</ref>  <ref>{{cite book |last1=Clement of Alexandria |editor1-last=Roberts |editor1-first=Alexander |editor2-first=Sir | editor2-last=James |editor3-last=Coxe |editor3-first=Arthur |title=The Stromata, or Miscellanies (With Active Table of Contents) |date=1885 |page=Kindle Location 11498 |edition=Kindle |chapter-url=https://www.amazon.com/Stromata-Miscellanies-Active-Table-Contents-ebook/dp/B005YIEMGQ |chapter=Book VI:IV}}</ref> (36 is like-wise a sacred number in Egyptian thought, related to time, in particular the thirty-six [[Decan]] stars and the thirty-six, 10-day \"weeks\" in the [[Egyptian calendar| Egyptian year ]] <ref>{{cite book |last1=Assman |first1=Jan |title=Of God and Gods: Egypt, Israel, and the Rise of Monotheism (George L. Mosse Series in Modern European Cultural and Intellectual History) |date=2008 |publisher=The University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=978-0299225544 |page=Kindle Location 1380|edition=Kindle}}</ref>.) The 42 books were not canonized like the Hebrew bible; they only supported and never replaced temple ritual. Hence, the destruction of the Egyptian temples and the cessation of the rituals ended Egyptian cultural continuity. <ref>{{cite book |last1=Assman |first1=Jan |title=Of God and Gods: Egypt, Israel, and the Rise of Monotheism (George L. Mosse Series in Modern European Cultural and Intellectual History) |date=2008 |publisher=The University of Wisconsin Press |isbn=978-0299225544 |page=Kindle Location 1418 |edition=Kindle}}</ref>\n*** ''42 negative confessions'':  In [[Egyptian mythology]], there are 42 questions asked of persons making their journey through Death. [[Ma'at]], a female personification, considered to be both maternal and a delivering force, is an Ancient Egyptian personification of physical and moral law, order, and truth. In the judgment scene described in the Egyptian and the Book of Pass (the [[Book of the Dead]], which evolved from the [[Coffin Texts]] and the [[Pyramid Texts]]), there are 42 questions personifying the analysis of [[Ma'at]]. If the departed reasonably can give answers to the 42 questions, they have the potential to either be reincarnate, or if completely successful, reach the ultimate goal of becoming a Star, whereon, they can continue to give Light, and fuel Universal growth. These 42 questions correspond to the \"42 Negative Confessions\" from funerary texts such as the [[Maat#42_Negative_Confessions_(Papyrus_of_Ani) | Papyrus of Ani]].\n** There are 42 [[Stations of the Exodus]] which are the locations visited by the [[Israelite|Israelites]] following their [[The Exodus|exodus from Egypt]], recorded in [https://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0433.htm#1 Numbers 33], with variations also recorded in the books of [[Book of Exodus|Exodus]] and [[Deuteronomy]].\n**42 is the number with which God creates the Universe in [[Kabbalah|Kabbalistic tradition]]. In Kabbalah, the most significant name is that of the En Sof (also known as \"[[Ein Sof]]\", \"Infinite\" or \"Endless\"), who is above the Sefirot (sometimes spelled \"[[Sephirot]]\").<ref>{{cite web|url=http://physics.ucsc.edu/cosmo/primack_abrams/InABeginningTikkun1995.pdf|title=In A Beginning...Quantum Cosmology and Kabbalah|accessdate=2008-03-14|author1=Joel Primack|author2=Nancy E. Abrams}}</ref> The Forty-Two-Lettered Name contains four combined names which are spelled in Hebrew letters  (spelled in letters   = 42 letters), which is the name of Azilut (or \"[[Atziluth]]\" \"Emanation\"). While there are obvious links between the Forty-Two Lettered Name of the Babylonian Talmud and the Kabbalah's Forty-Two Lettered Name, they are probably not identical because of the Kabbalah's emphasis on numbers. The Kabbalah also contains a Forty-Five Lettered Name and a Seventy-Two Lettered Name.\n** The number 42 appears in various contexts in [[Christianity]]. There are 42 generations (names) in the [[Gospel of Matthew]]'s version of the [[Genealogy of Jesus]]; it is prophesied that for 42 months the [[The Beast (Revelation)|Beast]] will hold dominion over the Earth ([[Book of Revelation|Revelation]] 13:5); 42 men of Beth-azmaveth were counted in the [[census]] of men of [[Israel]] upon return from exile ([[Book of Ezra|Ezra]] 2:24); [[God in Christianity|God]] sent bears to maul 42 of the teenage boys who mocked [[Elisha]] for his baldness ([[Books of Kings|2 Kings]] 2:23), etc.\n** In [[Judaism]], the number (in the ''Babylonian Talmud'', compiled 375&nbsp;AD to 499&nbsp;AD) of the \"Forty-Two Lettered Name\" ascribed to God. Rab (or Rabhs), a 3rd-century source in the Talmud stated \"The Forty-Two Lettered Name is entrusted only to him who is pious, meek, middle-aged, free from bad temper, sober, and not insistent on his rights\". [Source: ''Talmud Kidduschin'' 71a, Translated by Rabbi Dr. I. Epstein]. [[Maimonides]] felt that the original Talmudic Forty-Two Lettered Name was perhaps composed of several combined divine names [Maimonides \"Moreh\"]. The apparently unpronouncable [[Tetragrammaton]] provides the backdrop from the Twelve-Lettered Name and the Forty-Two Lettered Name of the Talmud.{{Citation needed|date=February 2011}}\n** In [[Judaism]], by some traditions the [[Sefer Torah|Torah scroll]] is written with no fewer than 42 lines per column, based on the journeys of Israel. <ref>{{cite book |last1=Ganzfried |first1=R. Solomon |translator-last1=Friendman |translator-first1=Jen |editor1-link=translation |title= \u05e7\u05e1\u05ea \u05d4\u05e1\u05d5\u05e4\u05e8|trans-title =Keset haSofer |date=1902|publisher=\u05d3\u05e4\u05d5\u05e1 \u05d9\u05d5\u05e1\u05e3 \u05de\u05d0\u05d9\u05e8 \u05d1\u05dc\u05d9\u05d9\u05e2\u05e8 |location=Bardejov |edition=First |url=http://www.hasoferet.com/halakha-for-scribes/keset-ha-sofer/chapter-13 | language=Hebrew,English | quote=It is the custom to have no fewer than 48 lines, representing the journeys of Israel, and some say no fewer than 42, because of what God did in the Sinai wilderness at Kadesh. Also, we don\u2019t have more than 60 lines, representing the 60 myriads of Israel who received the Torah.}}</ref> In the present day, 42 lines is the most common standard <ref> {{cite encyclopedia\n  | first1 = Joseph \n  | last1 = Jacobs\n  | first2 = Judah \n  | last2 = Eisenstein\n  | first3 = Executive Committee of the Editorial Board\n  | last3 = .\n  | first4 = Ludwig \n  | last4 = Blau \n  | encyclopedia = Jewish Encyclopedia\n  | title = SCROLL OF THE LAW (Hebrew, \"Sefer Torah\")\n  | url = http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/articles/13358-scroll-of-the-law#1288\n  | access-date = 12 February 2020\n  | language = English\n  | year = 1906\n  | quote = \"(At the present day the forty-two-lined column is the generally accepted style of the scroll, its length being about 24 inches.)\"\n}} </ref>, but various traditions remain in use (see [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sefer_Torah]).\n** The [[Gutenberg Bible]] is also known as the \"42-line Bible\", as the book contained 42 lines per page.\n** The [[Forty-Two Articles|Forty-Two Articles (1552)]], largely the work of [[Thomas Cranmer]], were intended to summarize Anglican doctrine, as it now existed under the reign of [[Edward VI]].\n* [[Eastern religions]]\n** In Japanese culture, the number 42 is considered unlucky because the numerals when pronounced separately\u2014''shi ni'' (four two)\u2014sound like the word \"[[death|dying]]\"<ref>Niiya, Brian. Japanese American history: an A-to-Z reference from 1868 to the present. Facts on File, Inc., 1993, p. 352</ref> like a Latin word \"[[mori]]\".\n** The [[Sutra of 42 Sections]] is a Buddhist scripture.\n\n==Popular culture==\n===''The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy''===<!-- This section is linked from [[Douglas Adams]] -->\n[[File:Answer to Life.png|thumb|The Answer to the Ultimate Question of Life, The Universe, and Everything.]]\nThe number 42 is, in ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (novel)|The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]'' by [[Douglas Adams]], the \"[[Phrases from The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy#Answer to the Ultimate Question of Life, the Universe, and Everything (42)|Answer to the Ultimate Question of Life, the Universe, and Everything]]\", calculated by [[Deep Thought (The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy)|an enormous supercomputer named Deep Thought]] over a period of 7.5 million years. Unfortunately, no one knows what the question is. Thus, to calculate the Ultimate Question, a special computer the size of a small planet was built from organic components and named \"Earth\". The Ultimate Question \"What do you get when you multiply six by nine\"<!-- please do not change to seven--><ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://kasmana.people.cofc.edu/MATHFICT/mfview.php?callnumber=mf458\n|title=Mathematical Fiction: Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (1979)\n|accessdate=30 November 2016\n}} See this website for possible explanations of this seeming error.</ref> was found by Arthur Dent and Ford Prefect in the second book of the series, ''[[The Restaurant at the End of the Universe]]''. This appeared first in the [[radio play]] and later in the novelization of ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]''. The fact that Adams named the episodes of the radio play \"fits\", the same archaic title for a chapter or section used by Lewis Carroll in ''[[The Hunting of the Snark]]'', suggests that Adams was influenced by Carroll's fascination with and frequent use of the number. The fourth book in the series, {{H2G2|book|4|link=yes}}, contains 42 chapters.  According to {{H2G2|book|5|link=yes}}, 42 is the street address of Stavromula Beta. In 1994 Adams created the ''[[42 Puzzle]]'', a game based on the number 42.\n\nThe book ''42: Douglas Adams' Amazingly Accurate Answer to Life, the Universe and Everything'' (2011)<ref>{{cite news |last=Gill |first=Peter |title=42: Douglas Adams' Amazingly Accurate Answer to Life the Universe and Everything |url= https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/feb/03/douglas-adams-42-hitchhiker?INTCMP=SRCH |newspaper=Guardian |accessdate=3 April 2011 |location=London |date=February 3, 2011}}</ref> examines Adams' choice of the number 42, and contains a compendium of some instances of the number in science, popular culture, and humour.\n\n===Works of Lewis Carroll===\n[[Lewis Carroll]], who was a mathematician,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_hb346/is_1_38/ai_n29162565/|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120629081121/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_hb346/is_1_38/ai_n29162565/|url-status=dead |title=Lewis Carroll and Douglas Adams - Word Ways - Find Articles|date=29 June 2012|archivedate=29 June 2012|publisher=}}</ref> made repeated use of this number in his writings.<ref>''The Mystery of Lewis Carroll,'' Jenny Woolf</ref>\n\nExamples of Carroll's use of 42:\n* ''[[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland]]'' has 42 illustrations.\n* Alice's attempts at multiplication (chapter two of ''Alice in Wonderland'') work if one uses base 18 to write the first answer, and increases the base by threes to 21, 24, etc. (the answers working up to 4 \u00d7 12 = \"19\" in base 39), but \"breaks\" precisely when one attempts the answer to 4 \u00d7 13 in base 42, leading Alice to declare \"oh dear! I shall never get to twenty at that rate!\"\n* Rule Forty-two in ''Alice's Adventures in Wonderland'' (\"All persons more than a mile high to leave the court\").\n* Rule 42 of the Code in the preface<ref name=\"CarrollSnark\">{{cite web| url= http://www.snrk.de/snarkhunt/?newpics=no#preface |title=The Hunting of the Snark |first=Lewis |last=Carroll |authorlink= Lewis Carroll |publisher=}}</ref> to ''[[The Hunting of the Snark]]'' (\"No one shall speak to the Man at the Helm\").\n* In \"fit the first\" of ''[[The Hunting of the Snark]]'' the Baker had \"forty-two boxes, all carefully packed, With his name painted clearly on each.\"<ref name=\"CarrollSnark\"/>\n* The White Queen announces her age as \"one hundred and one, five months and a day\", which\u2014if the best possible date is assumed for the action of ''[[Through the Looking-Glass]]'' (e.g., a date is chosen such that the rollover from February to March is excluded from what would otherwise be an imprecise measurement of \"five months and a day\")\u2014gives a total of 37,044 days.  If the Red Queen, as part of the same chess set, is regarded as the same age, their combined age is 74,088 days, or 42 \u00d7 42 \u00d7 42.<ref>[http://www.slate.com/id/2245647/ What Lewis Carroll Taught Us: Alice's creator knew all about role-playing.] by Seth Lerer, March 4, 2010</ref>\n\n===Music===\n* [[Level 42]] is an English [[pop music|pop]]/[[rock music|rock]] music band.\n* \"[[42 (song)|42]]\" is one of the tracks on [[Coldplay]]\u2032s 2008 album ''[[Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends]]''.\n* \"[[Channel 42 (song)|Channel 42]]\" is an electronic music song by [[deadmau5]] featuring [[Wolfgang Gartner]]; it appears on the 2012 deadmau5 album ''[[Album Title Goes Here]]''.\n* \"42\" is a song from Mumford and Sons\u2032 2018 album ''[[Delta (Mumford & Sons album)|Delta]]''.\n* \"42\" is a song written and produced by hip-hop and record production trio [[3Racha]], which consists of members [[Bang Chan]], [[Han Ji-sung|Han Jisung]], and [[Seo Chang-bin|Seo Changbin]] of popular k-pop group [[Stray Kids]]. A lyric in this song states, \u201cWhy do we live? What\u2019s the purpose? Is it 42? Stop speaking nonsense,\u201d which directly references to ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]''\u2019s definition of 42.\n* \"42\" is a song from the 2019 album ''[[Don\u2032t Panic (IZZ album)|Don\u2032t Panic]]'' by the progressive rock band [[IZZ]].  The album is a partial concept album based on ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]''.\n\n===Finance===\nThe statutory price of gold is set by law has been constant at $42 per fine troy ounce since 1973.<ref name=\"Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System\">{{cite web |title=Does the Federal Reserve own or hold gold? |website=Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System |url=https://www.federalreserve.gov/faqs/does-the-federal-reserve-own-or-hold-gold.htm |access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n===Television and film===\n* ''[[The Kumars at No. 42]]'' television series\n* \"[[42 (Doctor Who)|42]]\" is an episode of ''[[Doctor Who]]'', set in [[Real time (media)|real time]] lasting approximately 42&nbsp;minutes.\n* On the game show ''[[Jeopardy!]]'',  \"[[Watson (computer)|Watson]]\" the IBM supercomputer, has 42 \"threads\" in its avatar.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/id/2284721/|title=Watson Jeopardy! computer: Ken Jennings describes what it's like to play against a machine.|work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]|accessdate=2 October 2015}}</ref>\n* ''[[42 (film)|42]]'' is a film on the life of American baseball player Jackie Robinson.\n* ''[[Captain Harlock]]'' is sometimes seen wearing clothing with the number 42 on it.\n* In ''[[Stargate Atlantis (season 4)]]'' \"Quarantine\", Colonel Sheppard states that Dr. McKay's password ends in 42 because \"It's the ultimate answer to the great question of life, the universe and everything.\"\n* In ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'', the Festival of the Ancestors on Planet Pasaana is held every 42 years. The film itself was released in 2019, 42 years after the 1977 original ''[[Star Wars (film)|Star Wars]]'' film.  By a \"whole string of pretty meaningless coincidences\"<ref>{{cite book |last1=Adams |first1=Douglas |title=The Ultimate Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy |date=September 29, 2010 |publisher=Del Ray |isbn=978-0-307-49846-5 |page=27 |edition=Kindle}}</ref>, 2019 is the same year that 42 was found to be the last possible natural number below 100 to be expressed as a [[sum of three cubes]].<ref name=\"booker2019\"/>\n\n===Video games===\n* [[42 Entertainment]] is the company responsible for several [[alternate reality game]]s, including ''[[I Love Bees]]'', ''[[Year Zero (game)|Year Zero]]'', and ''Why So Serious''.\n* ''[[Tokyo 42]]'' is a videogame released in 2017.\n*''[[Squadron 42]]'' is a videogame set in the Star Citizen Universe with an unspecified release date.\n\n===Sports===\n[[File:Jrobinson.jpg|thumb|right|[[Jackie Robinson]] in his now-retired number 42 jersey]]\n* The [[squad number|jersey number]] of [[Jackie Robinson]], which is the only number [[retired number|retired]] by all [[Major League Baseball]] teams. Although the number was retired in 1997, [[Mariano Rivera]] of the [[New York Yankees]], the last professional baseball player to wear number 42, continued to wear it until he retired at the end of the 2013 season. As of the 2014 season, no player will ever again wear the number 42 in Major League Baseball except on [[Jackie Robinson Day]] (April 15), when ''all'' uniformed personnel (players, managers, coaches, and umpires) wear the number.\n* The number of [[laws of cricket]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lords.org/mcc/laws-of-cricket/|title=The Laws of Cricket|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Rule 42]] is the historic name of a [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] rule (now codified in Rule 5.1 and Rule 44) that in practice prohibits the playing of \"foreign sports\" (generally [[association football]] and the [[rugby football|rugby codes]]) at GAA grounds.\n\n===Architecture===\n* The architects of the [[Rockefeller Center]] in [[New York City]] worked daily in the [[Graybar Building]] where on \"the twenty-fifth floor, one enormous drafting room contained forty-two identical drawing boards, each the size of a six-seat dining room table; another room harboured twelve more, and an additional fourteen stood just outside the principals' offices at the top of the circular iron staircase connecting 25 to 26\".<ref>Okrent, Daniel. Great Fortune: the Epic of the Rockefeller Centre. Viking Penguin, 2003, p. 147</ref>\n* In the [[Rockefeller Center]] ([[New York City]]) there are a total of \"forty-two elevators in five separate banks\"<ref>Okrent, Daniel. Great Fortune: the Epic of the Rockefeller Centre. Viking Penguin, 2003, p. 162</ref> which carry tenants and visitors to the sixty-six floors.\n\n===Comics===\n* [[Miles Morales]] was bitten by a spider bearing the number 42, causing him to become a Spider-Man. The number was later heavily referenced in the film ''[[Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse]]''. The use of 42 within the franchise references Jackie Robinson's use of the number, though many fans incorrectly believed it to be a ''The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy'' reference.<ref name=\"Spider-Verse\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/spider-man-spider-verse-42-meaning-2019-2|title=Why the number 42 was hidden in plain sight throughout 'Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse'|first=Kim|last=Renfro|date=February 26, 2019|accessdate=November 29, 2019|publisher=[[Insider Inc.]]}}</ref>\n\n==Other fields==\n* +42 is the historical Select Country for the former country of [[Czechoslovakia]].\n* There are 42 US gallons in a [[Barrel of oil equivalent|barrel of oil]].\n* 42 is the number of the French [[Departments of France|department]] of [[Loire (department)|Loire]]. The number is also reflected in the [[Postal codes in France|postal code]] for that area.\n* [[Tower 42]] is a skyscraper in the [[City of London]], formerly known as the [[National Westminster Bank|NatWest]] Tower.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tower 42 - City of London |url=https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/services/environment-and-planning/building-control/our-projects/Pages/tower-42.aspx |website=cityoflondon.gov.uk |accessdate=23 October 2018}}</ref>\n* In [[New York City]], [[42nd Street (Manhattan)|42nd Street]] is a main and very popular two-way thoroughfare. Landmarks on it include the [[Chrysler Building]], [[Grand Central Terminal]], the main branch of the [[New York Public Library]], and [[Times Square]]. The [[Headquarters of the United Nations]] is at the east end of the street. The New York City street is also the setting for a [[42nd Street (film)|movie]] by the same name (which also gave fame to its [[42nd Street (song)|eponymous title song]]), and which later inspired a musical adaptation, ''[[42nd Street (musical)|42nd Street]]''.\n* 42 is the inspiration for the name of the 42 Center of Excellence for Artificial Intelligence, based in Vienna, Austria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://futurezone.at/thema/start-ups/42-neues-ki-start-up-von-jajah-gruender-daniel-mattes/165.491.442|title=42: Neues KI-Start-up von Jajah-Gr\u00fcnder Daniel Mattes|publisher=Futurezone|accessdate=2015-11-22}}</ref>\n* 42 is the name of the private [[computer science]] [[42 (school)|school]] with [[campus]]es located in [[Paris, France]], and [[Fremont, California]].\n* 42 in Chinese reads s\u00ec \u00e8r which is very close to sh\u00ec a (\u662f\u554a) and that means 'yes'. It was once popular among young Chinese to send 42 in short message which stands for 'yes'.{{citation needed|date=April 2018}}\n\n==Other languages==\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"margin:1em auto 1em auto;\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:bottom;\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Language\n! scope=\"col\" | Translation\n|-\n|[[Afrikaans Language|Afrikaans]] || ''{{lang|af|twee-en-veertig}}''\n|-\n|[[Albanian Language|Albanian]] || {{lang|sq|dyzetedy}}\n|-\n|[[Arabic numerals|Arabic]] || {{lang|ar|\u0625\u062b\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0623\u0631\u0628\u0639\u0648\u0646}} (''\u02beithn\u0101n wa \u02bearba\u02bf\u016bn'')\n|-\n|[[Basque language|Basque]] || ''{{lang|eu|berrogeita bi}}''\n\n|-\n|[[Bangla Language|Bangla]] || ''{{lang|bn|biyallis \u09ea\u09e8 \u09ac\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b2\u09cd\u09b2\u09bf\u09b6 }}''\n|-\n|[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]] || {{lang|be|\u0441\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043a \u0434\u0432\u0430}} (''sorak dva'')\n|-\n|[[Bosnian language|Bosnian]] || ''{{lang|bs|\u010detrdeset dva}}''\n|-\n|[[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]] || {{lang|bg|\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0442 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0435}} (''\u010detirideset i dve'')\n|-\n|[[Catalan language|Catalan]] || ''{{lang|ca|quaranta-dos}}''\n|-\n|[[Chinese numerals|Chinese]] || {{lang|zh|\u56db\u5341\u4e8c}} (<big>{{lang|zh|\u8086\u62fe\u8d30}}</big>) (''s\u00ecsh\u00ed'\u00e8r'')\n|-   \n|[[Chuvash numerals|Chuvash]] || \u0445\u0115\u0440\u0115\u0445 \u0438\u043a\u043a\u0115 (''x\u0115r\u0115x ikk\u0115'', IIXXXX)\n|-\n|[[Croatian language|Croatian]] || ''{{lang|hr|\u010detrdeset dva}}''\n|-\n|[[Czech language|Czech]] || ''{{lang|cs|\u010dty\u0159icet dva}}''\n|-\n|[[Danish language|Danish]] || ''{{lang|da|toogfyrre}}''\n|-\n|[[Maldivian language|Dhivehi]] || ''Saalhees Dheyh''\n|-\n|[[Dutch language|Dutch]] || ''{{lang|nl|twee\u00ebnveertig}}''\n|-\n|[[Esperanto]] || ''{{lang|eo|kvardek du}}''\n|-\n|[[Estonian language|Estonian]] || ''{{lang|et|nelik\u00fcmmend kaks}}''\n|-\n|[[Finnish language|Finnish]]|| ''{{lang|fi|nelj\u00e4kymment\u00e4kaksi}}''\n|-\n|[[Filipino language|Filipino]] || ''{{lang|fil|apatnapu't dalawa}}''\n|-\n|[[French language|French]] || ''{{lang|fr|quarante-deux}}''\n|-\n|[[West Frisian language|West Frisian]] || ''{{lang|fy|twaenfjirtich}}''\n|-\n|[[Galician language|Galician]] || ''{{lang|gl|corenta e dous}}''\n|-\n|[[Georgian language|Georgian]] || {{lang|ka|\u10dd\u10e0\u10db\u10dd\u10ea\u10d3\u10d0\u10dd\u10e0\u10d8}} (''ormocdaori'')\n|-\n|[[German language|German]] || ''{{lang|de|zweiundvierzig}}''\n|-\n|[[Greek language|Greek]]|| {{lang|el|\u03c3\u03b1\u03c1\u03ac\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1 \u03b4\u03cd\u03bf}} (''sar\u00e1nta d\u00fdo'')\n|-\n|[[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]|| ''betalis''\n|-\n|[[Hebrew numerals|Hebrew]] || {{lang|he|\u05d0\u05e8\u05d1\u05e2\u05d9\u05dd \u05d5\u05e9\u05ea\u05d9\u05d9\u05dd}} (''arbayim u-shtayim'')\n|-\n|[[Hindi language|Hindi]] || {{lang|hi|\u092c\u092f\u093e\u0932\u0940\u0938, \u096a\u0968}} (''bay\u0101l\u012bs'')\n|-\n|[[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] || ''{{lang|hu|negyvenkett\u0151}}''\n|-\n|[[Icelandic language|Icelandic]] || ''{{lang|is|fj\u00f6rut\u00edu og tveir}}''\n|-\n|[[Indonesian language|Indonesian]] || ''{{lang|id|empat puluh dua}}''\n|-\n|[[Irish language|Irish]] || ''{{lang|ga|daichead a d\u00f3}}''\n|-\n|[[Italian language|Italian]] || ''{{lang|it|quarantadue}}''\n|-\n|[[Japanese writing system|Japanese]]|| {{lang|ja|\u56db\u5341\u4e8c (\u3088\u3093\u3058\u3085\u3046\u306b)}} (''yonj\u016bni'')\n|-\n|[[Kazakh language|Kazakh]] || {{lang|kk|\u049b\u044b\u0440\u044b\u049b \u0435\u043a\u0456}} (''q\u0131r\u0131q eki'')\n|-\n|[[Korean writing system|Korean]]|| {{lang|ko|\uc0ac\uc2ed\uc774 / \ub9c8\ud754\ub458}} (''sasibi''/''maheundul'')\n|-\n|[[Kannada Language|Kannada]] || {{lang|kn|\u0ca8\u0cb2\u0cb5\u0ca4\u0ccd\u0ca4\u0cc1 \u0c8e\u0cb0\u0ca1\u0cc1}} (''nalavatthu eradu'')\n|-\n|[[Latvian language|Latvian]]|| ''{{lang|lv|\u010detrdesmit divi}}''\n|-\n|[[Livonian language|Livonian]]|| ''{{lang|liv|n\u0113\u013cakimd\u00f5 kak\u0161}}''\n|-\n|[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]]|| ''{{lang|lt|keturiasde\u0161imt du}}''\n|-\n|[[Lojban]]|| ''{{lang|jbo|vore}}''\n|-\n|[[Luxembourgish language|Luxembourgish]]|| ''{{lang|lb|zweeav\u00e9ierzeg}}''\n|-\n|[[Macedonian language|Macedonian]] || {{lang|mk|\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0442 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430}} (''\u010detirieset i dva'')\n|-\n|[[Malayalam language|Malayalam]] || <big>{{lang|ml|\u0d28\u0d3e\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41}}</big>\n|-\n|[[Maltese language|Maltese]] || ''{{lang|mt|tnejn u erbg\u0127in}}''\n|-\n|[[Maori language|M\u0101ori]] || ''{{lang|mi|wh\u0101 tekau ma rua}}''\n|-\n|[[Marathi language|Marathi]] || ''bechalis''\n|-\n|[[Mongolian language|Mongolian]] || {{lang|mn|\u0434\u04e9\u0447\u0438\u043d \u0445\u043e\u0451\u0440}} (''d\u00f6chin khoyor'')\n|-\n|[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] || ''{{lang|no|f\u00f8rtito}}''\n|-\n|[[Pashto 