|mejilelogoji}}''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Wiktionary|forty-two}}\n{{commonscatinline}}\n* {{cite web|last=Grime|first=James|title=42 and Douglas Adams|url=http://www.numberphile.com/videos/42.html|work=Numberphile|publisher=[[Brady Haran]]|author2=Gerardo Adesso|author3=Phil Moriarty|access-date=2013-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013132841/http://www.numberphile.com/videos/42.html|archive-date=2018-10-13|url-status=dead}}\n* [http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/42.html My latest favorite Number: 42], [[John C. Baez]]\n* [http://st-news.com/issues/st-news-volume-11-issues-1-2/features/the-significance/forty-two-in-real-life/ The number Forty-two in real life]\n{{Integers|zero}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:42 (Number)}}\n[[Category:Integers]]\n[[Category:In-jokes]]\n", "name_user": "135.0.207.30", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eMathematics)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/42_(number)"}
{"title_page": "Cycling at the 2019 European Games", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox sports competition event\n| event         = Cycling\n| competition   = 2019 European Games\n| image         = [[Image:Cycling (road) 2019 European Games.svg|100px]] [[Image:Cycling (track) 2019 European Games.svg|100px]]\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| venues        = [[Minsk]] city centre (Road)<br>[[Minsk Arena]] Velodrome (Track)\n| location      = [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]]\n| dates         = 22\u221230 June\n| competitors   = 542 (expected)\n| nations       = \n| teams         = \n| win_value     = \n| gold          = \n| silver        = \n| bronze        = \n| gold_nation   = \n| silver_nation = \n| bronze_nation = \n| previous      = [[Cycling at the 2015 European Games|2015]]\n| next          = [[Cycling at the 2023 European Games|2023]]\n}}\n{{Cycling at the 2019 European Games}}\nThe [[cycling]] competitions of the [[2019 European Games]] in [[Minsk]] were held at two venues, twenty-four events between 22 June and 30 June.\n\nThe venues were [[Minsk]] city centre for the road cycling road race<ref>{{cite web|url=https://minsk2019.by/en/belarus/belarus-sport/6 |title=Minsk European Games venues- Minsk city centre|publisher=minsk2019.by |date= |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref> and [[Minsk Arena]] Velodrome for the track cycling events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://minsk2019.by/en/belarus/belarus-sport/12|title=Minsk European Games venues- Minsk Arena|publisher=minsk2019.by |date= |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Cycling at the European Games|Cycling]] competitions have been contested in both of the European Games since the [[2015 European Games|first]] in 2015.\n\n==Venues==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Venue\n!Sport\n!Date\n!Medal events\n!Capacity\n|-\n| [[Minsk]] city centre || [[Road bicycle racing|Road cycling]]<br>(road race) ||align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"6\"| 22\u201325 June ||align=\"center\"| 4 ||data-sort-valu