resources/Olympics%20EuroGames/Minsk%20Results%20Book.pdf Cycling \u2212 Track \u2212 Results book]\n\n{{Events at the 2019 European Games}}\n{{2019 in road cycling}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cycling At The 2019 European Games}}\n[[Category:Sports at the 2019 European Games]]\n[[Category:Cycling at the European Games|2019]]\n[[Category:2019 in cycle racing|European Games]]\n[[Category:Cycling at the 2019 European Games| ]]\n[[Category:Cycle races in Belarus]]\n[[Category:2019 in road cycling|European Games]]\n[[Category:2019 in track cycling|European Games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox sports competition event\n| event         = Cycling\n| competition   = 2019 European Games\n| image         = [[Image:Cycling (road) 2019 European Games.svg|100px]] [[Image:Cycling (track) 2019 European Games.svg|100px]]\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| venues        = [[Minsk]] city centre (Road)<br>[[Minsk Arena]] Velodrome (Track)\n| location      = [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]]\n| dates         = 22\u221230 June\n| competitors   = 542 (expected)\n| nations       = \n| teams         = \n| win_value     = \n| gold          = \n| silver        = \n| bronze        = \n| gold_nation   = \n| silver_nation = \n| bronze_nation = \n| previous      = [[Cycling at the 2015 European Games|2015]]\n| next          = [[Cycling at the 2023 European Games|2023]]\n}}\n{{Cycling at the 2019 European Games}}\nThe [[cycling]] competitions of the [[2019 European Games]] in [[Minsk]] were held at two venues, twenty-four events between 22 June and 30 June.\n\nThe venues were [[Minsk]] city centre for the road cycling road race<ref>{{cite web|url=https://minsk2019.by/en/belarus/belarus-sport/6 |title=Minsk European Games venues- Minsk city centre|publisher=minsk2019.by |date= |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref> and [[Minsk Arena]] Velodrome for the track cycling events<ref>{{cite web|url=https://minsk2019.by/en/belarus/belarus-sport/12|title=Minsk European Games venues- Minsk Arena|publisher=minsk2019.by |date= |accessdate=24 October 2018}}</ref>.\n\n[[Cycling at the European Games|Cycling]] competitions have been contested in both of the European Games since the [[2015 European Games|first]] in 2015.\n\n==Venues==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Venue\n!Sport\n!Date\n!Medal events\n!Capacity\n|-\n| [[Minsk]] city centre || [[Road bicycle racing|Road cycling]]<br>(road race) ||align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"6\"| 22\u201325 June ||align=\"center\"| 4 ||data-sort-value=\"5001\"| Unlimited (standing)\n|-\n| [[Minsk Arena]] Velodrome || [[Track cycling]] ||align=\"center\" data-sort-value=\"19\"| 27\u201330 June ||align=\"center\"| 20 ||data-sort-value=\"25000\"| 2000 (seating)\n|}\n{{reflist|group=N}}\n\n==Qualification==\n{{main article|Cycling at the 2019 European Games \u2013 Qualification}}\n\n==Participation==\n===Participating nations===\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = BLR\n | flag_template  = flagIOC2\n | event          = 2019 European Games\n | team           = \n | gold_AUT = 0 | silver_AUT = 1 | bronze_AUT = 1\n | gold_BEL = 0 | silver_BEL = 0 | bronze_BEL = 1\n | gold_BLR = 2 | silver_BLR = 0 | bronze_BLR = 3 | host_BLR =yes\n | gold_CZE = 1 | silver_CZE = 0 | bronze_CZE = 2\n | gold_EST = 0 | silver_EST = 1 | bronze_EST = 0\n | gold_FRA = 0 | silver_FRA = 3 | bronze_FRA = 0\n | gold_GBR = 1 | silver_GBR = 1 | bronze_GBR = 2\n | gold_GRE = 2 | silver_GRE = 0 | bronze_GRE = 0\n | gold_ITA = 2 | silver_ITA = 5 | bronze_ITA = 2\n | gold_LTU = 1 | silver_LTU = 1 | bronze_LTU = 0\n | gold_NED = 7 | silver_NED = 7 | bronze_NED = 1\n | gold_POL = 0 | silver_POL = 1 | bronze_POL = 3\n | gold_POR = 0 | silver_POR = 1 | bronze_POR = 0\n | gold_RUS = 5 | silver_RUS = 1 | bronze_RUS = 7\n | gold_SUI = 2 | silver_SUI = 1 | bronze_SUI = 2\n | gold_UKR = 1 | silver_UKR = 1 | bronze_UKR = 0\n}}\n\n==Medal summary==\n===Road cycling===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event}}\n|-\n| Men's road race<b